50const char g_sliceTypeToChar[] = {'B', 'P', 'I'};
51
52/* Dolby Vision profile specific settings */
53typedef struct
54{
55 int bEmitHRDSEI;
56 int bEnableVideoSignalTypePresentFlag;
57 int bEnableColorDescriptionPresentFlag;
58 int bEnableAccessUnitDelimiters;
59 int bAnnexB;
60
61 /* VUI parameters specific to Dolby Vision Profile */
62 int videoFormat;
63 int bEnableVideoFullRangeFlag;
64 int transferCharacteristics;
65 int colorPrimaries;
66 int matrixCoeffs;
67
68 int doviProfileId;
69}DolbyVisionProfileSpec;
70
71DolbyVisionProfileSpec dovi[] =
72{
73 { 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 5, 1, 2, 2, 2, 50 },
74 { 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 5, 0, 16, 9, 9, 81 },
75 { 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 5, 0, 1, 1, 1, 82 }
76};
77
78typedef struct
79{
80 int bEnableVideoSignalTypePresentFlag;
81 int bEnableColorDescriptionPresentFlag;
82 int bEnableChromaLocInfoPresentFlag;
83 int colorPrimaries;
84 int transferCharacteristics;
85 int matrixCoeffs;
86 int bEnableVideoFullRangeFlag;
87 int chromaSampleLocTypeTopField;
88 int chromaSampleLocTypeBottomField;
89 const char* systemId;
90}VideoSignalTypePresets;
91

93{
94 {1, 1, 1, 6, 6, 6, 0, 0, 0, "BT601_525"},
95 {1, 1, 1, 5, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, "BT601_626"},
96 {1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, "BT709_YCC"},

112 * TODO: come up an algorithm for adoptive threshold */
113#define MVTHRESHOLD (10*10)
114#define PU_2Nx2N 1
115#define MAX_CHROMA_QP_OFFSET 12
116#define CONF_OFFSET_BYTES (2 * sizeof(int))
117static const char* defaultAnalysisFileName = "x265_analysis.dat";

121Encoder::Encoder()
122{
123 m_aborted = false;
124 m_reconfigure = false;
125 m_reconfigureRc = false;
126 m_encodedFrameNum = 0;
127 m_pocLast = -1;
128 m_curEncoder = 0;
129 m_numLumaWPFrames = 0;
130 m_numChromaWPFrames = 0;
131 m_numLumaWPBiFrames = 0;
132 m_numChromaWPBiFrames = 0;
133 m_lookahead = NULL;
134 m_rateControl = NULL;
135 m_dpb = NULL;
136 m_exportedPic = NULL;
137 m_numDelayedPic = 0;
138 m_outputCount = 0;
139 m_param = NULL;
140 m_latestParam = NULL;
141 m_threadPool = NULL;
142 m_analysisFileIn = NULL;
143 m_analysisFileOut = NULL;
144 m_naluFile = NULL;
145 m_offsetEmergency = NULL;
146 m_iFrameNum = 0;
147 m_iPPSQpMinus26 = 0;
148 m_rpsInSpsCount = 0;
149 m_cB = 1.0;
150 m_cR = 1.0;
151 for (int i = 0; i < X265_MAX_FRAME_THREADS; i++)
152 m_frameEncoder[i] = NULL;
153 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < DUP_BUFFER; i++)
154 m_dupBuffer[i] = NULL;
155 MotionEstimate::initScales();
156
157#if ENABLE_HDR10_PLUS
158 m_hdr10plus_api = hdr10plus_api_get();
159 m_numCimInfo = 0;
160 m_cim = NULL;
161#endif
162
163#if SVT_HEVC
164 m_svtAppData = NULL;
165#endif
166 m_prevTonemapPayload.payload = NULL;
167 m_startPoint = 0;
168 m_saveCTUSize = 0;
169 m_edgePic = NULL;
170 m_edgeHistThreshold = 0;
171 m_chromaHistThreshold = 0.0;
172 m_scaledEdgeThreshold = 0.0;
173 m_scaledChromaThreshold = 0.0;
174 m_zoneIndex = 0;
175}
176
177inline char *strcatFilename(const char *input, const char *suffix)
178{
179 char *output = X265_MALLOC(char, strlen(input) + strlen(suffix) + 1);
180 if (!output)
181 {
182 x265_log(NULL, X265_LOG_ERROR, "unable to allocate memory for filename\n");
183 return NULL;
184 }
185 strcpy(output, input);
186 strcat(output, suffix);
187 return output;
188}
189
190void Encoder::create()
191{
192 if (!primitives.pu[0].sad)
193 {
194 // this should be an impossible condition when using our public API, and indicates a serious bug.
195 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Primitives must be initialized before encoder is created\n");
196 abort();
197 }
198
199 x265_param* p = m_param;
200
201 int rows = (p->sourceHeight + p->maxCUSize - 1) >> g_log2Size[p->maxCUSize];
202 int cols = (p->sourceWidth + p->maxCUSize - 1) >> g_log2Size[p->maxCUSize];
203
204 if (m_param->bEnableFrameDuplication)
205 {
206 size_t framesize = 0;
207 int pixelbytes = p->sourceBitDepth > 8 ? 2 : 1;
208 for (int i = 0; i < x265_cli_csps[p->internalCsp].planes; i++)
209 {
210 int stride = (p->sourceWidth >> x265_cli_csps[p->internalCsp].width[i]) * pixelbytes;
211 framesize += (stride * (p->sourceHeight >> x265_cli_csps[p->internalCsp].height[i]));
212 }
213
214 //Sets the picture structure and emits it in the picture timing SEI message
215 m_param->pictureStructure = 0;
216
217 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < DUP_BUFFER; i++)
218 {
219 m_dupBuffer[i] = (AdaptiveFrameDuplication*)x265_malloc(sizeof(AdaptiveFrameDuplication));
220 m_dupBuffer[i]->dupPic = NULL;
221 m_dupBuffer[i]->dupPic = x265_picture_alloc();
222 x265_picture_init(p, m_dupBuffer[i]->dupPic);
223 m_dupBuffer[i]->dupPlane = NULL;
224 m_dupBuffer[i]->dupPlane = X265_MALLOC(char, framesize);
225 m_dupBuffer[i]->dupPic->planes[0] = m_dupBuffer[i]->dupPlane;
226 m_dupBuffer[i]->bOccupied = false;
227 m_dupBuffer[i]->bDup = false;
228 }
229
230 if (!(p->sourceBitDepth == 8 && p->internalBitDepth == 8))
231 {
232 int size = p->sourceWidth * p->sourceHeight;
233 int hshift = CHROMA_H_SHIFT(p->internalCsp);
234 int vshift = CHROMA_V_SHIFT(p->internalCsp);
235 int widthC = p->sourceWidth >> hshift;
236 int heightC = p->sourceHeight >> vshift;
237
238 m_dupPicOne[0] = X265_MALLOC(pixel, size);
239 m_dupPicTwo[0] = X265_MALLOC(pixel, size);
240 if (p->internalCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
241 {
242 for (int k = 1; k < 3; k++)
243 {
244 m_dupPicOne[k] = X265_MALLOC(pixel, widthC * heightC);
245 m_dupPicTwo[k] = X265_MALLOC(pixel, widthC * heightC);
246 }
247 }
248 }
249 }
250
251 if (m_param->bHistBasedSceneCut)
252 {
253 m_planeSizes[0] = (m_param->sourceWidth >> x265_cli_csps[p->internalCsp].width[0]) * (m_param->sourceHeight >> x265_cli_csps[m_param->internalCsp].height[0]);
254 uint32_t pixelbytes = m_param->internalBitDepth > 8 ? 2 : 1;
255 m_edgePic = X265_MALLOC(pixel, m_planeSizes[0] * pixelbytes);
256 m_edgeHistThreshold = m_param->edgeTransitionThreshold;
257 m_chromaHistThreshold = x265_min(m_edgeHistThreshold * 10.0, MAX_SCENECUT_THRESHOLD);
258 m_scaledEdgeThreshold = x265_min(m_edgeHistThreshold * SCENECUT_STRENGTH_FACTOR, MAX_SCENECUT_THRESHOLD);
259 m_scaledChromaThreshold = x265_min(m_chromaHistThreshold * SCENECUT_STRENGTH_FACTOR, MAX_SCENECUT_THRESHOLD);
260 if (m_param->sourceBitDepth != m_param->internalBitDepth)
261 {
262 int size = m_param->sourceWidth * m_param->sourceHeight;
263 int hshift = CHROMA_H_SHIFT(m_param->internalCsp);
264 int vshift = CHROMA_V_SHIFT(m_param->internalCsp);
265 int widthC = m_param->sourceWidth >> hshift;
266 int heightC = m_param->sourceHeight >> vshift;
267
268 m_inputPic[0] = X265_MALLOC(pixel, size);
269 if (m_param->internalCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
270 {
271 for (int j = 1; j < 3; j++)
272 {
273 m_inputPic[j] = X265_MALLOC(pixel, widthC * heightC);
274 }
275 }
276 }
277 }
278
279 // Do not allow WPP if only one row or fewer than 3 columns, it is pointless and unstable
280 if (rows == 1 || cols < 3)
281 {
282 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Too few rows/columns, --wpp disabled\n");
283 p->bEnableWavefront = 0;
284 }
285
286 bool allowPools = !p->numaPools || strcmp(p->numaPools, "none");
287
288 // Trim the thread pool if --wpp, --pme, and --pmode are disabled
289 if (!p->bEnableWavefront && !p->bDistributeModeAnalysis && !p->bDistributeMotionEstimation && !p->lookaheadSlices)
290 allowPools = false;
291
292 m_numPools = 0;
293 if (allowPools)
294 m_threadPool = ThreadPool::allocThreadPools(p, m_numPools, 0);
295 else
296 {
297 if (!p->frameNumThreads)
298 {
299 // auto-detect frame threads
300 int cpuCount = ThreadPool::getCpuCount();
301 ThreadPool::getFrameThreadsCount(p, cpuCount);
302 }
303 }
304
305 if (!m_numPools)
306 {
307 // issue warnings if any of these features were requested
308 if (p->bEnableWavefront)
309 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "No thread pool allocated, --wpp disabled\n");
310 if (p->bDistributeMotionEstimation)
311 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "No thread pool allocated, --pme disabled\n");
312 if (p->bDistributeModeAnalysis)
313 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "No thread pool allocated, --pmode disabled\n");
314 if (p->lookaheadSlices)
315 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "No thread pool allocated, --lookahead-slices disabled\n");
316
317 // disable all pool features if the thread pool is disabled or unusable.
318 p->bEnableWavefront = p->bDistributeModeAnalysis = p->bDistributeMotionEstimation = p->lookaheadSlices = 0;
319 }
320
321 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_INFO, "Slices : %d\n", p->maxSlices);
322
323 char buf[128];
324 int len = 0;
325 if (p->bEnableWavefront)
326 len += sprintf(buf + len, "wpp(%d rows)", rows);
327 if (p->bDistributeModeAnalysis)
328 len += sprintf(buf + len, "%spmode", len ? "+" : "");
329 if (p->bDistributeMotionEstimation)
330 len += sprintf(buf + len, "%spme ", len ? "+" : "");
331 if (!len)
332 strcpy(buf, "none");
333
334 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_INFO, "frame threads / pool features : %d / %s\n", p->frameNumThreads, buf);
335
336 for (int i = 0; i < m_param->frameNumThreads; i++)
337 {
338 m_frameEncoder[i] = new FrameEncoder;
339 m_frameEncoder[i]->m_nalList.m_annexB = !!m_param->bAnnexB;
340 }
341
342 if (m_numPools)
343 {
344 for (int i = 0; i < m_param->frameNumThreads; i++)
345 {
346 int pool = i % m_numPools;
347 m_frameEncoder[i]->m_pool = &m_threadPool[pool];
348 m_frameEncoder[i]->m_jpId = m_threadPool[pool].m_numProviders++;
349 m_threadPool[pool].m_jpTable[m_frameEncoder[i]->m_jpId] = m_frameEncoder[i];
350 }
351 for (int i = 0; i < m_numPools; i++)
352 m_threadPool[i].start();
353 }
354 else
355 {
356 /* CU stats and noise-reduction buffers are indexed by jpId, so it cannot be left as -1 */
357 for (int i = 0; i < m_param->frameNumThreads; i++)
358 m_frameEncoder[i]->m_jpId = 0;
359 }
360
361 if (!m_scalingList.init())
362 {
363 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Unable to allocate scaling list arrays\n");
364 m_aborted = true;
365 return;
366 }
367 else if (!m_param->scalingLists || !strcmp(m_param->scalingLists, "off"))
368 m_scalingList.m_bEnabled = false;
369 else if (!strcmp(m_param->scalingLists, "default"))
370 m_scalingList.setDefaultScalingList();
371 else if (m_scalingList.parseScalingList(m_param->scalingLists))
372 m_aborted = true;
373 int pools = m_numPools;
374 ThreadPool* lookAheadThreadPool = 0;
375 if (m_param->lookaheadThreads > 0)
376 {
377 lookAheadThreadPool = ThreadPool::allocThreadPools(p, pools, 1);
378 }
379 else
380 lookAheadThreadPool = m_threadPool;
381 m_lookahead = new Lookahead(m_param, lookAheadThreadPool);
382 if (pools)
383 {
384 m_lookahead->m_jpId = lookAheadThreadPool[0].m_numProviders++;
385 lookAheadThreadPool[0].m_jpTable[m_lookahead->m_jpId] = m_lookahead;
386 }
387 if (m_param->lookaheadThreads > 0)
388 for (int i = 0; i < pools; i++)
389 lookAheadThreadPool[i].start();
390 m_lookahead->m_numPools = pools;
391 m_dpb = new DPB(m_param);
392 m_rateControl = new RateControl(*m_param, this);
393 if (!m_param->bResetZoneConfig)
394 {
395 zoneReadCount = new ThreadSafeInteger[m_param->rc.zonefileCount];
396 zoneWriteCount = new ThreadSafeInteger[m_param->rc.zonefileCount];
397 }
398
399 initVPS(&m_vps);
400 initSPS(&m_sps);
401 initPPS(&m_pps);
402
403 if (m_param->rc.vbvBufferSize)
404 {
405 m_offsetEmergency = (uint16_t(*)[MAX_NUM_TR_CATEGORIES][MAX_NUM_TR_COEFFS])X265_MALLOC(uint16_t, MAX_NUM_TR_CATEGORIES * MAX_NUM_TR_COEFFS * (QP_MAX_MAX - QP_MAX_SPEC));
406 if (!m_offsetEmergency)
407 {
408 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Unable to allocate memory\n");
409 m_aborted = true;
410 return;
411 }
412
413 bool scalingEnabled = m_scalingList.m_bEnabled;
414 if (!scalingEnabled)
415 {
416 m_scalingList.setDefaultScalingList();
417 m_scalingList.setupQuantMatrices(m_sps.chromaFormatIdc);
418 }
419 else
420 m_scalingList.setupQuantMatrices(m_sps.chromaFormatIdc);
421
422 for (int q = 0; q < QP_MAX_MAX - QP_MAX_SPEC; q++)
423 {
424 for (int cat = 0; cat < MAX_NUM_TR_CATEGORIES; cat++)
425 {
426 uint16_t *nrOffset = m_offsetEmergency[q][cat];
427
428 int trSize = cat & 3;
429
430 int coefCount = 1 << ((trSize + 2) * 2);
431
432 /* Denoise chroma first then luma, then DC. */
433 int dcThreshold = (QP_MAX_MAX - QP_MAX_SPEC) * 2 / 3;
434 int lumaThreshold = (QP_MAX_MAX - QP_MAX_SPEC) * 2 / 3;
435 int chromaThreshold = 0;
436
437 int thresh = (cat < 4 || (cat >= 8 && cat < 12)) ? lumaThreshold : chromaThreshold;
438
439 double quantF = (double)(1ULL << (q / 6 + 16 + 8));
440
441 for (int i = 0; i < coefCount; i++)
442 {
443 /* True "emergency mode": remove all DCT coefficients */
444 if (q == QP_MAX_MAX - QP_MAX_SPEC - 1)
445 {
446 nrOffset[i] = INT16_MAX;
447 continue;
448 }
449
450 int iThresh = i == 0 ? dcThreshold : thresh;
451 if (q < iThresh)
452 {
453 nrOffset[i] = 0;
454 continue;
455 }
456
457 int numList = (cat >= 8) * 3 + ((int)!iThresh);
458
459 double pos = (double)(q - iThresh + 1) / (QP_MAX_MAX - QP_MAX_SPEC - iThresh);
460 double start = quantF / (m_scalingList.m_quantCoef[trSize][numList][QP_MAX_SPEC % 6][i]);
461
462 // Formula chosen as an exponential scale to vaguely mimic the effects of a higher quantizer.
463 double bias = (pow(2, pos * (QP_MAX_MAX - QP_MAX_SPEC)) * 0.003 - 0.003) * start;
464 nrOffset[i] = (uint16_t)X265_MIN(bias + 0.5, INT16_MAX);
465 }
466 }
467 }
468
469 if (!scalingEnabled)
470 {
471 m_scalingList.m_bEnabled = false;
472 m_scalingList.m_bDataPresent = false;
473 m_scalingList.setupQuantMatrices(m_sps.chromaFormatIdc);
474 }
475 }
476 else
477 m_scalingList.setupQuantMatrices(m_sps.chromaFormatIdc);
478
479 int numRows = (m_param->sourceHeight + m_param->maxCUSize - 1) / m_param->maxCUSize;
480 int numCols = (m_param->sourceWidth + m_param->maxCUSize - 1) / m_param->maxCUSize;
481 for (int i = 0; i < m_param->frameNumThreads; i++)
482 {
483 if (!m_frameEncoder[i]->init(this, numRows, numCols))
484 {
485 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Unable to initialize frame encoder, aborting\n");
486 m_aborted = true;
487 }
488 }
489
490 for (int i = 0; i < m_param->frameNumThreads; i++)
491 {
492 m_frameEncoder[i]->start();
493 m_frameEncoder[i]->m_done.wait(); /* wait for thread to initialize */
494 }
495
496 if (m_param->bEmitHRDSEI)
497 m_rateControl->initHRD(m_sps);
498
499 if (!m_rateControl->init(m_sps))
500 m_aborted = true;
501 if (!m_lookahead->create())
502 m_aborted = true;
503
504 initRefIdx();
505 if (m_param->analysisSave && m_param->bUseAnalysisFile)
506 {
507 char* temp = strcatFilename(m_param->analysisSave, ".temp");
508 if (!temp)
509 m_aborted = true;
510 else
511 {
512 m_analysisFileOut = x265_fopen(temp, "wb");
513 X265_FREE(temp);
514 }
515 if (!m_analysisFileOut)
516 {
517 x265_log_file(NULL, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Analysis save: failed to open file %s.temp\n", m_param->analysisSave);
518 m_aborted = true;
519 }
520 }
521
522 if (m_param->analysisMultiPassRefine || m_param->analysisMultiPassDistortion)
523 {
524 const char* name = m_param->analysisReuseFileName;
525 if (!name)
526 name = defaultAnalysisFileName;
527 if (m_param->rc.bStatWrite)
528 {
529 char* temp = strcatFilename(name, ".temp");
530 if (!temp)
531 m_aborted = true;
532 else
533 {
534 m_analysisFileOut = x265_fopen(temp, "wb");
535 X265_FREE(temp);
536 }
537 if (!m_analysisFileOut)
538 {
539 x265_log_file(NULL, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Analysis 2 pass: failed to open file %s.temp\n", name);
540 m_aborted = true;
541 }
542 }
543 if (m_param->rc.bStatRead)
544 {
545 m_analysisFileIn = x265_fopen(name, "rb");
546 if (!m_analysisFileIn)
547 {
548 x265_log_file(NULL, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Analysis 2 pass: failed to open file %s\n", name);
549 m_aborted = true;
550 }
551 }
552 }
553 m_bZeroLatency = !m_param->bframes && !m_param->lookaheadDepth && m_param->frameNumThreads == 1 && m_param->maxSlices == 1;
554 m_aborted |= parseLambdaFile(m_param);
555
556 m_encodeStartTime = x265_mdate();
557
558 m_nalList.m_annexB = !!m_param->bAnnexB;
559
560 if (m_param->naluFile)
561 {
562 m_naluFile = x265_fopen(m_param->naluFile, "r");
563 if (!m_naluFile)
564 {
565 x265_log_file(NULL, X265_LOG_ERROR, "%s file not found or Failed to open\n", m_param->naluFile);
566 m_aborted = true;
567 }
568 else
569 m_enableNal = 1;
570 }
571 else
572 m_enableNal = 0;
573
574#if ENABLE_HDR10_PLUS
575 if (m_bToneMap)
576 m_numCimInfo = m_hdr10plus_api->hdr10plus_json_to_movie_cim(m_param->toneMapFile, m_cim);
577#endif
578 if (m_param->bDynamicRefine)
579 {
580 /* Allocate memory for 1 GOP and reuse it for the subsequent GOPs */
581 int size = (m_param->keyframeMax + m_param->lookaheadDepth) * m_param->maxCUDepth * X265_REFINE_INTER_LEVELS;
582 CHECKED_MALLOC_ZERO(m_variance, uint64_t, size);
583 CHECKED_MALLOC_ZERO(m_rdCost, uint64_t, size);
584 CHECKED_MALLOC_ZERO(m_trainingCount, uint32_t, size);
585 return;
586 fail:
587 m_aborted = true;
588 }
589}
590
591void Encoder::stopJobs()
592{
593 if (m_rateControl)
594 m_rateControl->terminate(); // unblock all blocked RC calls
595
596 if (m_lookahead)
597 m_lookahead->stopJobs();
598
599 for (int i = 0; i < m_param->frameNumThreads; i++)
600 {
601 if (m_frameEncoder[i])
602 {
603 m_frameEncoder[i]->getEncodedPicture(m_nalList);
604 m_frameEncoder[i]->m_threadActive = false;
605 m_frameEncoder[i]->m_enable.trigger();
606 m_frameEncoder[i]->stop();
607 }
608 }
609
610 if (m_threadPool)
611 {
612 for (int i = 0; i < m_numPools; i++)
613 m_threadPool[i].stopWorkers();
614 }
615}
616
617int Encoder::copySlicetypePocAndSceneCut(int *slicetype, int *poc, int *sceneCut)
618{
619 Frame *FramePtr = m_dpb->m_picList.getCurFrame();
620 if (FramePtr != NULL)
621 {
622 *slicetype = FramePtr->m_lowres.sliceType;
623 *poc = FramePtr->m_encData->m_slice->m_poc;
624 *sceneCut = FramePtr->m_lowres.bScenecut;
625 }
626 else
627 {
628 x265_log(NULL, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Frame is still in lookahead pipeline, this API must be called after (poc >= lookaheadDepth + bframes + 2) condition check\n");
629 return -1;
630 }
631 return 0;
632}
633
634int Encoder::getRefFrameList(PicYuv** l0, PicYuv** l1, int sliceType, int poc, int* pocL0, int* pocL1)
635{
636 if (!(IS_X265_TYPE_I(sliceType)))
637 {
638 Frame *framePtr = m_dpb->m_picList.getPOC(poc);
639 if (framePtr != NULL)
640 {
641 for (int j = 0; j < framePtr->m_encData->m_slice->m_numRefIdx[0]; j++) // check only for --ref=n number of frames.
642 {
643 if (framePtr->m_encData->m_slice->m_refFrameList[0][j] && framePtr->m_encData->m_slice->m_refFrameList[0][j]->m_reconPic != NULL)
644 {
645 int l0POC = framePtr->m_encData->m_slice->m_refFrameList[0][j]->m_poc;
646 pocL0[j] = l0POC;
647 Frame* l0Fp = m_dpb->m_picList.getPOC(l0POC);
648 while (l0Fp->m_reconRowFlag[l0Fp->m_numRows - 1].get() == 0)
649 l0Fp->m_reconRowFlag[l0Fp->m_numRows - 1].waitForChange(0); /* If recon is not ready, current frame encoder has to wait. */
650 l0[j] = l0Fp->m_reconPic;
651 }
652 }
653 for (int j = 0; j < framePtr->m_encData->m_slice->m_numRefIdx[1]; j++) // check only for --ref=n number of frames.
654 {
655 if (framePtr->m_encData->m_slice->m_refFrameList[1][j] && framePtr->m_encData->m_slice->m_refFrameList[1][j]->m_reconPic != NULL)
656 {
657 int l1POC = framePtr->m_encData->m_slice->m_refFrameList[1][j]->m_poc;
658 pocL1[j] = l1POC;
659 Frame* l1Fp = m_dpb->m_picList.getPOC(l1POC);
660 while (l1Fp->m_reconRowFlag[l1Fp->m_numRows - 1].get() == 0)
661 l1Fp->m_reconRowFlag[l1Fp->m_numRows - 1].waitForChange(0); /* If recon is not ready, current frame encoder has to wait. */
662 l1[j] = l1Fp->m_reconPic;
663 }
664 }
665 }
666 else
667 {
668 x265_log(NULL, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Current frame is not in DPB piclist.\n");
669 return 1;
670 }
671 }
672 else
673 {
674 x265_log(NULL, X265_LOG_ERROR, "I frames does not have a refrence List\n");
675 return -1;
676 }
677 return 0;
678}
679
680int Encoder::setAnalysisDataAfterZScan(x265_analysis_data *analysis_data, Frame* curFrame)
681{
682 int mbImageWidth, mbImageHeight;
683 mbImageWidth = (curFrame->m_fencPic->m_picWidth + 16 - 1) >> 4; //AVC block sizes
684 mbImageHeight = (curFrame->m_fencPic->m_picHeight + 16 - 1) >> 4;
685 if (analysis_data->sliceType == X265_TYPE_IDR || analysis_data->sliceType == X265_TYPE_I)
686 {
687 curFrame->m_analysisData.sliceType = X265_TYPE_I;
688 if (m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel < 7)
689 return -1;
690 curFrame->m_analysisData.numPartitions = m_param->num4x4Partitions;
691 int num16x16inCUWidth = m_param->maxCUSize >> 4;
692 uint32_t ctuAddr, offset, cuPos;
693 x265_analysis_intra_data * intraData = curFrame->m_analysisData.intraData;
694 x265_analysis_intra_data * srcIntraData = analysis_data->intraData;
695 for (int i = 0; i < mbImageHeight; i++)
696 {
697 for (int j = 0; j < mbImageWidth; j++)
698 {
699 int mbIndex = j + i * mbImageWidth;
700 ctuAddr = (j / num16x16inCUWidth + ((i / num16x16inCUWidth) * (mbImageWidth / num16x16inCUWidth)));
701 offset = ((i % num16x16inCUWidth) << 5) + ((j % num16x16inCUWidth) << 4);
702 if ((j % 4 >= 2) && m_param->maxCUSize == 64)
703 offset += (2 * 16);
704 if ((i % 4 >= 2) && m_param->maxCUSize == 64)
705 offset += (2 * 32);
706 cuPos = ctuAddr * curFrame->m_analysisData.numPartitions + offset;
707 memcpy(&(intraData)->depth[cuPos], &(srcIntraData)->depth[mbIndex * 16], 16);
708 memcpy(&(intraData)->chromaModes[cuPos], &(srcIntraData)->chromaModes[mbIndex * 16], 16);
709 memcpy(&(intraData)->partSizes[cuPos], &(srcIntraData)->partSizes[mbIndex * 16], 16);
710 memcpy(&(intraData)->partSizes[cuPos], &(srcIntraData)->partSizes[mbIndex * 16], 16);
711 }
712 }
713 memcpy(&(intraData)->modes, (srcIntraData)->modes, curFrame->m_analysisData.numPartitions * analysis_data->numCUsInFrame);
714 }
715 else
716 {
717 uint32_t numDir = analysis_data->sliceType == X265_TYPE_P ? 1 : 2;
718 if (m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel < 7)
719 return -1;
720 curFrame->m_analysisData.numPartitions = m_param->num4x4Partitions;
721 int num16x16inCUWidth = m_param->maxCUSize >> 4;
722 uint32_t ctuAddr, offset, cuPos;
723 x265_analysis_inter_data * interData = curFrame->m_analysisData.interData;
724 x265_analysis_inter_data * srcInterData = analysis_data->interData;
725 for (int i = 0; i < mbImageHeight; i++)
726 {
727 for (int j = 0; j < mbImageWidth; j++)
728 {
729 int mbIndex = j + i * mbImageWidth;
730 ctuAddr = (j / num16x16inCUWidth + ((i / num16x16inCUWidth) * (mbImageWidth / num16x16inCUWidth)));
731 offset = ((i % num16x16inCUWidth) << 5) + ((j % num16x16inCUWidth) << 4);
732 if ((j % 4 >= 2) && m_param->maxCUSize == 64)
733 offset += (2 * 16);
734 if ((i % 4 >= 2) && m_param->maxCUSize == 64)
735 offset += (2 * 32);
736 cuPos = ctuAddr * curFrame->m_analysisData.numPartitions + offset;
737 memcpy(&(interData)->depth[cuPos], &(srcInterData)->depth[mbIndex * 16], 16);
738 memcpy(&(interData)->modes[cuPos], &(srcInterData)->modes[mbIndex * 16], 16);
739
740 memcpy(&(interData)->partSize[cuPos], &(srcInterData)->partSize[mbIndex * 16], 16);
741
742 int bytes = curFrame->m_analysisData.numPartitions >> ((srcInterData)->depth[mbIndex * 16] * 2);
743 int cuCount = 1;
744 if (bytes < 16)
745 cuCount = 4;
746 for (int cuI = 0; cuI < cuCount; cuI++)
747 {
748 int numPU = nbPartsTable[(srcInterData)->partSize[mbIndex * 16 + cuI * bytes]];
749 for (int pu = 0; pu < numPU; pu++)
750 {
751 int cuOffset = cuI * bytes + pu;
752 (interData)->mergeFlag[cuPos + cuOffset] = (srcInterData)->mergeFlag[(mbIndex * 16) + cuOffset];
753 (interData)->sadCost[cuPos + cuOffset] = (srcInterData)->sadCost[(mbIndex * 16) + cuOffset];
754 (interData)->interDir[cuPos + cuOffset] = (srcInterData)->interDir[(mbIndex * 16) + cuOffset];
755 for (uint32_t k = 0; k < numDir; k++)
756 {
757 (interData)->mvpIdx[k][cuPos + cuOffset] = (srcInterData)->mvpIdx[k][(mbIndex * 16) + cuOffset];
758 (interData)->refIdx[k][cuPos + cuOffset] = (srcInterData)->refIdx[k][(mbIndex * 16) + cuOffset];
759 memcpy(&(interData)->mv[k][cuPos + cuOffset], &(srcInterData)->mv[k][(mbIndex * 16) + cuOffset], sizeof(MV));
760 if (m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel == 7 && numPU == PU_2Nx2N &&
761 ((interData)->depth[cuPos + cuOffset] == (m_param->maxCUSize >> 5)))
762 {
763 int mv_x = (interData)->mv[k][cuPos + cuOffset].x;
764 int mv_y = (interData)->mv[k][cuPos + cuOffset].y;
765 if ((mv_x*mv_x + mv_y*mv_y) <= MVTHRESHOLD)
766 memset(&curFrame->m_analysisData.modeFlag[k][cuPos + cuOffset], 1, bytes);
767 }
768 }
769 }
770 }
771 }
772 }
773 }
774 return 0;
775}
776
777int Encoder::setAnalysisData(x265_analysis_data *analysis_data, int poc, uint32_t cuBytes)
778{
779 uint32_t widthInCU = (m_param->sourceWidth + m_param->maxCUSize - 1) >> m_param->maxLog2CUSize;
780 uint32_t heightInCU = (m_param->sourceHeight + m_param->maxCUSize - 1) >> m_param->maxLog2CUSize;
781
782 Frame* curFrame = m_dpb->m_picList.getPOC(poc);
783 if (curFrame != NULL)
784 {
785 curFrame->m_analysisData = (*analysis_data);
786 curFrame->m_analysisData.numCUsInFrame = widthInCU * heightInCU;
787 curFrame->m_analysisData.numPartitions = m_param->num4x4Partitions;
788 x265_alloc_analysis_data(m_param, &curFrame->m_analysisData);
789 if (m_param->maxCUSize == 16)
790 {
791 if (analysis_data->sliceType == X265_TYPE_IDR || analysis_data->sliceType == X265_TYPE_I)
792 {
793 curFrame->m_analysisData.sliceType = X265_TYPE_I;
794 if (m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel < 2)
795 return -1;
796
797 curFrame->m_analysisData.numPartitions = m_param->num4x4Partitions;
798 size_t count = 0;
799 x265_analysis_intra_data * currIntraData = curFrame->m_analysisData.intraData;
800 x265_analysis_intra_data * intraData = analysis_data->intraData;
801 for (uint32_t d = 0; d < cuBytes; d++)
802 {
803 int bytes = curFrame->m_analysisData.numPartitions >> ((intraData)->depth[d] * 2);
804 memset(&(currIntraData)->depth[count], (intraData)->depth[d], bytes);
805 memset(&(currIntraData)->chromaModes[count], (intraData)->chromaModes[d], bytes);
806 memset(&(currIntraData)->partSizes[count], (intraData)->partSizes[d], bytes);
807 memset(&(currIntraData)->partSizes[count], (intraData)->partSizes[d], bytes);
808 count += bytes;
809 }
810 memcpy(&(currIntraData)->modes, (intraData)->modes, curFrame->m_analysisData.numPartitions * analysis_data->numCUsInFrame);
811 }
812 else
813 {
814 uint32_t numDir = analysis_data->sliceType == X265_TYPE_P ? 1 : 2;
815 if (m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel < 2)
816 return -1;
817
818 curFrame->m_analysisData.numPartitions = m_param->num4x4Partitions;
819 size_t count = 0;
820 x265_analysis_inter_data * currInterData = curFrame->m_analysisData.interData;
821 x265_analysis_inter_data * interData = analysis_data->interData;
822 for (uint32_t d = 0; d < cuBytes; d++)
823 {
824 int bytes = curFrame->m_analysisData.numPartitions >> ((interData)->depth[d] * 2);
825 memset(&(currInterData)->depth[count], (interData)->depth[d], bytes);
826 memset(&(currInterData)->modes[count], (interData)->modes[d], bytes);
827 memcpy(&(currInterData)->sadCost[count], &(analysis_data->interData)->sadCost[d], bytes);
828 if (m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel > 4)
829 {
830 memset(&(currInterData)->partSize[count], (interData)->partSize[d], bytes);
831 int numPU = nbPartsTable[(interData)->partSize[d]];
832 for (int pu = 0; pu < numPU; pu++)
833 {
834 if (pu) d++;
835 (currInterData)->mergeFlag[count + pu] = (interData)->mergeFlag[d];
836 if (m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel >= 7)
837 {
838 (currInterData)->interDir[count + pu] = (interData)->interDir[d];
839 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < numDir; i++)
840 {
841 (currInterData)->mvpIdx[i][count + pu] = (interData)->mvpIdx[i][d];
842 (currInterData)->refIdx[i][count + pu] = (interData)->refIdx[i][d];
843 memcpy(&(currInterData)->mv[i][count + pu], &(interData)->mv[i][d], sizeof(MV));
844 if (m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel == 7 && numPU == PU_2Nx2N && m_param->num4x4Partitions <= 16)
845 {
846 int mv_x = (currInterData)->mv[i][count + pu].x;
847 int mv_y = (currInterData)->mv[i][count + pu].y;
848 if ((mv_x*mv_x + mv_y*mv_y) <= MVTHRESHOLD)
849 memset(&curFrame->m_analysisData.modeFlag[i][count + pu], 1, bytes);
850 }
851 }
852 }
853 }
854 }
855 count += bytes;
856 }
857 }
858 }
859 else
860 setAnalysisDataAfterZScan(analysis_data, curFrame);
861
862 curFrame->m_copyMVType.trigger();
863 return 0;
864 }
865 return -1;
866}
867
868void Encoder::destroy()
869{
870#if ENABLE_HDR10_PLUS
871 if (m_bToneMap)
872 m_hdr10plus_api->hdr10plus_clear_movie(m_cim, m_numCimInfo);
873#endif
874
875 if (m_param->bDynamicRefine)
876 {
877 X265_FREE(m_variance);
878 X265_FREE(m_rdCost);
879 X265_FREE(m_trainingCount);
880 }
881 if (m_exportedPic)
882 {
883 ATOMIC_DEC(&m_exportedPic->m_countRefEncoders);
884 m_exportedPic = NULL;
885 }
886
887 if (m_param->bEnableFrameDuplication)
888 {
889 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < DUP_BUFFER; i++)
890 {
891 X265_FREE(m_dupBuffer[i]->dupPlane);
892 x265_picture_free(m_dupBuffer[i]->dupPic);
893 X265_FREE(m_dupBuffer[i]);
894 }
895
896 if (!(m_param->sourceBitDepth == 8 && m_param->internalBitDepth == 8))
897 {
898 for (int k = 0; k < 3; k++)
899 {
900 if (k == 0)
901 {
902 X265_FREE(m_dupPicOne[k]);
903 X265_FREE(m_dupPicTwo[k]);
904 }
905 else if(k >= 1 && m_param->internalCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
906 {
907 X265_FREE(m_dupPicOne[k]);
908 X265_FREE(m_dupPicTwo[k]);
909 }
910 }
911 }
912 }
913
914 if (m_param->bHistBasedSceneCut)
915 {
916 if (m_edgePic != NULL)
917 {
918 X265_FREE_ZERO(m_edgePic);
919 }
920
921 if (m_param->sourceBitDepth != m_param->internalBitDepth)
922 {
923 X265_FREE_ZERO(m_inputPic[0]);
924 if (m_param->internalCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
925 {
926 for (int i = 1; i < 3; i++)
927 {
928 X265_FREE_ZERO(m_inputPic[i]);
929 }
930 }
931 }
932 }
933
934 for (int i = 0; i < m_param->frameNumThreads; i++)
935 {
936 if (m_frameEncoder[i])
937 {
938 m_frameEncoder[i]->destroy();
939 delete m_frameEncoder[i];
940 }
941 }
942
943 // thread pools can be cleaned up now that all the JobProviders are
944 // known to be shutdown
945 delete [] m_threadPool;
946
947 if (m_lookahead)
948 {
949 m_lookahead->destroy();
950 delete m_lookahead;
951 }
952
953 delete m_dpb;
954 if (!m_param->bResetZoneConfig && m_param->rc.zonefileCount)
955 {
956 delete[] zoneReadCount;
957 delete[] zoneWriteCount;
958 }
959 if (m_rateControl)
960 {
961 m_rateControl->destroy();
962 delete m_rateControl;
963 }
964
965 X265_FREE(m_offsetEmergency);
966
967 if (m_latestParam != NULL && m_latestParam != m_param)
968 {
969 if (m_latestParam->scalingLists != m_param->scalingLists)
970 free((char*)m_latestParam->scalingLists);
971
972 PARAM_NS::x265_param_free(m_latestParam);
973 }
974 if (m_analysisFileIn)
975 fclose(m_analysisFileIn);
976
977 if (m_analysisFileOut)
978 {
979 int bError = 1;
980 fclose(m_analysisFileOut);
981 const char* name = m_param->analysisSave ? m_param->analysisSave : m_param->analysisReuseFileName;
982 if (!name)
983 name = defaultAnalysisFileName;
984 char* temp = strcatFilename(name, ".temp");
985 if (temp)
986 {
987 x265_unlink(name);
988 bError = x265_rename(temp, name);
989 }
990 if (bError)
991 {
992 x265_log_file(m_param, X265_LOG_ERROR, "failed to rename analysis stats file to \"%s\"\n", name);
993 }
994 X265_FREE(temp);
995 }
996 if (m_naluFile)
997 fclose(m_naluFile);
998
999#ifdef SVT_HEVC
1000 X265_FREE(m_svtAppData);
1001#endif
1002 if (m_param)
1003 {
1004 if (m_param->csvfpt)
1005 fclose(m_param->csvfpt);
1006 /* release string arguments that were strdup'd */
1007 free((char*)m_param->rc.lambdaFileName);
1008 free((char*)m_param->rc.statFileName);
1009 free((char*)m_param->analysisReuseFileName);
1010 free((char*)m_param->scalingLists);
1011 free((char*)m_param->csvfn);
1012 free((char*)m_param->numaPools);
1013 free((char*)m_param->masteringDisplayColorVolume);
1014 free((char*)m_param->toneMapFile);
1015 free((char*)m_param->analysisSave);
1016 free((char*)m_param->analysisLoad);
1017 free((char*)m_param->videoSignalTypePreset);
1018 PARAM_NS::x265_param_free(m_param);
1019 }
1020}
1021
1022void Encoder::updateVbvPlan(RateControl* rc)
1023{
1024 for (int i = 0; i < m_param->frameNumThreads; i++)
1025 {
1026 FrameEncoder *encoder = m_frameEncoder[i];
1027 if (encoder->m_rce.isActive && encoder->m_rce.poc != rc->m_curSlice->m_poc)
1028 {
1029 int64_t bits = m_param->rc.bEnableConstVbv ? (int64_t)encoder->m_rce.frameSizePlanned : (int64_t)X265_MAX(encoder->m_rce.frameSizeEstimated, encoder->m_rce.frameSizePlanned);
1030 rc->m_bufferFill -= bits;
1031 rc->m_bufferFill = X265_MAX(rc->m_bufferFill, 0);
1032 rc->m_bufferFill += encoder->m_rce.bufferRate;
1033 rc->m_bufferFill = X265_MIN(rc->m_bufferFill, rc->m_bufferSize);
1034 if (rc->m_2pass)
1035 rc->m_predictedBits += bits;
1036 }
1037 }
1038}
1039
1040void Encoder::calcRefreshInterval(Frame* frameEnc)
1041{
1042 Slice* slice = frameEnc->m_encData->m_slice;
1043 uint32_t numBlocksInRow = slice->m_sps->numCuInWidth;
1044 FrameData::PeriodicIR* pir = &frameEnc->m_encData->m_pir;
1045 if (slice->m_sliceType == I_SLICE)
1046 {
1047 pir->framesSinceLastPir = 0;
1048 m_bQueuedIntraRefresh = 0;
1049 /* PIR is currently only supported with ref == 1, so any intra frame effectively refreshes
1050 * the whole frame and counts as an intra refresh. */
1051 pir->pirEndCol = numBlocksInRow;
1052 }
1053 else if (slice->m_sliceType == P_SLICE)
1054 {
1055 Frame* ref = frameEnc->m_encData->m_slice->m_refFrameList[0][0];
1056 int pocdiff = frameEnc->m_poc - ref->m_poc;
1057 int numPFramesInGOP = m_param->keyframeMax / pocdiff;
1058 int increment = (numBlocksInRow + numPFramesInGOP - 1) / numPFramesInGOP;
1059 pir->pirEndCol = ref->m_encData->m_pir.pirEndCol;
1060 pir->framesSinceLastPir = ref->m_encData->m_pir.framesSinceLastPir + pocdiff;
1061 if (pir->framesSinceLastPir >= m_param->keyframeMax ||
1062 (m_bQueuedIntraRefresh && pir->pirEndCol >= numBlocksInRow))
1063 {
1064 pir->pirEndCol = 0;
1065 pir->framesSinceLastPir = 0;
1066 m_bQueuedIntraRefresh = 0;
1067 frameEnc->m_lowres.bKeyframe = 1;
1068 }
1069 pir->pirStartCol = pir->pirEndCol;
1070 pir->pirEndCol += increment;
1071 /* If our intra refresh has reached the right side of the frame, we're done. */
1072 if (pir->pirEndCol >= numBlocksInRow)
1073 {
1074 pir->pirEndCol = numBlocksInRow;
1075 }
1076 }
1077}
1078
1079void Encoder::copyUserSEIMessages(Frame *frame, const x265_picture* pic_in)
1080{
1081 x265_sei_payload toneMap;
1082 toneMap.payload = NULL;
1083 int toneMapPayload = 0;
1084
1085#if ENABLE_HDR10_PLUS
1086 if (m_bToneMap)
1087 {
1088 int currentPOC = m_pocLast;
1089 if (currentPOC < m_numCimInfo)
1090 {
1091 int32_t i = 0;
1092 toneMap.payloadSize = 0;
1093 while (m_cim[currentPOC][i] == 0xFF)
1094 toneMap.payloadSize += m_cim[currentPOC][i++];
1095 toneMap.payloadSize += m_cim[currentPOC][i];
1096
1097 toneMap.payload = (uint8_t*)x265_malloc(sizeof(uint8_t) * toneMap.payloadSize);
1098 toneMap.payloadType = USER_DATA_REGISTERED_ITU_T_T35;
1099 memcpy(toneMap.payload, &m_cim[currentPOC][i + 1], toneMap.payloadSize);
1100 toneMapPayload = 1;
1101 }
1102 }
1103#endif
1104 /* seiMsg will contain SEI messages specified in a fixed file format in POC order.
1105 * Format of the file : <POC><space><PREFIX><space><NAL UNIT TYPE>/<SEI TYPE><space><SEI Payload> */
1106 x265_sei_payload seiMsg;
1107 seiMsg.payload = NULL;
1108 int userPayload = 0;
1109 if (m_enableNal)
1110 {
1111 readUserSeiFile(seiMsg, m_pocLast);
1112 if (seiMsg.payload)
1113 userPayload = 1;;
1114 }
1115
1116 int numPayloads = pic_in->userSEI.numPayloads + toneMapPayload + userPayload;
1117 frame->m_userSEI.numPayloads = numPayloads;
1118
1119 if (frame->m_userSEI.numPayloads)
1120 {
1121 if (!frame->m_userSEI.payloads)
1122 {
1123 frame->m_userSEI.payloads = new x265_sei_payload[numPayloads];
1124 for (int i = 0; i < numPayloads; i++)
1125 frame->m_userSEI.payloads[i].payload = NULL;
1126 }
1127 for (int i = 0; i < numPayloads; i++)
1128 {
1129 x265_sei_payload input;
1130 if ((i == (numPayloads - 1)) && toneMapPayload)
1131 input = toneMap;
1132 else if (m_enableNal)
1133 input = seiMsg;
1134 else
1135 input = pic_in->userSEI.payloads[i];
1136
1137 if (!frame->m_userSEI.payloads[i].payload)
1138 frame->m_userSEI.payloads[i].payload = new uint8_t[input.payloadSize];
1139 memcpy(frame->m_userSEI.payloads[i].payload, input.payload, input.payloadSize);
1140 frame->m_userSEI.payloads[i].payloadSize = input.payloadSize;
1141 frame->m_userSEI.payloads[i].payloadType = input.payloadType;
1142 }
1143 if (toneMap.payload)
1144 x265_free(toneMap.payload);
1145 if (seiMsg.payload)
1146 x265_free(seiMsg.payload);
1147 }
1148}
1149
1150//Find Sum of Squared Difference (SSD) between two pictures
1151uint64_t Encoder::computeSSD(pixel *fenc, pixel *rec, intptr_t stride, uint32_t width, uint32_t height, x265_param *param)
1152{
1153 uint64_t ssd = 0;
1154
1155 if (!param->bEnableFrameDuplication || (width & 3))
1156 {
1157 if ((width | height) & 3)
1158 {
1159 /* Slow Path */
1160 for (uint32_t y = 0; y < height; y++)
1161 {
1162 for (uint32_t x = 0; x < width; x++)
1163 {
1164 int diff = (int)(fenc[x] - rec[x]);
1165 ssd += diff * diff;
1166 }
1167
1168 fenc += stride;
1169 rec += stride;
1170 }
1171
1172 return ssd;
1173 }
1174 }
1175
1176 uint32_t y = 0;
1177
1178 /* Consume rows in ever narrower chunks of height */
1179 for (int size = BLOCK_64x64; size >= BLOCK_4x4 && y < height; size--)
1180 {
1181 uint32_t rowHeight = 1 << (size + 2);
1182
1183 for (; y + rowHeight <= height; y += rowHeight)
1184 {
1185 uint32_t y1, x = 0;
1186
1187 /* Consume each row using the largest square blocks possible */
1188 if (size == BLOCK_64x64 && !(stride & 31))
1189 for (; x + 64 <= width; x += 64)
1190 ssd += primitives.cu[BLOCK_64x64].sse_pp(fenc + x, stride, rec + x, stride);
1191
1192 if (size >= BLOCK_32x32 && !(stride & 15))
1193 for (; x + 32 <= width; x += 32)
1194 for (y1 = 0; y1 + 32 <= rowHeight; y1 += 32)
1195 ssd += primitives.cu[BLOCK_32x32].sse_pp(fenc + y1 * stride + x, stride, rec + y1 * stride + x, stride);
1196
1197 if (size >= BLOCK_16x16)
1198 for (; x + 16 <= width; x += 16)
1199 for (y1 = 0; y1 + 16 <= rowHeight; y1 += 16)
1200 ssd += primitives.cu[BLOCK_16x16].sse_pp(fenc + y1 * stride + x, stride, rec + y1 * stride + x, stride);
1201
1202 if (size >= BLOCK_8x8)
1203 for (; x + 8 <= width; x += 8)
1204 for (y1 = 0; y1 + 8 <= rowHeight; y1 += 8)
1205 ssd += primitives.cu[BLOCK_8x8].sse_pp(fenc + y1 * stride + x, stride, rec + y1 * stride + x, stride);
1206
1207 for (; x + 4 <= width; x += 4)
1208 for (y1 = 0; y1 + 4 <= rowHeight; y1 += 4)
1209 ssd += primitives.cu[BLOCK_4x4].sse_pp(fenc + y1 * stride + x, stride, rec + y1 * stride + x, stride);
1210
1211 fenc += stride * rowHeight;
1212 rec += stride * rowHeight;
1213 }
1214 }
1215
1216 /* Handle last few rows of frames for videos
1217 with height not divisble by 4 */
1218 uint32_t h = height % y;
1219 if (param->bEnableFrameDuplication && h)
1220 {
1221 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < h; i++)
1222 {
1223 for (uint32_t j = 0; j < width; j++)
1224 {
1225 int diff = (int)(fenc[j] - rec[j]);
1226 ssd += diff * diff;
1227 }
1228
1229 fenc += stride;
1230 rec += stride;
1231 }
1232 }
1233
1234 return ssd;
1235}
1236
1237//Compute the PSNR weightage between two pictures
1238double Encoder::ComputePSNR(x265_picture *firstPic, x265_picture *secPic, x265_param *param)
1239{
1240 uint64_t ssdY = 0, ssdU = 0, ssdV = 0;
1241 intptr_t strideL, strideC;
1242 uint32_t widthL, heightL, widthC, heightC;
1243 double psnrY = 0, psnrU = 0, psnrV = 0, psnrWeight = 0;
1244 int width = firstPic->width;
1245 int height = firstPic->height;
1246 int hshift = CHROMA_H_SHIFT(firstPic->colorSpace);
1247 int vshift = CHROMA_V_SHIFT(firstPic->colorSpace);
1248 pixel *yFirstPic = NULL, *ySecPic = NULL;
1249 pixel *uFirstPic = NULL, *uSecPic = NULL;
1250 pixel *vFirstPic = NULL, *vSecPic = NULL;
1251
1252 strideL = widthL = width;
1253 heightL = height;
1254
1255 strideC = widthC = widthL >> hshift;
1256 heightC = heightL >> vshift;
1257
1258 int size = width * height;
1259 int maxvalY = 255 << (X265_DEPTH - 8);
1260 int maxvalC = 255 << (X265_DEPTH - 8);
1261 double refValueY = (double)maxvalY * maxvalY * size;
1262 double refValueC = (double)maxvalC * maxvalC * size / 4.0;
1263
1264 if (firstPic->bitDepth == 8 && X265_DEPTH == 8)
1265 {
1266 yFirstPic = (pixel*)firstPic->planes[0];
1267 ySecPic = (pixel*)secPic->planes[0];
1268 if (param->internalCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
1269 {
1270 uFirstPic = (pixel*)firstPic->planes[1];
1271 uSecPic = (pixel*)secPic->planes[1];
1272 vFirstPic = (pixel*)firstPic->planes[2];
1273 vSecPic = (pixel*)secPic->planes[2];
1274 }
1275 }
1276 else if (firstPic->bitDepth == 8 && X265_DEPTH > 8)
1277 {
1278 int shift = (X265_DEPTH - 8);
1279 uint8_t *yChar1, *yChar2, *uChar1, *uChar2, *vChar1, *vChar2;
1280
1281 yChar1 = (uint8_t*)firstPic->planes[0];
1282 yChar2 = (uint8_t*)secPic->planes[0];
1283
1284 primitives.planecopy_cp(yChar1, firstPic->stride[0] / sizeof(*yChar1), m_dupPicOne[0], firstPic->stride[0] / sizeof(*yChar1), width, height, shift);
1285 primitives.planecopy_cp(yChar2, secPic->stride[0] / sizeof(*yChar2), m_dupPicTwo[0], secPic->stride[0] / sizeof(*yChar2), width, height, shift);
1286
1287 if (param->internalCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
1288 {
1289 uChar1 = (uint8_t*)firstPic->planes[1];
1290 uChar2 = (uint8_t*)secPic->planes[1];
1291 vChar1 = (uint8_t*)firstPic->planes[2];
1292 vChar2 = (uint8_t*)secPic->planes[2];
1293
1294 primitives.planecopy_cp(uChar1, firstPic->stride[1] / sizeof(*uChar1), m_dupPicOne[1], firstPic->stride[1] / sizeof(*uChar1), widthC, heightC, shift);
1295 primitives.planecopy_cp(uChar2, secPic->stride[1] / sizeof(*uChar2), m_dupPicTwo[1], secPic->stride[1] / sizeof(*uChar2), widthC, heightC, shift);
1296
1297 primitives.planecopy_cp(vChar1, firstPic->stride[2] / sizeof(*vChar1), m_dupPicOne[2], firstPic->stride[2] / sizeof(*vChar1), widthC, heightC, shift);
1298 primitives.planecopy_cp(vChar2, secPic->stride[2] / sizeof(*vChar2), m_dupPicTwo[2], secPic->stride[2] / sizeof(*vChar2), widthC, heightC, shift);
1299 }
1300 }
1301 else
1302 {
1303 uint16_t *yShort1, *yShort2, *uShort1, *uShort2, *vShort1, *vShort2;
1304 /* defensive programming, mask off bits that are supposed to be zero */
1305 uint16_t mask = (1 << X265_DEPTH) - 1;
1306 int shift = abs(firstPic->bitDepth - X265_DEPTH);
1307
1308 yShort1 = (uint16_t*)firstPic->planes[0];
1309 yShort2 = (uint16_t*)secPic->planes[0];
1310
1311 if (firstPic->bitDepth > X265_DEPTH)
1312 {
1313 /* shift right and mask pixels to final size */
1314 primitives.planecopy_sp(yShort1, firstPic->stride[0] / sizeof(*yShort1), m_dupPicOne[0], firstPic->stride[0] / sizeof(*yShort1), width, height, shift, mask);
1315 primitives.planecopy_sp(yShort2, secPic->stride[0] / sizeof(*yShort2), m_dupPicTwo[0], secPic->stride[0] / sizeof(*yShort2), width, height, shift, mask);
1316 }
1317 else /* Case for (pic.bitDepth <= X265_DEPTH) */
1318 {
1319 /* shift left and mask pixels to final size */
1320 primitives.planecopy_sp_shl(yShort1, firstPic->stride[0] / sizeof(*yShort1), m_dupPicOne[0], firstPic->stride[0] / sizeof(*yShort1), width, height, shift, mask);
1321 primitives.planecopy_sp_shl(yShort2, secPic->stride[0] / sizeof(*yShort2), m_dupPicTwo[0], secPic->stride[0] / sizeof(*yShort2), width, height, shift, mask);
1322 }
1323
1324 if (param->internalCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
1325 {
1326 uShort1 = (uint16_t*)firstPic->planes[1];
1327 uShort2 = (uint16_t*)secPic->planes[1];
1328 vShort1 = (uint16_t*)firstPic->planes[2];
1329 vShort2 = (uint16_t*)secPic->planes[2];
1330
1331 if (firstPic->bitDepth > X265_DEPTH)
1332 {
1333 primitives.planecopy_sp(uShort1, firstPic->stride[1] / sizeof(*uShort1), m_dupPicOne[1], firstPic->stride[1] / sizeof(*uShort1), widthC, heightC, shift, mask);
1334 primitives.planecopy_sp(uShort2, secPic->stride[1] / sizeof(*uShort2), m_dupPicTwo[1], secPic->stride[1] / sizeof(*uShort2), widthC, heightC, shift, mask);
1335
1336 primitives.planecopy_sp(vShort1, firstPic->stride[2] / sizeof(*vShort1), m_dupPicOne[2], firstPic->stride[2] / sizeof(*vShort1), widthC, heightC, shift, mask);
1337 primitives.planecopy_sp(vShort2, secPic->stride[2] / sizeof(*vShort2), m_dupPicTwo[2], secPic->stride[2] / sizeof(*vShort2), widthC, heightC, shift, mask);
1338 }
1339 else /* Case for (pic.bitDepth <= X265_DEPTH) */
1340 {
1341 primitives.planecopy_sp_shl(uShort1, firstPic->stride[1] / sizeof(*uShort1), m_dupPicOne[1], firstPic->stride[1] / sizeof(*uShort1), widthC, heightC, shift, mask);
1342 primitives.planecopy_sp_shl(uShort2, secPic->stride[1] / sizeof(*uShort2), m_dupPicTwo[1], secPic->stride[1] / sizeof(*uShort2), widthC, heightC, shift, mask);
1343
1344 primitives.planecopy_sp_shl(vShort1, firstPic->stride[2] / sizeof(*vShort1), m_dupPicOne[2], firstPic->stride[2] / sizeof(*vShort1), widthC, heightC, shift, mask);
1345 primitives.planecopy_sp_shl(vShort2, secPic->stride[2] / sizeof(*vShort2), m_dupPicTwo[2], secPic->stride[2] / sizeof(*vShort2), widthC, heightC, shift, mask);
1346 }
1347 }
1348 }
1349
1350 if (!(firstPic->bitDepth == 8 && X265_DEPTH == 8))
1351 {
1352 yFirstPic = m_dupPicOne[0]; ySecPic = m_dupPicTwo[0];
1353 uFirstPic = m_dupPicOne[1]; uSecPic = m_dupPicTwo[1];
1354 vFirstPic = m_dupPicOne[2]; vSecPic = m_dupPicTwo[2];
1355 }
1356
1357 //Compute SSD
1358 ssdY = computeSSD(yFirstPic, ySecPic, strideL, widthL, heightL, param);
1359 psnrY = (ssdY ? 10.0 * log10(refValueY / (double)ssdY) : 99.99);
1360
1361 if (param->internalCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
1362 {
1363 ssdU = computeSSD(uFirstPic, uSecPic, strideC, widthC, heightC, param);
1364 ssdV = computeSSD(vFirstPic, vSecPic, strideC, widthC, heightC, param);
1365 psnrU = (ssdU ? 10.0 * log10(refValueC / (double)ssdU) : 99.99);
1366 psnrV = (ssdV ? 10.0 * log10(refValueC / (double)ssdV) : 99.99);
1367 }
1368
1369 //Compute PSNR(picN,pic(N+1))
1370 return psnrWeight = (psnrY * 6 + psnrU + psnrV) / 8;
1371}
1372
1373void Encoder::copyPicture(x265_picture *dest, const x265_picture *src)
1374{
1375 dest->poc = src->poc;
1376 dest->pts = src->pts;
1377 dest->userSEI = src->userSEI;
1378 dest->bitDepth = src->bitDepth;
1379 dest->framesize = src->framesize;
1380 dest->height = src->height;
1381 dest->width = src->width;
1382 dest->colorSpace = src->colorSpace;
1383 dest->userSEI = src->userSEI;
1384 dest->rpu.payload = src->rpu.payload;
1385 dest->picStruct = src->picStruct;
1386 dest->stride[0] = src->stride[0];
1387 dest->stride[1] = src->stride[1];
1388 dest->stride[2] = src->stride[2];
1389 memcpy(dest->planes[0], src->planes[0], src->framesize * sizeof(char));
1390 dest->planes[1] = (char*)dest->planes[0] + src->stride[0] * src->height;
1391 dest->planes[2] = (char*)dest->planes[1] + src->stride[1] * (src->height >> x265_cli_csps[src->colorSpace].height[1]);
1392}
1393
1394bool Encoder::computeHistograms(x265_picture *pic)
1395{
1396 pixel *src = NULL, *planeV = NULL, *planeU = NULL;
1397 uint32_t widthC, heightC;
1398 int hshift, vshift;
1399
1400 hshift = CHROMA_H_SHIFT(pic->colorSpace);
1401 vshift = CHROMA_V_SHIFT(pic->colorSpace);
1402 widthC = pic->width >> hshift;
1403 heightC = pic->height >> vshift;
1404
1405 if (pic->bitDepth == X265_DEPTH)
1406 {
1407 src = (pixel*)pic->planes[0];
1408 if (m_param->internalCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
1409 {
1410 planeU = (pixel*)pic->planes[1];
1411 planeV = (pixel*)pic->planes[2];
1412 }
1413 }
1414 else if (pic->bitDepth == 8 && X265_DEPTH > 8)
1415 {
1416 int shift = (X265_DEPTH - 8);
1417 uint8_t *yChar, *uChar, *vChar;
1418
1419 yChar = (uint8_t*)pic->planes[0];
1420 primitives.planecopy_cp(yChar, pic->stride[0] / sizeof(*yChar), m_inputPic[0], pic->stride[0] / sizeof(*yChar), pic->width, pic->height, shift);
1421 src = m_inputPic[0];
1422 if (m_param->internalCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
1423 {
1424 uChar = (uint8_t*)pic->planes[1];
1425 vChar = (uint8_t*)pic->planes[2];
1426 primitives.planecopy_cp(uChar, pic->stride[1] / sizeof(*uChar), m_inputPic[1], pic->stride[1] / sizeof(*uChar), widthC, heightC, shift);
1427 primitives.planecopy_cp(vChar, pic->stride[2] / sizeof(*vChar), m_inputPic[2], pic->stride[2] / sizeof(*vChar), widthC, heightC, shift);
1428 planeU = m_inputPic[1];
1429 planeV = m_inputPic[2];
1430 }
1431 }
1432 else
1433 {
1434 uint16_t *yShort, *uShort, *vShort;
1435 /* mask off bits that are supposed to be zero */
1436 uint16_t mask = (1 << X265_DEPTH) - 1;
1437 int shift = abs(pic->bitDepth - X265_DEPTH);
1438
1439 yShort = (uint16_t*)pic->planes[0];
1440 uShort = (uint16_t*)pic->planes[1];
1441 vShort = (uint16_t*)pic->planes[2];
1442
1443 if (pic->bitDepth > X265_DEPTH)
1444 {
1445 /* shift right and mask pixels to final size */
1446 primitives.planecopy_sp(yShort, pic->stride[0] / sizeof(*yShort), m_inputPic[0], pic->stride[0] / sizeof(*yShort), pic->width, pic->height, shift, mask);
1447 if (m_param->internalCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
1448 {
1449 primitives.planecopy_sp(uShort, pic->stride[1] / sizeof(*uShort), m_inputPic[1], pic->stride[1] / sizeof(*uShort), widthC, heightC, shift, mask);
1450 primitives.planecopy_sp(vShort, pic->stride[2] / sizeof(*vShort), m_inputPic[2], pic->stride[2] / sizeof(*vShort), widthC, heightC, shift, mask);
1451 }
1452 }
1453 else /* Case for (pic.bitDepth < X265_DEPTH) */
1454 {
1455 /* shift left and mask pixels to final size */
1456 primitives.planecopy_sp_shl(yShort, pic->stride[0] / sizeof(*yShort), m_inputPic[0], pic->stride[0] / sizeof(*yShort), pic->width, pic->height, shift, mask);
1457 if (m_param->internalCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
1458 {
1459 primitives.planecopy_sp_shl(uShort, pic->stride[1] / sizeof(*uShort), m_inputPic[1], pic->stride[1] / sizeof(*uShort), widthC, heightC, shift, mask);
1460 primitives.planecopy_sp_shl(vShort, pic->stride[2] / sizeof(*vShort), m_inputPic[2], pic->stride[2] / sizeof(*vShort), widthC, heightC, shift, mask);
1461 }
1462 }
1463
1464 src = m_inputPic[0];
1465 planeU = m_inputPic[1];
1466 planeV = m_inputPic[2];
1467 }
1468
1469 size_t bufSize = sizeof(pixel) * m_planeSizes[0];
1470 memset(m_edgePic, 0, bufSize);
1471
1472 if (!computeEdge(m_edgePic, src, NULL, pic->width, pic->height, pic->width, false, 1))
1473 {
1474 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Failed to compute edge!");
1475 return false;
1476 }
1477
1478 pixel pixelVal;
1479 int32_t *edgeHist = m_curEdgeHist;
1480 memset(edgeHist, 0, EDGE_BINS * sizeof(int32_t));
1481 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < m_planeSizes[0]; i++)
1482 {
1483 if (m_edgePic[i])
1484 edgeHist[1]++;
1485 else
1486 edgeHist[0]++;
1487 }
1488
1489 /* Y Histogram Calculation */
1490 int32_t *yHist = m_curYUVHist[0];
1491 memset(yHist, 0, HISTOGRAM_BINS * sizeof(int32_t));
1492 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < m_planeSizes[0]; i++)
1493 {
1494 pixelVal = src[i];
1495 yHist[pixelVal]++;
1496 }
1497
1498 if (pic->colorSpace != X265_CSP_I400)
1499 {
1500 /* U Histogram Calculation */
1501 int32_t *uHist = m_curYUVHist[1];
1502 memset(uHist, 0, sizeof(m_curYUVHist[1]));
1503 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < m_planeSizes[1]; i++)
1504 {
1505 pixelVal = planeU[i];
1506 uHist[pixelVal]++;
1507 }
1508
1509 /* V Histogram Calculation */
1510 pixelVal = 0;
1511 int32_t *vHist = m_curYUVHist[2];
1512 memset(vHist, 0, sizeof(m_curYUVHist[2]));
1513 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < m_planeSizes[2]; i++)
1514 {
1515 pixelVal = planeV[i];
1516 vHist[pixelVal]++;
1517 }
1518 }
1519 return true;
1520}
1521
1522void Encoder::computeHistogramSAD(double *normalizedMaxUVSad, double *normalizedEdgeSad, int curPoc)
1523{
1524
1525 if (curPoc == 0)
1526 { /* first frame is scenecut by default no sad computation for the same. */
1527 *normalizedMaxUVSad = 0.0;
1528 *normalizedEdgeSad = 0.0;
1529 }
1530 else
1531 {
1532 /* compute sum of absolute differences of histogram bins of chroma and luma edge response between the current and prev pictures. */
1533 int32_t edgeHistSad = 0;
1534 int32_t uHistSad = 0;
1535 int32_t vHistSad = 0;
1536 double normalizedUSad = 0.0;
1537 double normalizedVSad = 0.0;
1538
1539 for (int j = 0; j < HISTOGRAM_BINS; j++)
1540 {
1541 if (j < 2)
1542 {
1543 edgeHistSad += abs(m_curEdgeHist[j] - m_prevEdgeHist[j]);
1544 }
1545 uHistSad += abs(m_curYUVHist[1][j] - m_prevYUVHist[1][j]);
1546 vHistSad += abs(m_curYUVHist[2][j] - m_prevYUVHist[2][j]);
1547 }
1548 *normalizedEdgeSad = normalizeRange(edgeHistSad, 0, 2 * m_planeSizes[0], 0.0, 1.0);
1549 normalizedUSad = normalizeRange(uHistSad, 0, 2 * m_planeSizes[1], 0.0, 1.0);
1550 normalizedVSad = normalizeRange(vHistSad, 0, 2 * m_planeSizes[2], 0.0, 1.0);
1551 *normalizedMaxUVSad = x265_max(normalizedUSad, normalizedVSad);
1552 }
1553
1554 /* store histograms of previous frame for reference */
1555 memcpy(m_prevEdgeHist, m_curEdgeHist, sizeof(m_curEdgeHist));
1556 memcpy(m_prevYUVHist, m_curYUVHist, sizeof(m_curYUVHist));
1557}
1558
1559double Encoder::normalizeRange(int32_t value, int32_t minValue, int32_t maxValue, double rangeStart, double rangeEnd)
1560{
1561 return (double)(value - minValue) * (rangeEnd - rangeStart) / (maxValue - minValue) + rangeStart;
1562}
1563
1564void Encoder::findSceneCuts(x265_picture *pic, bool& bDup, double maxUVSad, double edgeSad, bool& isMaxThres, bool& isHardSC)
1565{
1566 double minEdgeT = m_edgeHistThreshold * MIN_EDGE_FACTOR;
1567 double minChromaT = minEdgeT * SCENECUT_CHROMA_FACTOR;
1568 double maxEdgeT = m_edgeHistThreshold * MAX_EDGE_FACTOR;
1569 double maxChromaT = maxEdgeT * SCENECUT_CHROMA_FACTOR;
1570 pic->frameData.bScenecut = false;
1571
1572 if (pic->poc == 0)
1573 {
1574 /* for first frame */
1575 pic->frameData.bScenecut = false;
1576 bDup = false;
1577 }
1578 else
1579 {
1580 if (edgeSad == 0.0 && maxUVSad == 0.0)
1581 {
1582 bDup = true;
1583 }
1584 else if (edgeSad < minEdgeT && maxUVSad < minChromaT)
1585 {
1586 pic->frameData.bScenecut = false;
1587 }
1588 else if (edgeSad > maxEdgeT && maxUVSad > maxChromaT)
1589 {
1590 pic->frameData.bScenecut = true;
1591 isMaxThres = true;
1592 isHardSC = true;
1593 }
1594 else if (edgeSad > m_scaledEdgeThreshold || maxUVSad >= m_scaledChromaThreshold
1595 || (edgeSad > m_edgeHistThreshold && maxUVSad >= m_chromaHistThreshold))
1596 {
1597 pic->frameData.bScenecut = true;
1598 bDup = false;
1599 if (edgeSad > m_scaledEdgeThreshold || maxUVSad >= m_scaledChromaThreshold)
1600 isHardSC = true;
1601 }
1602 }
1603}
1604
1605/**
1606 * Feed one new input frame into the encoder, get one frame out. If pic_in is
1607 * NULL, a flush condition is implied and pic_in must be NULL for all subsequent
1608 * calls for this encoder instance.
1609 *
1610 * pic_in input original YUV picture or NULL
1611 * pic_out pointer to reconstructed picture struct
1612 *
1613 * returns 0 if no frames are currently available for output
1614 * 1 if frame was output, m_nalList contains access unit
1615 * negative on malloc error or abort */
1616int Encoder::encode(const x265_picture* pic_in, x265_picture* pic_out)
1617{
1618#if CHECKED_BUILD || _DEBUG
1619 if (g_checkFailures)
1620 {
1621 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_ERROR, "encoder aborting because of internal error\n");
1622 return -1;
1623 }
1624#endif
1625 if (m_aborted)
1626 return -1;
1627
1628 const x265_picture* inputPic = NULL;
1629 static int written = 0, read = 0;
1630 bool dontRead = false;
1631 bool bdropFrame = false;
1632 bool dropflag = false;
1633 bool isMaxThres = false;
1634 bool isHardSC = false;
1635
1636 if (m_exportedPic)
1637 {
1638 if (!m_param->bUseAnalysisFile && m_param->analysisSave)
1639 x265_free_analysis_data(m_param, &m_exportedPic->m_analysisData);
1640 ATOMIC_DEC(&m_exportedPic->m_countRefEncoders);
1641 m_exportedPic = NULL;
1642 m_dpb->recycleUnreferenced();
1643 }
1644 if ((pic_in && (!m_param->chunkEnd || (m_encodedFrameNum < m_param->chunkEnd))) || (m_param->bEnableFrameDuplication && !pic_in && (read < written)))
1645 {
1646 if (m_param->bHistBasedSceneCut && pic_in)
1647 {
1648 x265_picture *pic = (x265_picture *) pic_in;
1649
1650 if (pic->poc == 0)
1651 {
1652 /* for entire encode compute the chroma plane sizes only once */
1653 for (int i = 1; i < x265_cli_csps[m_param->internalCsp].planes; i++)
1654 m_planeSizes[i] = (pic->width >> x265_cli_csps[m_param->internalCsp].width[i]) * (pic->height >> x265_cli_csps[m_param->internalCsp].height[i]);
1655 }
1656
1657 if (computeHistograms(pic))
1658 {
1659 double maxUVSad = 0.0, edgeSad = 0.0;
1660 computeHistogramSAD(&maxUVSad, &edgeSad, pic_in->poc);
1661 findSceneCuts(pic, bdropFrame, maxUVSad, edgeSad, isMaxThres, isHardSC);
1662 }
1663 }
1664
1665 if ((m_param->bEnableFrameDuplication && !pic_in && (read < written)))
1666 dontRead = true;
1667 else
1668 {
1669 if (m_latestParam->forceFlush == 1)
1670 {
1671 m_lookahead->setLookaheadQueue();
1672 m_latestParam->forceFlush = 0;
1673 }
1674 if (m_latestParam->forceFlush == 2)
1675 {
1676 m_lookahead->m_filled = false;
1677 m_latestParam->forceFlush = 0;
1678 }
1679
1680 if (pic_in->bitDepth < 8 || pic_in->bitDepth > 16)
1681 {
1682 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Input bit depth (%d) must be between 8 and 16\n",
1683 pic_in->bitDepth);
1684 return -1;
1685 }
1686 }
1687
1688 if (m_param->bEnableFrameDuplication)
1689 {
1690 double psnrWeight = 0;
1691
1692 if (!dontRead)
1693 {
1694 if (!m_dupBuffer[0]->bOccupied)
1695 {
1696 copyPicture(m_dupBuffer[0]->dupPic, pic_in);
1697 m_dupBuffer[0]->bOccupied = true;
1698 written++;
1699 return 0;
1700 }
1701 else if (!m_dupBuffer[1]->bOccupied)
1702 {
1703 copyPicture(m_dupBuffer[1]->dupPic, pic_in);
1704 m_dupBuffer[1]->bOccupied = true;
1705 written++;
1706 }
1707
1708 if (m_param->bEnableFrameDuplication && m_param->bHistBasedSceneCut)
1709 {
1710 if (!bdropFrame && m_dupBuffer[1]->dupPic->frameData.bScenecut == false)
1711 {
1712 psnrWeight = ComputePSNR(m_dupBuffer[0]->dupPic, m_dupBuffer[1]->dupPic, m_param);
1713 if (psnrWeight >= m_param->dupThreshold)
1714 dropflag = true;
1715 }
1716 else
1717 {
1718 dropflag = true;
1719 }
1720 }
1721 else if (m_param->bEnableFrameDuplication)
1722 {
1723 psnrWeight = ComputePSNR(m_dupBuffer[0]->dupPic, m_dupBuffer[1]->dupPic, m_param);
1724 if (psnrWeight >= m_param->dupThreshold)
1725 dropflag = true;
1726 }
1727
1728 if (dropflag)
1729 {
1730 if (m_dupBuffer[0]->bDup)
1731 {
1732 m_dupBuffer[0]->dupPic->picStruct = tripling;
1733 m_dupBuffer[0]->bDup = false;
1734 read++;
1735 }
1736 else
1737 {
1738 m_dupBuffer[0]->dupPic->picStruct = doubling;
1739 m_dupBuffer[0]->bDup = true;
1740 m_dupBuffer[1]->bOccupied = false;
1741 read++;
1742 return 0;
1743 }
1744 }
1745 else if (m_dupBuffer[0]->bDup)
1746 m_dupBuffer[0]->bDup = false;
1747 else
1748 m_dupBuffer[0]->dupPic->picStruct = 0;
1749 }
1750
1751 if (read < written)
1752 {
1753 inputPic = m_dupBuffer[0]->dupPic;
1754 read++;
1755 }
1756 }
1757 else
1758 inputPic = pic_in;
1759
1760 Frame *inFrame;
1761 x265_param *p = (m_reconfigure || m_reconfigureRc) ? m_latestParam : m_param;
1762 if (m_dpb->m_freeList.empty())
1763 {
1764 inFrame = new Frame;
1765 inFrame->m_encodeStartTime = x265_mdate();
1766 if (inFrame->create(p, inputPic->quantOffsets))
1767 {
1768 /* the first PicYuv created is asked to generate the CU and block unit offset
1769 * arrays which are then shared with all subsequent PicYuv (orig and recon)
1770 * allocated by this top level encoder */
1771 if (m_sps.cuOffsetY)
1772 {
1773 inFrame->m_fencPic->m_cuOffsetY = m_sps.cuOffsetY;
1774 inFrame->m_fencPic->m_buOffsetY = m_sps.buOffsetY;
1775 if (m_param->internalCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
1776 {
1777 inFrame->m_fencPic->m_cuOffsetC = m_sps.cuOffsetC;
1778 inFrame->m_fencPic->m_buOffsetC = m_sps.buOffsetC;
1779 }
1780 }
1781 else
1782 {
1783 if (!inFrame->m_fencPic->createOffsets(m_sps))
1784 {
1785 m_aborted = true;
1786 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_ERROR, "memory allocation failure, aborting encode\n");
1787 inFrame->destroy();
1788 delete inFrame;
1789 return -1;
1790 }
1791 else
1792 {
1793 m_sps.cuOffsetY = inFrame->m_fencPic->m_cuOffsetY;
1794 m_sps.buOffsetY = inFrame->m_fencPic->m_buOffsetY;
1795 if (m_param->internalCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
1796 {
1797 m_sps.cuOffsetC = inFrame->m_fencPic->m_cuOffsetC;
1798 m_sps.cuOffsetY = inFrame->m_fencPic->m_cuOffsetY;
1799 m_sps.buOffsetC = inFrame->m_fencPic->m_buOffsetC;
1800 m_sps.buOffsetY = inFrame->m_fencPic->m_buOffsetY;
1801 }
1802 }
1803 }
1804 if (m_param->recursionSkipMode == EDGE_BASED_RSKIP && m_param->bHistBasedSceneCut)
1805 {
1806 pixel* src = m_edgePic;
1807 primitives.planecopy_pp_shr(src, inFrame->m_fencPic->m_picWidth, inFrame->m_edgeBitPic, inFrame->m_fencPic->m_stride,
1808 inFrame->m_fencPic->m_picWidth, inFrame->m_fencPic->m_picHeight, 0);
1809 }
1810 }
1811 else
1812 {
1813 m_aborted = true;
1814 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_ERROR, "memory allocation failure, aborting encode\n");
1815 inFrame->destroy();
1816 delete inFrame;
1817 return -1;
1818 }
1819 }
1820 else
1821 {
1822 inFrame = m_dpb->m_freeList.popBack();
1823 inFrame->m_encodeStartTime = x265_mdate();
1824 /* Set lowres scencut and satdCost here to aovid overwriting ANALYSIS_READ
1825 decision by lowres init*/
1826 inFrame->m_lowres.bScenecut = false;
1827 inFrame->m_lowres.satdCost = (int64_t)-1;
1828 inFrame->m_lowresInit = false;
1829 inFrame->m_isInsideWindow = 0;
1830 }
1831
1832 /* Copy input picture into a Frame and PicYuv, send to lookahead */
1833 inFrame->m_fencPic->copyFromPicture(*inputPic, *m_param, m_sps.conformanceWindow.rightOffset, m_sps.conformanceWindow.bottomOffset);
1834
1835 inFrame->m_poc = ++m_pocLast;
1836 inFrame->m_userData = inputPic->userData;
1837 inFrame->m_pts = inputPic->pts;
1838 if (m_param->bHistBasedSceneCut)
1839 {
1840 inFrame->m_lowres.bScenecut = (inputPic->frameData.bScenecut == 1) ? true : false;
1841 inFrame->m_lowres.m_bIsMaxThres = isMaxThres;
1842 if (m_param->radl && m_param->keyframeMax != m_param->keyframeMin)
1843 inFrame->m_lowres.m_bIsHardScenecut = isHardSC;
1844 }
1845
1846 if ((m_param->bEnableSceneCutAwareQp & BACKWARD) && m_param->rc.bStatRead)
1847 {
1848 RateControlEntry * rcEntry = NULL;
1849 rcEntry = &(m_rateControl->m_rce2Pass[inFrame->m_poc]);
1850 if(rcEntry->scenecut)
1851 {
1852 int backwardWindow = X265_MIN(int((m_param->bwdScenecutWindow / 1000.0) * (m_param->fpsNum / m_param->fpsDenom)), p->lookaheadDepth);
1853 for (int i = 1; i <= backwardWindow; i++)
1854 {
1855 int frameNum = inFrame->m_poc - i;
1856 Frame * frame = m_lookahead->m_inputQueue.getPOC(frameNum);
1857 if (frame)
1858 frame->m_isInsideWindow = BACKWARD_WINDOW;
1859 }
1860 }
1861 }
1862 if (m_param->bHistBasedSceneCut && m_param->analysisSave)
1863 {
1864 memcpy(inFrame->m_analysisData.edgeHist, m_curEdgeHist, EDGE_BINS * sizeof(int32_t));
1865 memcpy(inFrame->m_analysisData.yuvHist[0], m_curYUVHist[0], HISTOGRAM_BINS *sizeof(int32_t));
1866 if (inputPic->colorSpace != X265_CSP_I400)
1867 {
1868 memcpy(inFrame->m_analysisData.yuvHist[1], m_curYUVHist[1], HISTOGRAM_BINS * sizeof(int32_t));
1869 memcpy(inFrame->m_analysisData.yuvHist[2], m_curYUVHist[2], HISTOGRAM_BINS * sizeof(int32_t));
1870 }
1871 }
1872 inFrame->m_forceqp = inputPic->forceqp;
1873 inFrame->m_param = (m_reconfigure || m_reconfigureRc) ? m_latestParam : m_param;
1874 inFrame->m_picStruct = inputPic->picStruct;
1875 if (m_param->bField && m_param->interlaceMode)
1876 inFrame->m_fieldNum = inputPic->fieldNum;
1877
1878 copyUserSEIMessages(inFrame, inputPic);
1879
1880 /*Copy Dolby Vision RPU from inputPic to frame*/
1881 if (inputPic->rpu.payloadSize)
1882 {
1883 inFrame->m_rpu.payloadSize = inputPic->rpu.payloadSize;
1884 inFrame->m_rpu.payload = new uint8_t[inputPic->rpu.payloadSize];
1885 memcpy(inFrame->m_rpu.payload, inputPic->rpu.payload, inputPic->rpu.payloadSize);
1886 }
1887
1888 if (inputPic->quantOffsets != NULL)
1889 {
1890 int cuCount;
1891 if (m_param->rc.qgSize == 8)
1892 cuCount = inFrame->m_lowres.maxBlocksInRowFullRes * inFrame->m_lowres.maxBlocksInColFullRes;
1893 else
1894 cuCount = inFrame->m_lowres.maxBlocksInRow * inFrame->m_lowres.maxBlocksInCol;
1895 memcpy(inFrame->m_quantOffsets, inputPic->quantOffsets, cuCount * sizeof(float));
1896 }
1897
1898 if (m_pocLast == 0)
1899 m_firstPts = inFrame->m_pts;
1900 if (m_bframeDelay && m_pocLast == m_bframeDelay)
1901 m_bframeDelayTime = inFrame->m_pts - m_firstPts;
1902
1903 /* Encoder holds a reference count until stats collection is finished */
1904 ATOMIC_INC(&inFrame->m_countRefEncoders);
1905
1906 if ((m_param->rc.aqMode || m_param->bEnableWeightedPred || m_param->bEnableWeightedBiPred) &&
1907 (m_param->rc.cuTree && m_param->rc.bStatRead))
1908 {
1909 if (!m_rateControl->cuTreeReadFor2Pass(inFrame))
1910 {
1911 m_aborted = 1;
1912 return -1;
1913 }
1914 }
1915
1916 /* Use the frame types from the first pass, if available */
1917 int sliceType = (m_param->rc.bStatRead) ? m_rateControl->rateControlSliceType(inFrame->m_poc) : inputPic->sliceType;
1918
1919 /* In analysisSave mode, x265_analysis_data is allocated in inputPic and inFrame points to this */
1920 /* Load analysis data before lookahead->addPicture, since sliceType has been decided */
1921 if (m_param->analysisLoad)
1922 {
1923 /* reads analysis data for the frame and allocates memory based on slicetype */
1924 static int paramBytes = CONF_OFFSET_BYTES;
1925 if (!inFrame->m_poc && m_param->bAnalysisType != HEVC_INFO)
1926 {
1927 x265_analysis_validate saveParam = inputPic->analysisData.saveParam;
1928 paramBytes += validateAnalysisData(&saveParam, 0);
1929 if (paramBytes == -1)
1930 {
1931 m_aborted = true;
1932 return -1;
1933 }
1934 }
1935 if (m_saveCTUSize)
1936 {
1937 cuLocation cuLocInFrame;
1938 cuLocInFrame.init(m_param);
1939 /* Set skipWidth/skipHeight flags when the out of bound pixels in lowRes is greater than half of maxCUSize */
1940 int extendedWidth = ((m_param->sourceWidth / 2 + m_param->maxCUSize - 1) >> m_param->maxLog2CUSize) * m_param->maxCUSize;
1941 int extendedHeight = ((m_param->sourceHeight / 2 + m_param->maxCUSize - 1) >> m_param->maxLog2CUSize) * m_param->maxCUSize;
1942 uint32_t outOfBoundaryLowres = extendedWidth - m_param->sourceWidth / 2;
1943 if (outOfBoundaryLowres * 2 >= m_param->maxCUSize)
1944 cuLocInFrame.skipWidth = true;
1945 uint32_t outOfBoundaryLowresH = extendedHeight - m_param->sourceHeight / 2;
1946 if (outOfBoundaryLowresH * 2 >= m_param->maxCUSize)
1947 cuLocInFrame.skipHeight = true;
1948 readAnalysisFile(&inFrame->m_analysisData, inFrame->m_poc, inputPic, paramBytes, cuLocInFrame);
1949 }
1950 else
1951 readAnalysisFile(&inFrame->m_analysisData, inFrame->m_poc, inputPic, paramBytes);
1952 inFrame->m_poc = inFrame->m_analysisData.poc;
1953 sliceType = inFrame->m_analysisData.sliceType;
1954 inFrame->m_lowres.bScenecut = !!inFrame->m_analysisData.bScenecut;
1955 inFrame->m_lowres.satdCost = inFrame->m_analysisData.satdCost;
1956 if (m_param->bDisableLookahead)
1957 {
1958 inFrame->m_lowres.sliceType = sliceType;
1959 inFrame->m_lowres.bKeyframe = !!inFrame->m_analysisData.lookahead.keyframe;
1960 inFrame->m_lowres.bLastMiniGopBFrame = !!inFrame->m_analysisData.lookahead.lastMiniGopBFrame;
1961 if (m_rateControl->m_isVbv)
1962 {
1963 int vbvCount = m_param->lookaheadDepth + m_param->bframes + 2;
1964 for (int index = 0; index < vbvCount; index++)
1965 {
1966 inFrame->m_lowres.plannedSatd[index] = inFrame->m_analysisData.lookahead.plannedSatd[index];
1967 inFrame->m_lowres.plannedType[index] = inFrame->m_analysisData.lookahead.plannedType[index];
1968 }
1969 }
1970 }
1971 }
1972 if (m_param->bUseRcStats && inputPic->rcData)
1973 {
1974 RcStats* rc = (RcStats*)inputPic->rcData;
1975 m_rateControl->m_accumPQp = rc->cumulativePQp;
1976 m_rateControl->m_accumPNorm = rc->cumulativePNorm;
1977 m_rateControl->m_isNextGop = true;
1978 for (int j = 0; j < 3; j++)
1979 m_rateControl->m_lastQScaleFor[j] = rc->lastQScaleFor[j];
1980 m_rateControl->m_wantedBitsWindow = rc->wantedBitsWindow;
1981 m_rateControl->m_cplxrSum = rc->cplxrSum;
1982 m_rateControl->m_totalBits = rc->totalBits;
1983 m_rateControl->m_encodedBits = rc->encodedBits;
1984 m_rateControl->m_shortTermCplxSum = rc->shortTermCplxSum;
1985 m_rateControl->m_shortTermCplxCount = rc->shortTermCplxCount;
1986 if (m_rateControl->m_isVbv)
1987 {
1988 m_rateControl->m_bufferFillFinal = rc->bufferFillFinal;
1989 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++)
1990 {
1991 m_rateControl->m_pred[i].coeff = rc->coeff[i];
1992 m_rateControl->m_pred[i].count = rc->count[i];
1993 m_rateControl->m_pred[i].offset = rc->offset[i];
1994 }
1995 }
1996 m_param->bUseRcStats = 0;
1997 }
1998
1999 if (m_param->bEnableFrameDuplication && ((read < written) || (m_dupBuffer[0]->dupPic->picStruct == tripling && (read <= written))))
2000 {
2001 if (m_dupBuffer[0]->dupPic->picStruct == tripling)
2002 m_dupBuffer[0]->bOccupied = m_dupBuffer[1]->bOccupied = false;
2003 else
2004 {
2005 copyPicture(m_dupBuffer[0]->dupPic, m_dupBuffer[1]->dupPic);
2006 m_dupBuffer[1]->bOccupied = false;
2007 }
2008 }
2009
2010 if (m_reconfigureRc)
2011 inFrame->m_reconfigureRc = true;
2012
2013 m_lookahead->addPicture(*inFrame, sliceType);
2014 m_numDelayedPic++;
2015 }
2016 else if (m_latestParam->forceFlush == 2)
2017 m_lookahead->m_filled = true;
2018 else
2019 m_lookahead->flush();
2020
2021 FrameEncoder *curEncoder = m_frameEncoder[m_curEncoder];
2022 m_curEncoder = (m_curEncoder + 1) % m_param->frameNumThreads;
2023 int ret = 0;
2024
2025 /* Normal operation is to wait for the current frame encoder to complete its current frame
2026 * and then to give it a new frame to work on. In zero-latency mode, we must encode this
2027 * input picture before returning so the order must be reversed. This do/while() loop allows
2028 * us to alternate the order of the calls without ugly code replication */
2029 Frame* outFrame = NULL;
2030 Frame* frameEnc = NULL;
2031 int pass = 0;
2032 do
2033 {
2034 /* getEncodedPicture() should block until the FrameEncoder has completed
2035 * encoding the frame. This is how back-pressure through the API is
2036 * accomplished when the encoder is full */
2037 if (!m_bZeroLatency || pass)
2038 outFrame = curEncoder->getEncodedPicture(m_nalList);
2039 if (outFrame)
2040 {
2041 Slice *slice = outFrame->m_encData->m_slice;
2042 x265_frame_stats* frameData = NULL;
2043
2044 /* Free up inputPic->analysisData since it has already been used */
2045 if ((m_param->analysisLoad && !m_param->analysisSave) || ((m_param->bAnalysisType == AVC_INFO) && slice->m_sliceType != I_SLICE))
2046 x265_free_analysis_data(m_param, &outFrame->m_analysisData);
2047
2048 if (pic_out)
2049 {
2050 PicYuv *recpic = outFrame->m_reconPic;
2051 pic_out->poc = slice->m_poc;
2052 pic_out->bitDepth = X265_DEPTH;
2053 pic_out->userData = outFrame->m_userData;
2054 pic_out->colorSpace = m_param->internalCsp;
2055 frameData = &(pic_out->frameData);
2056
2057 pic_out->pts = outFrame->m_pts;
2058 pic_out->dts = outFrame->m_dts;
2059 pic_out->reorderedPts = outFrame->m_reorderedPts;
2060 pic_out->sliceType = outFrame->m_lowres.sliceType;
2061 pic_out->planes[0] = recpic->m_picOrg[0];
2062 pic_out->stride[0] = (int)(recpic->m_stride * sizeof(pixel));
2063 if (m_param->internalCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
2064 {
2065 pic_out->planes[1] = recpic->m_picOrg[1];
2066 pic_out->stride[1] = (int)(recpic->m_strideC * sizeof(pixel));
2067 pic_out->planes[2] = recpic->m_picOrg[2];
2068 pic_out->stride[2] = (int)(recpic->m_strideC * sizeof(pixel));
2069 }
2070
2071 /* Dump analysis data from pic_out to file in save mode and free */
2072 if (m_param->analysisSave)
2073 {
2074 pic_out->analysisData.poc = pic_out->poc;
2075 pic_out->analysisData.sliceType = pic_out->sliceType;
2076 pic_out->analysisData.bScenecut = outFrame->m_lowres.bScenecut;
2077 if (m_param->bHistBasedSceneCut)
2078 {
2079 memcpy(pic_out->analysisData.edgeHist, outFrame->m_analysisData.edgeHist, EDGE_BINS * sizeof(int32_t));
2080 memcpy(pic_out->analysisData.yuvHist[0], outFrame->m_analysisData.yuvHist[0], HISTOGRAM_BINS * sizeof(int32_t));
2081 if (pic_out->colorSpace != X265_CSP_I400)
2082 {
2083 memcpy(pic_out->analysisData.yuvHist[1], outFrame->m_analysisData.yuvHist[1], HISTOGRAM_BINS * sizeof(int32_t));
2084 memcpy(pic_out->analysisData.yuvHist[2], outFrame->m_analysisData.yuvHist[2], HISTOGRAM_BINS * sizeof(int32_t));
2085 }
2086 }
2087 pic_out->analysisData.satdCost = outFrame->m_lowres.satdCost;
2088 pic_out->analysisData.numCUsInFrame = outFrame->m_analysisData.numCUsInFrame;
2089 pic_out->analysisData.numPartitions = outFrame->m_analysisData.numPartitions;
2090 pic_out->analysisData.wt = outFrame->m_analysisData.wt;
2091 pic_out->analysisData.interData = outFrame->m_analysisData.interData;
2092 pic_out->analysisData.intraData = outFrame->m_analysisData.intraData;
2093 pic_out->analysisData.distortionData = outFrame->m_analysisData.distortionData;
2094 pic_out->analysisData.modeFlag[0] = outFrame->m_analysisData.modeFlag[0];
2095 pic_out->analysisData.modeFlag[1] = outFrame->m_analysisData.modeFlag[1];
2096 if (m_param->bDisableLookahead)
2097 {
2098 int factor = 1;
2099 if (m_param->scaleFactor)
2100 factor = m_param->scaleFactor * 2;
2101 pic_out->analysisData.numCuInHeight = outFrame->m_analysisData.numCuInHeight;
2102 pic_out->analysisData.lookahead.dts = outFrame->m_dts;
2103 pic_out->analysisData.lookahead.reorderedPts = outFrame->m_reorderedPts;
2104 pic_out->analysisData.satdCost *= factor;
2105 pic_out->analysisData.lookahead.keyframe = outFrame->m_lowres.bKeyframe;
2106 pic_out->analysisData.lookahead.lastMiniGopBFrame = outFrame->m_lowres.bLastMiniGopBFrame;
2107 if (m_rateControl->m_isVbv)
2108 {
2109 int vbvCount = m_param->lookaheadDepth + m_param->bframes + 2;
2110 for (int index = 0; index < vbvCount; index++)
2111 {
2112 pic_out->analysisData.lookahead.plannedSatd[index] = outFrame->m_lowres.plannedSatd[index];
2113 pic_out->analysisData.lookahead.plannedType[index] = outFrame->m_lowres.plannedType[index];
2114 }
2115 for (uint32_t index = 0; index < pic_out->analysisData.numCuInHeight; index++)
2116 {
2117 outFrame->m_analysisData.lookahead.intraSatdForVbv[index] = outFrame->m_encData->m_rowStat[index].intraSatdForVbv;
2118 outFrame->m_analysisData.lookahead.satdForVbv[index] = outFrame->m_encData->m_rowStat[index].satdForVbv;
2119 }
2120 pic_out->analysisData.lookahead.intraSatdForVbv = outFrame->m_analysisData.lookahead.intraSatdForVbv;
2121 pic_out->analysisData.lookahead.satdForVbv = outFrame->m_analysisData.lookahead.satdForVbv;
2122 for (uint32_t index = 0; index < pic_out->analysisData.numCUsInFrame; index++)
2123 {
2124 outFrame->m_analysisData.lookahead.intraVbvCost[index] = outFrame->m_encData->m_cuStat[index].intraVbvCost;
2125 outFrame->m_analysisData.lookahead.vbvCost[index] = outFrame->m_encData->m_cuStat[index].vbvCost;
2126 }
2127 pic_out->analysisData.lookahead.intraVbvCost = outFrame->m_analysisData.lookahead.intraVbvCost;
2128 pic_out->analysisData.lookahead.vbvCost = outFrame->m_analysisData.lookahead.vbvCost;
2129 }
2130 }
2131 writeAnalysisFile(&pic_out->analysisData, *outFrame->m_encData);
2132 pic_out->analysisData.saveParam = pic_out->analysisData.saveParam;
2133 if (m_param->bUseAnalysisFile)
2134 x265_free_analysis_data(m_param, &pic_out->analysisData);
2135 }
2136 }
2137 if (m_param->rc.bStatWrite && (m_param->analysisMultiPassRefine || m_param->analysisMultiPassDistortion))
2138 {
2139 if (pic_out)
2140 {
2141 pic_out->analysisData.poc = pic_out->poc;
2142 pic_out->analysisData.interData = outFrame->m_analysisData.interData;
2143 pic_out->analysisData.intraData = outFrame->m_analysisData.intraData;
2144 pic_out->analysisData.distortionData = outFrame->m_analysisData.distortionData;
2145 }
2146 writeAnalysisFileRefine(&outFrame->m_analysisData, *outFrame->m_encData);
2147 }
2148 if (m_param->analysisMultiPassRefine || m_param->analysisMultiPassDistortion)
2149 x265_free_analysis_data(m_param, &outFrame->m_analysisData);
2150 if (m_param->internalCsp == X265_CSP_I400)
2151 {
2152 if (slice->m_sliceType == P_SLICE)
2153 {
2154 if (slice->m_weightPredTable[0][0][0].wtPresent)
2155 m_numLumaWPFrames++;
2156 }
2157 else if (slice->m_sliceType == B_SLICE)
2158 {
2159 bool bLuma = false;
2160 for (int l = 0; l < 2; l++)
2161 {
2162 if (slice->m_weightPredTable[l][0][0].wtPresent)
2163 bLuma = true;
2164 }
2165 if (bLuma)
2166 m_numLumaWPBiFrames++;
2167 }
2168 }
2169 else
2170 {
2171 if (slice->m_sliceType == P_SLICE)
2172 {
2173 if (slice->m_weightPredTable[0][0][0].wtPresent)
2174 m_numLumaWPFrames++;
2175 if (slice->m_weightPredTable[0][0][1].wtPresent ||
2176 slice->m_weightPredTable[0][0][2].wtPresent)
2177 m_numChromaWPFrames++;
2178 }
2179 else if (slice->m_sliceType == B_SLICE)
2180 {
2181 bool bLuma = false, bChroma = false;
2182 for (int l = 0; l < 2; l++)
2183 {
2184 if (slice->m_weightPredTable[l][0][0].wtPresent)
2185 bLuma = true;
2186 if (slice->m_weightPredTable[l][0][1].wtPresent ||
2187 slice->m_weightPredTable[l][0][2].wtPresent)
2188 bChroma = true;
2189 }
2190
2191 if (bLuma)
2192 m_numLumaWPBiFrames++;
2193 if (bChroma)
2194 m_numChromaWPBiFrames++;
2195 }
2196 }
2197 if (m_aborted)
2198 return -1;
2199
2200 if ((m_outputCount + 1) >= m_param->chunkStart)
2201 finishFrameStats(outFrame, curEncoder, frameData, m_pocLast);
2202 if (m_param->analysisSave)
2203 {
2204 pic_out->analysisData.frameBits = frameData->bits;
2205 if (!slice->isIntra())
2206 {
2207 for (int ref = 0; ref < MAX_NUM_REF; ref++)
2208 pic_out->analysisData.list0POC[ref] = frameData->list0POC[ref];
2209
2210 double totalIntraPercent = 0;
2211
2212 for (uint32_t depth = 0; depth < m_param->maxCUDepth; depth++)
2213 for (uint32_t intramode = 0; intramode < 3; intramode++)
2214 totalIntraPercent += frameData->cuStats.percentIntraDistribution[depth][intramode];
2215 totalIntraPercent += frameData->cuStats.percentIntraNxN;
2216
2217 for (uint32_t depth = 0; depth < m_param->maxCUDepth; depth++)
2218 totalIntraPercent += frameData->puStats.percentIntraPu[depth];
2219 pic_out->analysisData.totalIntraPercent = totalIntraPercent;
2220
2221 if (!slice->isInterP())
2222 {
2223 for (int ref = 0; ref < MAX_NUM_REF; ref++)
2224 pic_out->analysisData.list1POC[ref] = frameData->list1POC[ref];
2225 }
2226 }
2227 }
2228
2229 /* Write RateControl Frame level stats in multipass encodes */
2230 if (m_param->rc.bStatWrite)
2231 if (m_rateControl->writeRateControlFrameStats(outFrame, &curEncoder->m_rce))
2232 m_aborted = true;
2233 if (pic_out)
2234 {
2235 /* m_rcData is allocated for every frame */
2236 pic_out->rcData = outFrame->m_rcData;
2237 outFrame->m_rcData->qpaRc = outFrame->m_encData->m_avgQpRc;
2238 outFrame->m_rcData->qRceq = curEncoder->m_rce.qRceq;
2239 outFrame->m_rcData->qpNoVbv = curEncoder->m_rce.qpNoVbv;
2240 outFrame->m_rcData->coeffBits = outFrame->m_encData->m_frameStats.coeffBits;
2241 outFrame->m_rcData->miscBits = outFrame->m_encData->m_frameStats.miscBits;
2242 outFrame->m_rcData->mvBits = outFrame->m_encData->m_frameStats.mvBits;
2243 outFrame->m_rcData->qScale = outFrame->m_rcData->newQScale = x265_qp2qScale(outFrame->m_encData->m_avgQpRc);
2244 outFrame->m_rcData->poc = curEncoder->m_rce.poc;
2245 outFrame->m_rcData->encodeOrder = curEncoder->m_rce.encodeOrder;
2246 outFrame->m_rcData->sliceType = curEncoder->m_rce.sliceType;
2247 outFrame->m_rcData->keptAsRef = curEncoder->m_rce.sliceType == B_SLICE && !IS_REFERENCED(outFrame) ? 0 : 1;
2248 outFrame->m_rcData->qpAq = outFrame->m_encData->m_avgQpAq;
2249 outFrame->m_rcData->iCuCount = outFrame->m_encData->m_frameStats.percent8x8Intra * m_rateControl->m_ncu;
2250 outFrame->m_rcData->pCuCount = outFrame->m_encData->m_frameStats.percent8x8Inter * m_rateControl->m_ncu;
2251 outFrame->m_rcData->skipCuCount = outFrame->m_encData->m_frameStats.percent8x8Skip * m_rateControl->m_ncu;
2252 }
2253
2254 /* Allow this frame to be recycled if no frame encoders are using it for reference */
2255 if (!pic_out)
2256 {
2257 ATOMIC_DEC(&outFrame->m_countRefEncoders);
2258 m_dpb->recycleUnreferenced();
2259 }
2260 else
2261 m_exportedPic = outFrame;
2262
2263 m_outputCount++;
2264 if (m_param->chunkEnd == m_outputCount)
2265 m_numDelayedPic = 0;
2266 else
2267 m_numDelayedPic--;
2268
2269 ret = 1;
2270 }
2271
2272 /* pop a single frame from decided list, then provide to frame encoder
2273 * curEncoder is guaranteed to be idle at this point */
2274 if (!pass)
2275 frameEnc = m_lookahead->getDecidedPicture();
2276 if (frameEnc && !pass && (!m_param->chunkEnd || (m_encodedFrameNum < m_param->chunkEnd)))
2277 {
2278 if ((m_param->bEnableSceneCutAwareQp & FORWARD) && m_param->rc.bStatRead)
2279 {
2280 RateControlEntry * rcEntry;
