2281 rcEntry = &(m_rateControl->m_rce2Pass[frameEnc->m_poc]);
2282
2283 if (rcEntry->scenecut)
2284 {
2285 if (m_rateControl->m_lastScenecut == -1)
2286 m_rateControl->m_lastScenecut = frameEnc->m_poc;
2287 else
2288 {
2289 int maxWindowSize = int((m_param->fwdScenecutWindow / 1000.0) * (m_param->fpsNum / m_param->fpsDenom) + 0.5);
2290 if (frameEnc->m_poc > (m_rateControl->m_lastScenecut + maxWindowSize))
2291 m_rateControl->m_lastScenecut = frameEnc->m_poc;
2292 }
2293 }
2294 }
2295
2296 if (m_param->analysisMultiPassRefine || m_param->analysisMultiPassDistortion)
2297 {
2298 uint32_t widthInCU = (m_param->sourceWidth + m_param->maxCUSize - 1) >> m_param->maxLog2CUSize;
2299 uint32_t heightInCU = (m_param->sourceHeight + m_param->maxCUSize - 1) >> m_param->maxLog2CUSize;
2300 frameEnc->m_analysisData.numCUsInFrame = widthInCU * heightInCU;
2301 frameEnc->m_analysisData.numPartitions = m_param->num4x4Partitions;
2302 x265_alloc_analysis_data(m_param, &frameEnc->m_analysisData);
2303 frameEnc->m_analysisData.poc = frameEnc->m_poc;
2304 if (m_param->rc.bStatRead)
2305 readAnalysisFile(&frameEnc->m_analysisData, frameEnc->m_poc, frameEnc->m_lowres.sliceType);
2306 }
2307
2308 if (m_param->bResetZoneConfig)
2309 {
2310 for (int i = 0; i < m_param->rc.zonefileCount; i++)
2311 {
2312 if (m_param->rc.zones[i].startFrame == frameEnc->m_poc)
2313 x265_encoder_reconfig(this, m_param->rc.zones[i].zoneParam);
2314 }
2315 }
2316
2317 if (frameEnc->m_reconfigureRc && m_reconfigureRc)
2318 {
2319 x265_copy_params(m_param, m_latestParam);
2320 m_rateControl->reconfigureRC();
2321 m_reconfigureRc = false;
2322 }
2323 if (frameEnc->m_reconfigureRc && !m_reconfigureRc)
2324 frameEnc->m_reconfigureRc = false;
2325 if (curEncoder->m_reconfigure)
2326 {
2327 /* One round robin cycle of FE reconfigure is complete */
2328 /* Safe to copy m_latestParam to Encoder::m_param, encoder reconfigure complete */
2329 for (int frameEncId = 0; frameEncId < m_param->frameNumThreads; frameEncId++)
2330 m_frameEncoder[frameEncId]->m_reconfigure = false;
2331 x265_copy_params(m_param, m_latestParam);
2332 m_reconfigure = false;
2333 }
2334
2335 /* Initiate reconfigure for this FE if necessary */
2336 curEncoder->m_param = m_reconfigure ? m_latestParam : m_param;
2337 curEncoder->m_reconfigure = m_reconfigure;
2338
2339 /* give this frame a FrameData instance before encoding */
2340 if (m_dpb->m_frameDataFreeList)
2341 {
2342 frameEnc->m_encData = m_dpb->m_frameDataFreeList;
2343 m_dpb->m_frameDataFreeList = m_dpb->m_frameDataFreeList->m_freeListNext;
2344 frameEnc->reinit(m_sps);
2345 frameEnc->m_param = m_reconfigure ? m_latestParam : m_param;
2346 frameEnc->m_encData->m_param = m_reconfigure ? m_latestParam : m_param;
2347 }
2348 else
2349 {
2350 frameEnc->allocEncodeData(m_reconfigure ? m_latestParam : m_param, m_sps);
2351 Slice* slice = frameEnc->m_encData->m_slice;
2352 slice->m_sps = &m_sps;
2353 slice->m_pps = &m_pps;
2354 slice->m_param = m_param;
2355 slice->m_maxNumMergeCand = m_param->maxNumMergeCand;
2356 slice->m_endCUAddr = slice->realEndAddress(m_sps.numCUsInFrame * m_param->num4x4Partitions);
2357 }
2358 if (m_param->analysisLoad && m_param->bDisableLookahead)
2359 {
2360 frameEnc->m_dts = frameEnc->m_analysisData.lookahead.dts;
2361 frameEnc->m_reorderedPts = frameEnc->m_analysisData.lookahead.reorderedPts;
2362 if (m_rateControl->m_isVbv)
2363 {
2364 for (uint32_t index = 0; index < frameEnc->m_analysisData.numCuInHeight; index++)
2365 {
2366 frameEnc->m_encData->m_rowStat[index].intraSatdForVbv = frameEnc->m_analysisData.lookahead.intraSatdForVbv[index];
2367 frameEnc->m_encData->m_rowStat[index].satdForVbv = frameEnc->m_analysisData.lookahead.satdForVbv[index];
2368 }
2369 for (uint32_t index = 0; index < frameEnc->m_analysisData.numCUsInFrame; index++)
2370 {
2371 frameEnc->m_encData->m_cuStat[index].intraVbvCost = frameEnc->m_analysisData.lookahead.intraVbvCost[index];
2372 frameEnc->m_encData->m_cuStat[index].vbvCost = frameEnc->m_analysisData.lookahead.vbvCost[index];
2373 }
2374 }
2375 }
2376 if (m_param->searchMethod == X265_SEA && frameEnc->m_lowres.sliceType != X265_TYPE_B)
2377 {
2378 int padX = m_param->maxCUSize + 32;
2379 int padY = m_param->maxCUSize + 16;
2380 uint32_t numCuInHeight = (frameEnc->m_encData->m_reconPic->m_picHeight + m_param->maxCUSize - 1) / m_param->maxCUSize;
2381 int maxHeight = numCuInHeight * m_param->maxCUSize;
2382 for (int i = 0; i < INTEGRAL_PLANE_NUM; i++)
2383 {
2384 frameEnc->m_encData->m_meBuffer[i] = X265_MALLOC(uint32_t, frameEnc->m_reconPic->m_stride * (maxHeight + (2 * padY)));
2385 if (frameEnc->m_encData->m_meBuffer[i])
2386 {
2387 memset(frameEnc->m_encData->m_meBuffer[i], 0, sizeof(uint32_t)* frameEnc->m_reconPic->m_stride * (maxHeight + (2 * padY)));
2388 frameEnc->m_encData->m_meIntegral[i] = frameEnc->m_encData->m_meBuffer[i] + frameEnc->m_encData->m_reconPic->m_stride * padY + padX;
2389 }
2390 else
2391 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_ERROR, "SEA motion search: POC %d Integral buffer[%d] unallocated\n", frameEnc->m_poc, i);
2392 }
2393 }
2394
2395 if (m_param->bOptQpPPS && frameEnc->m_lowres.bKeyframe && m_param->bRepeatHeaders)
2396 {
2397 ScopedLock qpLock(m_sliceQpLock);
2398 if (m_iFrameNum > 0)
2399 {
2400 //Search the least cost
2401 int64_t iLeastCost = m_iBitsCostSum[0];
2402 int iLeastId = 0;
2403 for (int i = 1; i < QP_MAX_MAX + 1; i++)
2404 {
2405 if (iLeastCost > m_iBitsCostSum[i])
2406 {
2407 iLeastId = i;
2408 iLeastCost = m_iBitsCostSum[i];
2409 }
2410 }
2411 /* If last slice Qp is close to (26 + m_iPPSQpMinus26) or outputs is all I-frame video,
2412 we don't need to change m_iPPSQpMinus26. */
2413 if (m_iFrameNum > 1)
2414 m_iPPSQpMinus26 = (iLeastId + 1) - 26;
2415 m_iFrameNum = 0;
2416 }
2417
2418 for (int i = 0; i < QP_MAX_MAX + 1; i++)
2419 m_iBitsCostSum[i] = 0;
2420 }
2421
2422 frameEnc->m_encData->m_slice->m_iPPSQpMinus26 = m_iPPSQpMinus26;
2423 frameEnc->m_encData->m_slice->numRefIdxDefault[0] = m_pps.numRefIdxDefault[0];
2424 frameEnc->m_encData->m_slice->numRefIdxDefault[1] = m_pps.numRefIdxDefault[1];
2425 frameEnc->m_encData->m_slice->m_iNumRPSInSPS = m_sps.spsrpsNum;
2426
2427 curEncoder->m_rce.encodeOrder = frameEnc->m_encodeOrder = m_encodedFrameNum++;
2428
2429 if (!m_param->analysisLoad || !m_param->bDisableLookahead)
2430 {
2431 if (m_bframeDelay)
2432 {
2433 int64_t *prevReorderedPts = m_prevReorderedPts;
2434 frameEnc->m_dts = m_encodedFrameNum > m_bframeDelay
2435 ? prevReorderedPts[(m_encodedFrameNum - m_bframeDelay) % m_bframeDelay]
2436 : frameEnc->m_reorderedPts - m_bframeDelayTime;
2437 prevReorderedPts[m_encodedFrameNum % m_bframeDelay] = frameEnc->m_reorderedPts;
2438 }
2439 else
2440 frameEnc->m_dts = frameEnc->m_reorderedPts;
2441 }
2442
2443 /* Allocate analysis data before encode in save mode. This is allocated in frameEnc */
2444 if (m_param->analysisSave && !m_param->analysisLoad)
2445 {
2446 x265_analysis_data* analysis = &frameEnc->m_analysisData;
2447 analysis->poc = frameEnc->m_poc;
2448 analysis->sliceType = frameEnc->m_lowres.sliceType;
2449 uint32_t widthInCU = (m_param->sourceWidth + m_param->maxCUSize - 1) >> m_param->maxLog2CUSize;
2450 uint32_t heightInCU = (m_param->sourceHeight + m_param->maxCUSize - 1) >> m_param->maxLog2CUSize;
2451
2452 uint32_t numCUsInFrame = widthInCU * heightInCU;
2453 analysis->numCUsInFrame = numCUsInFrame;
2454 analysis->numCuInHeight = heightInCU;
2455 analysis->numPartitions = m_param->num4x4Partitions;
2456 x265_alloc_analysis_data(m_param, analysis);
2457 }
2458 /* determine references, setup RPS, etc */
2459 m_dpb->prepareEncode(frameEnc);
2460 if (!!m_param->selectiveSAO)
2461 {
2462 Slice* slice = frameEnc->m_encData->m_slice;
2463 slice->m_bUseSao = curEncoder->m_frameFilter.m_useSao = 1;
2464 switch (m_param->selectiveSAO)
2465 {
2466 case 3: if (!IS_REFERENCED(frameEnc))
2467 slice->m_bUseSao = curEncoder->m_frameFilter.m_useSao = 0;
2468 break;
2469 case 2: if (!!m_param->bframes && slice->m_sliceType == B_SLICE)
2470 slice->m_bUseSao = curEncoder->m_frameFilter.m_useSao = 0;
2471 break;
2472 case 1: if (slice->m_sliceType != I_SLICE)
2473 slice->m_bUseSao = curEncoder->m_frameFilter.m_useSao = 0;
2474 break;
2475 }
2476 }
2477 else
2478 {
2479 Slice* slice = frameEnc->m_encData->m_slice;
2480 slice->m_bUseSao = curEncoder->m_frameFilter.m_useSao = 0;
2481 }
2482
2483 if (m_param->rc.rateControlMode != X265_RC_CQP)
2484 m_lookahead->getEstimatedPictureCost(frameEnc);
2485 if (m_param->bIntraRefresh)
2486 calcRefreshInterval(frameEnc);
2487
2488 /* Allow FrameEncoder::compressFrame() to start in the frame encoder thread */
2489 if (!curEncoder->startCompressFrame(frameEnc))
2490 m_aborted = true;
2491 }
2492 else if (m_encodedFrameNum)
2493 m_rateControl->setFinalFrameCount(m_encodedFrameNum);
2494 }
2495 while (m_bZeroLatency && ++pass < 2);
2496
2497 return ret;
2498}
2499
2500int Encoder::reconfigureParam(x265_param* encParam, x265_param* param)
2501{
2502 if (isReconfigureRc(encParam, param) && !param->rc.zonefileCount)
2503 {
2504 /* VBV can't be turned ON if it wasn't ON to begin with and can't be turned OFF if it was ON to begin with*/
2505 if (param->rc.vbvMaxBitrate > 0 && param->rc.vbvBufferSize > 0 &&
2506 encParam->rc.vbvMaxBitrate > 0 && encParam->rc.vbvBufferSize > 0)
2507 {
2508 m_reconfigureRc |= encParam->rc.vbvMaxBitrate != param->rc.vbvMaxBitrate;
2509 m_reconfigureRc |= encParam->rc.vbvBufferSize != param->rc.vbvBufferSize;
2510 if (m_reconfigureRc && m_param->bEmitHRDSEI)
2511 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_WARNING, "VBV parameters cannot be changed when HRD is in use.\n");
2512 else
2513 {
2514 encParam->rc.vbvMaxBitrate = param->rc.vbvMaxBitrate;
2515 encParam->rc.vbvBufferSize = param->rc.vbvBufferSize;
2516 }
2517 }
2518 m_reconfigureRc |= encParam->rc.bitrate != param->rc.bitrate;
2519 encParam->rc.bitrate = param->rc.bitrate;
2520 m_reconfigureRc |= encParam->rc.rfConstant != param->rc.rfConstant;
2521 encParam->rc.rfConstant = param->rc.rfConstant;
2522 }
2523 else
2524 {
2525 encParam->maxNumReferences = param->maxNumReferences; // never uses more refs than specified in stream headers
2526 encParam->bEnableFastIntra = param->bEnableFastIntra;
2527 encParam->bEnableEarlySkip = param->bEnableEarlySkip;
2528 encParam->recursionSkipMode = param->recursionSkipMode;
2529 encParam->searchMethod = param->searchMethod;
2530 /* Scratch buffer prevents me_range from being increased for esa/tesa */
2531 if (param->searchRange < encParam->searchRange)
2532 encParam->searchRange = param->searchRange;
2533 /* We can't switch out of subme=0 during encoding. */
2534 if (encParam->subpelRefine)
2535 encParam->subpelRefine = param->subpelRefine;
2536 encParam->rdoqLevel = param->rdoqLevel;
2537 encParam->rdLevel = param->rdLevel;
2538 encParam->bEnableRectInter = param->bEnableRectInter;
2539 encParam->maxNumMergeCand = param->maxNumMergeCand;
2540 encParam->bIntraInBFrames = param->bIntraInBFrames;
2541 if (param->scalingLists && !encParam->scalingLists)
2542 encParam->scalingLists = strdup(param->scalingLists);
2543
2544 encParam->rc.aqMode = param->rc.aqMode;
2545 encParam->rc.aqStrength = param->rc.aqStrength;
2546 encParam->noiseReductionInter = param->noiseReductionInter;
2547 encParam->noiseReductionIntra = param->noiseReductionIntra;
2548
2549 encParam->limitModes = param->limitModes;
2550 encParam->bEnableSplitRdSkip = param->bEnableSplitRdSkip;
2551 encParam->bCULossless = param->bCULossless;
2552 encParam->bEnableRdRefine = param->bEnableRdRefine;
2553 encParam->limitTU = param->limitTU;
2554 encParam->bEnableTSkipFast = param->bEnableTSkipFast;
2555 encParam->rdPenalty = param->rdPenalty;
2556 encParam->dynamicRd = param->dynamicRd;
2557 encParam->bEnableTransformSkip = param->bEnableTransformSkip;
2558 encParam->bEnableAMP = param->bEnableAMP;
2559
2560 /* Resignal changes in params in Parameter Sets */
2561 m_sps.maxAMPDepth = (m_sps.bUseAMP = param->bEnableAMP && param->bEnableAMP) ? param->maxCUDepth : 0;
2562 m_pps.bTransformSkipEnabled = param->bEnableTransformSkip ? 1 : 0;
2563
2564 }
2565 encParam->forceFlush = param->forceFlush;
2566 /* To add: Loop Filter/deblocking controls, transform skip, signhide require PPS to be resent */
2567 /* To add: SAO, temporal MVP, AMP, TU depths require SPS to be resent, at every CVS boundary */
2568 return x265_check_params(encParam);
2569}
2570
2571bool Encoder::isReconfigureRc(x265_param* latestParam, x265_param* param_in)
2572{
2573 return (latestParam->rc.vbvMaxBitrate != param_in->rc.vbvMaxBitrate
2574 || latestParam->rc.vbvBufferSize != param_in->rc.vbvBufferSize
2575 || latestParam->rc.bitrate != param_in->rc.bitrate
2576 || latestParam->rc.rfConstant != param_in->rc.rfConstant);
2577}
2578
2579void Encoder::copyCtuInfo(x265_ctu_info_t** frameCtuInfo, int poc)
2580{
2581 uint32_t widthInCU = (m_param->sourceWidth + m_param->maxCUSize - 1) >> m_param->maxLog2CUSize;
2582 uint32_t heightInCU = (m_param->sourceHeight + m_param->maxCUSize - 1) >> m_param->maxLog2CUSize;
2583 Frame* curFrame;
2584 Frame* prevFrame = NULL;
2585 int32_t* frameCTU;
2586 uint32_t numCUsInFrame = widthInCU * heightInCU;
2587 uint32_t maxNum8x8Partitions = 64;
2588 bool copied = false;
2589 do
2590 {
2591 curFrame = m_lookahead->m_inputQueue.getPOC(poc);
2592 if (!curFrame)
2593 curFrame = m_lookahead->m_outputQueue.getPOC(poc);
2594
2595 if (poc > 0)
2596 {
2597 prevFrame = m_lookahead->m_inputQueue.getPOC(poc - 1);
2598 if (!prevFrame)
2599 prevFrame = m_lookahead->m_outputQueue.getPOC(poc - 1);
2600 if (!prevFrame)
2601 {
2602 FrameEncoder* prevEncoder;
2603 for (int i = 0; i < m_param->frameNumThreads; i++)
2604 {
2605 prevEncoder = m_frameEncoder[i];
2606 prevFrame = prevEncoder->m_frame;
2607 if (prevFrame && (prevEncoder->m_frame->m_poc == poc - 1))
2608 {
2609 prevFrame = prevEncoder->m_frame;
2610 break;
2611 }
2612 }
2613 }
2614 }
2615 x265_ctu_info_t* ctuTemp, *prevCtuTemp;
2616 if (curFrame)
2617 {
2618 if (!curFrame->m_ctuInfo)
2619 CHECKED_MALLOC(curFrame->m_ctuInfo, x265_ctu_info_t*, 1);
2620 CHECKED_MALLOC(*curFrame->m_ctuInfo, x265_ctu_info_t, numCUsInFrame);
2621 CHECKED_MALLOC_ZERO(curFrame->m_prevCtuInfoChange, int, numCUsInFrame * maxNum8x8Partitions);
2622 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < numCUsInFrame; i++)
2623 {
2624 ctuTemp = *curFrame->m_ctuInfo + i;
2625 CHECKED_MALLOC(frameCTU, int32_t, maxNum8x8Partitions);
2626 ctuTemp->ctuInfo = (int32_t*)frameCTU;
2627 ctuTemp->ctuAddress = frameCtuInfo[i]->ctuAddress;
2628 memcpy(ctuTemp->ctuPartitions, frameCtuInfo[i]->ctuPartitions, sizeof(int32_t) * maxNum8x8Partitions);
2629 memcpy(ctuTemp->ctuInfo, frameCtuInfo[i]->ctuInfo, sizeof(int32_t) * maxNum8x8Partitions);
2630 if (prevFrame && curFrame->m_poc > 1)
2631 {
2632 prevCtuTemp = *prevFrame->m_ctuInfo + i;
2633 for (uint32_t j = 0; j < maxNum8x8Partitions; j++)
2634 curFrame->m_prevCtuInfoChange[i * maxNum8x8Partitions + j] = (*((int32_t *)prevCtuTemp->ctuInfo + j) == 2) ? (poc - 1) : prevFrame->m_prevCtuInfoChange[i * maxNum8x8Partitions + j];
2635 }
2636 }
2637 copied = true;
2638 curFrame->m_copied.trigger();
2639 }
2640 else
2641 {
2642 FrameEncoder* curEncoder;
2643 for (int i = 0; i < m_param->frameNumThreads; i++)
2644 {
2645 curEncoder = m_frameEncoder[i];
2646 curFrame = curEncoder->m_frame;
2647 if (curFrame)
2648 {
2649 if (poc == curFrame->m_poc)
2650 {
2651 if (!curFrame->m_ctuInfo)
2652 CHECKED_MALLOC(curFrame->m_ctuInfo, x265_ctu_info_t*, 1);
2653 CHECKED_MALLOC(*curFrame->m_ctuInfo, x265_ctu_info_t, numCUsInFrame);
2654 CHECKED_MALLOC_ZERO(curFrame->m_prevCtuInfoChange, int, numCUsInFrame * maxNum8x8Partitions);
2655 for (uint32_t l = 0; l < numCUsInFrame; l++)
2656 {
2657 ctuTemp = *curFrame->m_ctuInfo + l;
2658 CHECKED_MALLOC(frameCTU, int32_t, maxNum8x8Partitions);
2659 ctuTemp->ctuInfo = (int32_t*)frameCTU;
2660 ctuTemp->ctuAddress = frameCtuInfo[l]->ctuAddress;
2661 memcpy(ctuTemp->ctuPartitions, frameCtuInfo[l]->ctuPartitions, sizeof(int32_t) * maxNum8x8Partitions);
2662 memcpy(ctuTemp->ctuInfo, frameCtuInfo[l]->ctuInfo, sizeof(int32_t) * maxNum8x8Partitions);
2663 if (prevFrame && curFrame->m_poc > 1)
2664 {
2665 prevCtuTemp = *prevFrame->m_ctuInfo + l;
2666 for (uint32_t j = 0; j < maxNum8x8Partitions; j++)
2667 curFrame->m_prevCtuInfoChange[l * maxNum8x8Partitions + j] = (*((int32_t *)prevCtuTemp->ctuInfo + j) == CTU_INFO_CHANGE) ? (poc - 1) : prevFrame->m_prevCtuInfoChange[l * maxNum8x8Partitions + j];
2668 }
2669 }
2670 copied = true;
2671 curFrame->m_copied.trigger();
2672 break;
2673 }
2674 }
2675 }
2676 }
2677 } while (!copied);
2678 return;
2679fail:
2680 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < numCUsInFrame; i++)
2681 {
2682 X265_FREE((*curFrame->m_ctuInfo + i)->ctuInfo);
2683 (*curFrame->m_ctuInfo + i)->ctuInfo = NULL;
2684 }
2685 X265_FREE(*curFrame->m_ctuInfo);
2686 *(curFrame->m_ctuInfo) = NULL;
2687 X265_FREE(curFrame->m_ctuInfo);
2688 curFrame->m_ctuInfo = NULL;
2689 X265_FREE(curFrame->m_prevCtuInfoChange);
2690 curFrame->m_prevCtuInfoChange = NULL;
2691}
2692
2693void EncStats::addPsnr(double psnrY, double psnrU, double psnrV)
2694{
2695 m_psnrSumY += psnrY;
2696 m_psnrSumU += psnrU;
2697 m_psnrSumV += psnrV;
2698}
2699
2700void EncStats::addBits(uint64_t bits)
2701{
2702 m_accBits += bits;
2703 m_numPics++;
2704}
2705
2706void EncStats::addSsim(double ssim)
2707{
2708 m_globalSsim += ssim;
2709}
2710
2711void EncStats::addQP(double aveQp)
2712{
2713 m_totalQp += aveQp;
2714}
2715
2716char* Encoder::statsString(EncStats& stat, char* buffer)
2717{
2718 double fps = (double)m_param->fpsNum / m_param->fpsDenom;
2719 double scale = fps / 1000 / (double)stat.m_numPics;
2720
2721 int len = sprintf(buffer, "%6u, ", stat.m_numPics);
2722
2723 len += sprintf(buffer + len, "Avg QP:%2.2lf", stat.m_totalQp / (double)stat.m_numPics);
2724 len += sprintf(buffer + len, " kb/s: %-8.2lf", stat.m_accBits * scale);
2725 if (m_param->bEnablePsnr)
2726 {
2727 len += sprintf(buffer + len, " PSNR Mean: Y:%.3lf U:%.3lf V:%.3lf",
2728 stat.m_psnrSumY / (double)stat.m_numPics,
2729 stat.m_psnrSumU / (double)stat.m_numPics,
2730 stat.m_psnrSumV / (double)stat.m_numPics);
2731 }
2732 if (m_param->bEnableSsim)
2733 {
2734 sprintf(buffer + len, " SSIM Mean: %.6lf (%.3lfdB)",
2735 stat.m_globalSsim / (double)stat.m_numPics,
2736 x265_ssim2dB(stat.m_globalSsim / (double)stat.m_numPics));
2737 }
2738 return buffer;
2739}
2740
2741void Encoder::printSummary()
2742{
2743 if (m_param->logLevel < X265_LOG_INFO)
2744 return;
2745
2746 char buffer[200];
2747 if (m_analyzeI.m_numPics)
2748 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_INFO, "frame I: %s\n", statsString(m_analyzeI, buffer));
2749 if (m_analyzeP.m_numPics)
2750 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_INFO, "frame P: %s\n", statsString(m_analyzeP, buffer));
2751 if (m_analyzeB.m_numPics)
2752 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_INFO, "frame B: %s\n", statsString(m_analyzeB, buffer));
2753 if (m_param->bEnableWeightedPred && m_analyzeP.m_numPics)
2754 {
2755 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_INFO, "Weighted P-Frames: Y:%.1f%% UV:%.1f%%\n",
2756 (float)100.0 * m_numLumaWPFrames / m_analyzeP.m_numPics,
2757 (float)100.0 * m_numChromaWPFrames / m_analyzeP.m_numPics);
2758 }
2759 if (m_param->bEnableWeightedBiPred && m_analyzeB.m_numPics)
2760 {
2761 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_INFO, "Weighted B-Frames: Y:%.1f%% UV:%.1f%%\n",
2762 (float)100.0 * m_numLumaWPBiFrames / m_analyzeB.m_numPics,
2763 (float)100.0 * m_numChromaWPBiFrames / m_analyzeB.m_numPics);
2764 }
2765 int pWithB = 0;
2766 for (int i = 0; i <= m_param->bframes; i++)
2767 pWithB += m_lookahead->m_histogram[i];
2768
2769 if (pWithB)
2770 {
2771 int p = 0;
2772 for (int i = 0; i <= m_param->bframes; i++)
2773 p += sprintf(buffer + p, "%.1f%% ", 100. * m_lookahead->m_histogram[i] / pWithB);
2774
2775 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_INFO, "consecutive B-frames: %s\n", buffer);
2776 }
2777 if (m_param->bLossless)
2778 {
2779 float frameSize = (float)(m_param->sourceWidth - m_sps.conformanceWindow.rightOffset) *
2780 (m_param->sourceHeight - m_sps.conformanceWindow.bottomOffset);
2781 float uncompressed = frameSize * X265_DEPTH * m_analyzeAll.m_numPics;
2782
2783 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_INFO, "lossless compression ratio %.2f::1\n", uncompressed / m_analyzeAll.m_accBits);
2784 }
2785 if (m_param->bMultiPassOptRPS && m_param->rc.bStatRead)
2786 {
2787 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_INFO, "RPS in SPS: %d frames (%.2f%%), RPS not in SPS: %d frames (%.2f%%)\n",
2788 m_rpsInSpsCount, (float)100.0 * m_rpsInSpsCount / m_rateControl->m_numEntries,
2789 m_rateControl->m_numEntries - m_rpsInSpsCount,
2790 (float)100.0 * (m_rateControl->m_numEntries - m_rpsInSpsCount) / m_rateControl->m_numEntries);
2791 }
2792
2793 if (m_analyzeAll.m_numPics)
2794 {
2795 int p = 0;
2796 double elapsedEncodeTime = (double)(x265_mdate() - m_encodeStartTime) / 1000000;
2797 double elapsedVideoTime = (double)m_analyzeAll.m_numPics * m_param->fpsDenom / m_param->fpsNum;
2798 double bitrate = (0.001f * m_analyzeAll.m_accBits) / elapsedVideoTime;
2799
2800 p += sprintf(buffer + p, "\nencoded %d frames in %.2fs (%.2f fps), %.2f kb/s, Avg QP:%2.2lf", m_analyzeAll.m_numPics,
2801 elapsedEncodeTime, m_analyzeAll.m_numPics / elapsedEncodeTime, bitrate, m_analyzeAll.m_totalQp / (double)m_analyzeAll.m_numPics);
2802
2803 if (m_param->bEnablePsnr)
2804 {
2805 double globalPsnr = (m_analyzeAll.m_psnrSumY * 6 + m_analyzeAll.m_psnrSumU + m_analyzeAll.m_psnrSumV) / (8 * m_analyzeAll.m_numPics);
2806 p += sprintf(buffer + p, ", Global PSNR: %.3f", globalPsnr);
2807 }
2808
2809 if (m_param->bEnableSsim)
2810 p += sprintf(buffer + p, ", SSIM Mean Y: %.7f (%6.3f dB)", m_analyzeAll.m_globalSsim / m_analyzeAll.m_numPics, x265_ssim2dB(m_analyzeAll.m_globalSsim / m_analyzeAll.m_numPics));
2811
2812 sprintf(buffer + p, "\n");
2813 general_log(m_param, NULL, X265_LOG_INFO, buffer);
2814 }
2815 else
2816 general_log(m_param, NULL, X265_LOG_INFO, "\nencoded 0 frames\n");
2817
2818#if DETAILED_CU_STATS
2819 /* Summarize stats from all frame encoders */
2820 CUStats cuStats;
2821 for (int i = 0; i < m_param->frameNumThreads; i++)
2822 cuStats.accumulate(m_frameEncoder[i]->m_cuStats, *m_param);
2823
2824 if (!cuStats.totalCTUTime)
2825 return;
2826
2827 int totalWorkerCount = 0;
2828 for (int i = 0; i < m_numPools; i++)
2829 totalWorkerCount += m_threadPool[i].m_numWorkers;
2830
2831 int64_t batchElapsedTime, coopSliceElapsedTime;
2832 uint64_t batchCount, coopSliceCount;
2833 m_lookahead->getWorkerStats(batchElapsedTime, batchCount, coopSliceElapsedTime, coopSliceCount);
2834 int64_t lookaheadWorkerTime = m_lookahead->m_slicetypeDecideElapsedTime + m_lookahead->m_preLookaheadElapsedTime +
2835 batchElapsedTime + coopSliceElapsedTime;
2836
2837 int64_t totalWorkerTime = cuStats.totalCTUTime + cuStats.loopFilterElapsedTime + cuStats.pmodeTime +
2838 cuStats.pmeTime + lookaheadWorkerTime + cuStats.weightAnalyzeTime;
2839 int64_t elapsedEncodeTime = x265_mdate() - m_encodeStartTime;
2840
2841 int64_t interRDOTotalTime = 0, intraRDOTotalTime = 0;
2842 uint64_t interRDOTotalCount = 0, intraRDOTotalCount = 0;
2843 for (uint32_t i = 0; i <= m_param->maxCUDepth; i++)
2844 {
2845 interRDOTotalTime += cuStats.interRDOElapsedTime[i];
2846 intraRDOTotalTime += cuStats.intraRDOElapsedTime[i];
2847 interRDOTotalCount += cuStats.countInterRDO[i];
2848 intraRDOTotalCount += cuStats.countIntraRDO[i];
2849 }
2850
2851 /* Time within compressCTU() and pmode tasks not captured by ME, Intra mode selection, or RDO (2Nx2N merge, 2Nx2N bidir, etc) */
2852 int64_t unaccounted = (cuStats.totalCTUTime + cuStats.pmodeTime) -
2853 (cuStats.intraAnalysisElapsedTime + cuStats.motionEstimationElapsedTime + interRDOTotalTime + intraRDOTotalTime);
2854
2855#define ELAPSED_SEC(val) ((double)(val) / 1000000)
2856#define ELAPSED_MSEC(val) ((double)(val) / 1000)
2857
2858 if (m_param->bDistributeMotionEstimation && cuStats.countPMEMasters)
2859 {
2860 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_INFO, "CU: %%%05.2lf time spent in motion estimation, averaging %.3lf CU inter modes per CTU\n",
2861 100.0 * (cuStats.motionEstimationElapsedTime + cuStats.pmeTime) / totalWorkerTime,
2862 (double)cuStats.countMotionEstimate / cuStats.totalCTUs);
2863 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_INFO, "CU: %.3lf PME masters per inter CU, each blocked an average of %.3lf ns\n",
2864 (double)cuStats.countPMEMasters / cuStats.countMotionEstimate,
2865 (double)cuStats.pmeBlockTime / cuStats.countPMEMasters);
2866 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_INFO, "CU: %.3lf slaves per PME master, each took an average of %.3lf ms\n",
2867 (double)cuStats.countPMETasks / cuStats.countPMEMasters,
2868 ELAPSED_MSEC(cuStats.pmeTime) / cuStats.countPMETasks);
2869 }
2870 else
2871 {
2872 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_INFO, "CU: %%%05.2lf time spent in motion estimation, averaging %.3lf CU inter modes per CTU\n",
2873 100.0 * cuStats.motionEstimationElapsedTime / totalWorkerTime,
2874 (double)cuStats.countMotionEstimate / cuStats.totalCTUs);
2875
2876 if (cuStats.skippedMotionReferences[0] || cuStats.skippedMotionReferences[1] || cuStats.skippedMotionReferences[2])
2877 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_INFO, "CU: Skipped motion searches per depth %%%.2lf %%%.2lf %%%.2lf %%%.2lf\n",
2878 100.0 * cuStats.skippedMotionReferences[0] / cuStats.totalMotionReferences[0],
2879 100.0 * cuStats.skippedMotionReferences[1] / cuStats.totalMotionReferences[1],
2880 100.0 * cuStats.skippedMotionReferences[2] / cuStats.totalMotionReferences[2],
2881 100.0 * cuStats.skippedMotionReferences[3] / cuStats.totalMotionReferences[3]);
2882 }
2883 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_INFO, "CU: %%%05.2lf time spent in intra analysis, averaging %.3lf Intra PUs per CTU\n",
2884 100.0 * cuStats.intraAnalysisElapsedTime / totalWorkerTime,
2885 (double)cuStats.countIntraAnalysis / cuStats.totalCTUs);
2886 if (cuStats.skippedIntraCU[0] || cuStats.skippedIntraCU[1] || cuStats.skippedIntraCU[2])
2887 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_INFO, "CU: Skipped intra CUs at depth %%%.2lf %%%.2lf %%%.2lf\n",
2888 100.0 * cuStats.skippedIntraCU[0] / cuStats.totalIntraCU[0],
2889 100.0 * cuStats.skippedIntraCU[1] / cuStats.totalIntraCU[1],
2890 100.0 * cuStats.skippedIntraCU[2] / cuStats.totalIntraCU[2]);
2891 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_INFO, "CU: %%%05.2lf time spent in inter RDO, measuring %.3lf inter/merge predictions per CTU\n",
2892 100.0 * interRDOTotalTime / totalWorkerTime,
2893 (double)interRDOTotalCount / cuStats.totalCTUs);
2894 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_INFO, "CU: %%%05.2lf time spent in intra RDO, measuring %.3lf intra predictions per CTU\n",
2895 100.0 * intraRDOTotalTime / totalWorkerTime,
2896 (double)intraRDOTotalCount / cuStats.totalCTUs);
2897 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_INFO, "CU: %%%05.2lf time spent in loop filters, average %.3lf ms per call\n",
2898 100.0 * cuStats.loopFilterElapsedTime / totalWorkerTime,
2899 ELAPSED_MSEC(cuStats.loopFilterElapsedTime) / cuStats.countLoopFilter);
2900 if (cuStats.countWeightAnalyze && cuStats.weightAnalyzeTime)
2901 {
2902 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_INFO, "CU: %%%05.2lf time spent in weight analysis, average %.3lf ms per call\n",
2903 100.0 * cuStats.weightAnalyzeTime / totalWorkerTime,
2904 ELAPSED_MSEC(cuStats.weightAnalyzeTime) / cuStats.countWeightAnalyze);
2905 }
2906 if (m_param->bDistributeModeAnalysis && cuStats.countPModeMasters)
2907 {
2908 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_INFO, "CU: %.3lf PMODE masters per CTU, each blocked an average of %.3lf ns\n",
2909 (double)cuStats.countPModeMasters / cuStats.totalCTUs,
2910 (double)cuStats.pmodeBlockTime / cuStats.countPModeMasters);
2911 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_INFO, "CU: %.3lf slaves per PMODE master, each took average of %.3lf ms\n",
2912 (double)cuStats.countPModeTasks / cuStats.countPModeMasters,
2913 ELAPSED_MSEC(cuStats.pmodeTime) / cuStats.countPModeTasks);
2914 }
2915
2916 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_INFO, "CU: %%%05.2lf time spent in slicetypeDecide (avg %.3lfms) and prelookahead (avg %.3lfms)\n",
2917 100.0 * lookaheadWorkerTime / totalWorkerTime,
2918 ELAPSED_MSEC(m_lookahead->m_slicetypeDecideElapsedTime) / m_lookahead->m_countSlicetypeDecide,
2919 ELAPSED_MSEC(m_lookahead->m_preLookaheadElapsedTime) / m_lookahead->m_countPreLookahead);
2920
2921 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_INFO, "CU: %%%05.2lf time spent in other tasks\n",
2922 100.0 * unaccounted / totalWorkerTime);
2923
2924 if (intraRDOTotalTime && intraRDOTotalCount)
2925 {
2926 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_INFO, "CU: Intra RDO time per depth %%%05.2lf %%%05.2lf %%%05.2lf %%%05.2lf\n",
2927 100.0 * cuStats.intraRDOElapsedTime[0] / intraRDOTotalTime, // 64
2928 100.0 * cuStats.intraRDOElapsedTime[1] / intraRDOTotalTime, // 32
2929 100.0 * cuStats.intraRDOElapsedTime[2] / intraRDOTotalTime, // 16
2930 100.0 * cuStats.intraRDOElapsedTime[3] / intraRDOTotalTime); // 8
2931 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_INFO, "CU: Intra RDO calls per depth %%%05.2lf %%%05.2lf %%%05.2lf %%%05.2lf\n",
2932 100.0 * cuStats.countIntraRDO[0] / intraRDOTotalCount, // 64
2933 100.0 * cuStats.countIntraRDO[1] / intraRDOTotalCount, // 32
2934 100.0 * cuStats.countIntraRDO[2] / intraRDOTotalCount, // 16
2935 100.0 * cuStats.countIntraRDO[3] / intraRDOTotalCount); // 8
2936 }
2937
2938 if (interRDOTotalTime && interRDOTotalCount)
2939 {
2940 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_INFO, "CU: Inter RDO time per depth %%%05.2lf %%%05.2lf %%%05.2lf %%%05.2lf\n",
2941 100.0 * cuStats.interRDOElapsedTime[0] / interRDOTotalTime, // 64
2942 100.0 * cuStats.interRDOElapsedTime[1] / interRDOTotalTime, // 32
2943 100.0 * cuStats.interRDOElapsedTime[2] / interRDOTotalTime, // 16
2944 100.0 * cuStats.interRDOElapsedTime[3] / interRDOTotalTime); // 8
2945 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_INFO, "CU: Inter RDO calls per depth %%%05.2lf %%%05.2lf %%%05.2lf %%%05.2lf\n",
2946 100.0 * cuStats.countInterRDO[0] / interRDOTotalCount, // 64
2947 100.0 * cuStats.countInterRDO[1] / interRDOTotalCount, // 32
2948 100.0 * cuStats.countInterRDO[2] / interRDOTotalCount, // 16
2949 100.0 * cuStats.countInterRDO[3] / interRDOTotalCount); // 8
2950 }
2951
2952 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_INFO, "CU: " X265_LL " %dX%d CTUs compressed in %.3lf seconds, %.3lf CTUs per worker-second\n",
2953 cuStats.totalCTUs, m_param->maxCUSize, m_param->maxCUSize,
2954 ELAPSED_SEC(totalWorkerTime),
2955 cuStats.totalCTUs / ELAPSED_SEC(totalWorkerTime));
2956
2957 if (m_threadPool)
2958 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_INFO, "CU: %.3lf average worker utilization, %%%05.2lf of theoretical maximum utilization\n",
2959 (double)totalWorkerTime / elapsedEncodeTime,
2960 100.0 * totalWorkerTime / (elapsedEncodeTime * totalWorkerCount));
2961
2962#undef ELAPSED_SEC
2963#undef ELAPSED_MSEC
2964#endif
2965}
2966
2967void Encoder::fetchStats(x265_stats *stats, size_t statsSizeBytes)
2968{
2969 if (statsSizeBytes >= sizeof(stats))
2970 {
2971 stats->globalPsnrY = m_analyzeAll.m_psnrSumY;
2972 stats->globalPsnrU = m_analyzeAll.m_psnrSumU;
2973 stats->globalPsnrV = m_analyzeAll.m_psnrSumV;
2974 stats->encodedPictureCount = m_analyzeAll.m_numPics;
2975 stats->totalWPFrames = m_numLumaWPFrames;
2976 stats->accBits = m_analyzeAll.m_accBits;
2977 stats->elapsedEncodeTime = (double)(x265_mdate() - m_encodeStartTime) / 1000000;
2978 if (stats->encodedPictureCount > 0)
2979 {
2980 stats->globalSsim = m_analyzeAll.m_globalSsim / stats->encodedPictureCount;
2981 stats->globalPsnr = (stats->globalPsnrY * 6 + stats->globalPsnrU + stats->globalPsnrV) / (8 * stats->encodedPictureCount);
2982 stats->elapsedVideoTime = (double)stats->encodedPictureCount * m_param->fpsDenom / m_param->fpsNum;
2983 stats->bitrate = (0.001f * stats->accBits) / stats->elapsedVideoTime;
2984 }
2985 else
2986 {
2987 stats->globalSsim = 0;
2988 stats->globalPsnr = 0;
2989 stats->bitrate = 0;
2990 stats->elapsedVideoTime = 0;
2991 }
2992
2993 double fps = (double)m_param->fpsNum / m_param->fpsDenom;
2994 double scale = fps / 1000;
2995
2996 stats->statsI.numPics = m_analyzeI.m_numPics;
2997 stats->statsI.avgQp = m_analyzeI.m_totalQp / (double)m_analyzeI.m_numPics;
2998 stats->statsI.bitrate = m_analyzeI.m_accBits * scale / (double)m_analyzeI.m_numPics;
2999 stats->statsI.psnrY = m_analyzeI.m_psnrSumY / (double)m_analyzeI.m_numPics;
3000 stats->statsI.psnrU = m_analyzeI.m_psnrSumU / (double)m_analyzeI.m_numPics;
3001 stats->statsI.psnrV = m_analyzeI.m_psnrSumV / (double)m_analyzeI.m_numPics;
3002 stats->statsI.ssim = x265_ssim2dB(m_analyzeI.m_globalSsim / (double)m_analyzeI.m_numPics);
3003
3004 stats->statsP.numPics = m_analyzeP.m_numPics;
3005 stats->statsP.avgQp = m_analyzeP.m_totalQp / (double)m_analyzeP.m_numPics;
3006 stats->statsP.bitrate = m_analyzeP.m_accBits * scale / (double)m_analyzeP.m_numPics;
3007 stats->statsP.psnrY = m_analyzeP.m_psnrSumY / (double)m_analyzeP.m_numPics;
3008 stats->statsP.psnrU = m_analyzeP.m_psnrSumU / (double)m_analyzeP.m_numPics;
3009 stats->statsP.psnrV = m_analyzeP.m_psnrSumV / (double)m_analyzeP.m_numPics;
3010 stats->statsP.ssim = x265_ssim2dB(m_analyzeP.m_globalSsim / (double)m_analyzeP.m_numPics);
3011
3012 stats->statsB.numPics = m_analyzeB.m_numPics;
3013 stats->statsB.avgQp = m_analyzeB.m_totalQp / (double)m_analyzeB.m_numPics;
3014 stats->statsB.bitrate = m_analyzeB.m_accBits * scale / (double)m_analyzeB.m_numPics;
3015 stats->statsB.psnrY = m_analyzeB.m_psnrSumY / (double)m_analyzeB.m_numPics;
3016 stats->statsB.psnrU = m_analyzeB.m_psnrSumU / (double)m_analyzeB.m_numPics;
3017 stats->statsB.psnrV = m_analyzeB.m_psnrSumV / (double)m_analyzeB.m_numPics;
3018 stats->statsB.ssim = x265_ssim2dB(m_analyzeB.m_globalSsim / (double)m_analyzeB.m_numPics);
3019 if (m_param->csvLogLevel >= 2 || m_param->maxCLL || m_param->maxFALL)
3020 {
3021 stats->maxCLL = m_analyzeAll.m_maxCLL;
3022 stats->maxFALL = (uint16_t)(m_analyzeAll.m_maxFALL / m_analyzeAll.m_numPics);
3023 }
3024 }
3025 /* If new statistics are added to x265_stats, we must check here whether the
3026 * structure provided by the user is the new structure or an older one (for
3027 * future safety) */
3028}
3029
3030void Encoder::finishFrameStats(Frame* curFrame, FrameEncoder *curEncoder, x265_frame_stats* frameStats, int inPoc)
3031{
3032 PicYuv* reconPic = curFrame->m_reconPic;
3033 uint64_t bits = curEncoder->m_accessUnitBits;
3034
3035 //===== calculate PSNR =====
3036 int width = reconPic->m_picWidth - m_sps.conformanceWindow.rightOffset;
3037 int height = reconPic->m_picHeight - m_sps.conformanceWindow.bottomOffset;
3038 int size = width * height;
3039
3040 int maxvalY = 255 << (X265_DEPTH - 8);
3041 int maxvalC = 255 << (X265_DEPTH - 8);
3042 double refValueY = (double)maxvalY * maxvalY * size;
3043 double refValueC = (double)maxvalC * maxvalC * size / 4.0;
3044 uint64_t ssdY, ssdU, ssdV;
3045
3046 ssdY = curEncoder->m_SSDY;
3047 ssdU = curEncoder->m_SSDU;
3048 ssdV = curEncoder->m_SSDV;
3049 double psnrY = (ssdY ? 10.0 * log10(refValueY / (double)ssdY) : 99.99);
3050 double psnrU = (ssdU ? 10.0 * log10(refValueC / (double)ssdU) : 99.99);
3051 double psnrV = (ssdV ? 10.0 * log10(refValueC / (double)ssdV) : 99.99);
3052
3053 FrameData& curEncData = *curFrame->m_encData;
3054 Slice* slice = curEncData.m_slice;
3055
3056 //===== add bits, psnr and ssim =====
3057 m_analyzeAll.addBits(bits);
3058 m_analyzeAll.addQP(curEncData.m_avgQpAq);
3059
3060 if (m_param->bEnablePsnr)
3061 m_analyzeAll.addPsnr(psnrY, psnrU, psnrV);
3062
3063 double ssim = 0.0;
3064 if (m_param->bEnableSsim && curEncoder->m_ssimCnt)
3065 {
3066 ssim = curEncoder->m_ssim / curEncoder->m_ssimCnt;
3067 m_analyzeAll.addSsim(ssim);
3068 }
3069 if (slice->isIntra())
3070 {
3071 m_analyzeI.addBits(bits);
3072 m_analyzeI.addQP(curEncData.m_avgQpAq);
3073 if (m_param->bEnablePsnr)
3074 m_analyzeI.addPsnr(psnrY, psnrU, psnrV);
3075 if (m_param->bEnableSsim)
3076 m_analyzeI.addSsim(ssim);
3077 }
3078 else if (slice->isInterP())
3079 {
3080 m_analyzeP.addBits(bits);
3081 m_analyzeP.addQP(curEncData.m_avgQpAq);
3082 if (m_param->bEnablePsnr)
3083 m_analyzeP.addPsnr(psnrY, psnrU, psnrV);
3084 if (m_param->bEnableSsim)
3085 m_analyzeP.addSsim(ssim);
3086 }
3087 else if (slice->isInterB())
3088 {
3089 m_analyzeB.addBits(bits);
3090 m_analyzeB.addQP(curEncData.m_avgQpAq);
3091 if (m_param->bEnablePsnr)
3092 m_analyzeB.addPsnr(psnrY, psnrU, psnrV);
3093 if (m_param->bEnableSsim)
3094 m_analyzeB.addSsim(ssim);
3095 }
3096 if (m_param->csvLogLevel >= 2 || m_param->maxCLL || m_param->maxFALL)
3097 {
3098 m_analyzeAll.m_maxFALL += curFrame->m_fencPic->m_avgLumaLevel;
3099 m_analyzeAll.m_maxCLL = X265_MAX(m_analyzeAll.m_maxCLL, curFrame->m_fencPic->m_maxLumaLevel);
3100 }
3101 char c = (slice->isIntra() ? (curFrame->m_lowres.sliceType == X265_TYPE_IDR ? 'I' : 'i') : slice->isInterP() ? 'P' : 'B');
3102 int poc = slice->m_poc;
3103 if (!IS_REFERENCED(curFrame))
3104 c += 32; // lower case if unreferenced
3105
3106 if (frameStats)
3107 {
3108 const int picOrderCntLSB = slice->m_poc - slice->m_lastIDR;
3109
3110 frameStats->encoderOrder = m_outputCount;
3111 frameStats->sliceType = c;
3112 frameStats->poc = picOrderCntLSB;
3113 frameStats->qp = curEncData.m_avgQpAq;
3114 frameStats->bits = bits;
3115 frameStats->bScenecut = curFrame->m_lowres.bScenecut;
3116 if (m_param->csvLogLevel >= 2)
3117 frameStats->ipCostRatio = curFrame->m_lowres.ipCostRatio;
3118 frameStats->bufferFill = m_rateControl->m_bufferFillActual;
3119 frameStats->bufferFillFinal = m_rateControl->m_bufferFillFinal;
3120 if (m_param->csvLogLevel >= 2)
3121 frameStats->unclippedBufferFillFinal = m_rateControl->m_unclippedBufferFillFinal;
3122 frameStats->frameLatency = inPoc - poc;
3123 if (m_param->rc.rateControlMode == X265_RC_CRF)
3124 frameStats->rateFactor = curEncData.m_rateFactor;
3125 frameStats->psnrY = psnrY;
3126 frameStats->psnrU = psnrU;
3127 frameStats->psnrV = psnrV;
3128 double psnr = (psnrY * 6 + psnrU + psnrV) / 8;
3129 frameStats->psnr = psnr;
3130 frameStats->ssim = ssim;
3131 if (!slice->isIntra())
3132 {
3133 for (int ref = 0; ref < MAX_NUM_REF; ref++)
3134 frameStats->list0POC[ref] = ref < slice->m_numRefIdx[0] ? slice->m_refPOCList[0][ref] - slice->m_lastIDR : -1;
3135
3136 if (!slice->isInterP())
3137 {
3138 for (int ref = 0; ref < MAX_NUM_REF; ref++)
3139 frameStats->list1POC[ref] = ref < slice->m_numRefIdx[1] ? slice->m_refPOCList[1][ref] - slice->m_lastIDR : -1;
3140 }
3141 }
3142#define ELAPSED_MSEC(start, end) (((double)(end) - (start)) / 1000)
3143 if (m_param->csvLogLevel >= 2)
3144 {
3145#if ENABLE_LIBVMAF
3146 frameStats->vmafFrameScore = curFrame->m_fencPic->m_vmafScore;
3147#endif
3148 frameStats->decideWaitTime = ELAPSED_MSEC(0, curEncoder->m_slicetypeWaitTime);
3149 frameStats->row0WaitTime = ELAPSED_MSEC(curEncoder->m_startCompressTime, curEncoder->m_row0WaitTime);
3150 frameStats->wallTime = ELAPSED_MSEC(curEncoder->m_row0WaitTime, curEncoder->m_endCompressTime);
3151 frameStats->refWaitWallTime = ELAPSED_MSEC(curEncoder->m_row0WaitTime, curEncoder->m_allRowsAvailableTime);
3152 frameStats->totalCTUTime = ELAPSED_MSEC(0, curEncoder->m_totalWorkerElapsedTime);
3153 frameStats->stallTime = ELAPSED_MSEC(0, curEncoder->m_totalNoWorkerTime);
3154 frameStats->totalFrameTime = ELAPSED_MSEC(curFrame->m_encodeStartTime, x265_mdate());
3155 if (curEncoder->m_totalActiveWorkerCount)
3156 frameStats->avgWPP = (double)curEncoder->m_totalActiveWorkerCount / curEncoder->m_activeWorkerCountSamples;
3157 else
3158 frameStats->avgWPP = 1;
3159 frameStats->countRowBlocks = curEncoder->m_countRowBlocks;
3160
3161 frameStats->avgChromaDistortion = curFrame->m_encData->m_frameStats.avgChromaDistortion;
3162 frameStats->avgLumaDistortion = curFrame->m_encData->m_frameStats.avgLumaDistortion;
3163 frameStats->avgPsyEnergy = curFrame->m_encData->m_frameStats.avgPsyEnergy;
3164 frameStats->avgResEnergy = curFrame->m_encData->m_frameStats.avgResEnergy;
3165 frameStats->maxLumaLevel = curFrame->m_fencPic->m_maxLumaLevel;
3166 frameStats->minLumaLevel = curFrame->m_fencPic->m_minLumaLevel;
3167 frameStats->avgLumaLevel = curFrame->m_fencPic->m_avgLumaLevel;
3168
3169 frameStats->maxChromaULevel = curFrame->m_fencPic->m_maxChromaULevel;
3170 frameStats->minChromaULevel = curFrame->m_fencPic->m_minChromaULevel;
3171 frameStats->avgChromaULevel = curFrame->m_fencPic->m_avgChromaULevel;
3172
3173 frameStats->maxChromaVLevel = curFrame->m_fencPic->m_maxChromaVLevel;
3174 frameStats->minChromaVLevel = curFrame->m_fencPic->m_minChromaVLevel;
3175 frameStats->avgChromaVLevel = curFrame->m_fencPic->m_avgChromaVLevel;
3176
3177 if (curFrame->m_encData->m_frameStats.totalPu[4] == 0)
3178 frameStats->puStats.percentNxN = 0;
3179 else
3180 frameStats->puStats.percentNxN = (double)(curFrame->m_encData->m_frameStats.cnt4x4 / (double)curFrame->m_encData->m_frameStats.totalPu[4]) * 100;
3181 for (uint32_t depth = 0; depth <= m_param->maxCUDepth; depth++)
3182 {
3183 if (curFrame->m_encData->m_frameStats.totalPu[depth] == 0)
3184 {
3185 frameStats->puStats.percentSkipPu[depth] = 0;
3186 frameStats->puStats.percentIntraPu[depth] = 0;
3187 frameStats->puStats.percentAmpPu[depth] = 0;
3188 for (int i = 0; i < INTER_MODES - 1; i++)
3189 {
3190 frameStats->puStats.percentInterPu[depth][i] = 0;
3191 frameStats->puStats.percentMergePu[depth][i] = 0;
3192 }
3193 }
3194 else
3195 {
3196 frameStats->puStats.percentSkipPu[depth] = (double)(curFrame->m_encData->m_frameStats.cntSkipPu[depth] / (double)curFrame->m_encData->m_frameStats.totalPu[depth]) * 100;
3197 frameStats->puStats.percentIntraPu[depth] = (double)(curFrame->m_encData->m_frameStats.cntIntraPu[depth] / (double)curFrame->m_encData->m_frameStats.totalPu[depth]) * 100;
3198 frameStats->puStats.percentAmpPu[depth] = (double)(curFrame->m_encData->m_frameStats.cntAmp[depth] / (double)curFrame->m_encData->m_frameStats.totalPu[depth]) * 100;
3199 for (int i = 0; i < INTER_MODES - 1; i++)
3200 {
3201 frameStats->puStats.percentInterPu[depth][i] = (double)(curFrame->m_encData->m_frameStats.cntInterPu[depth][i] / (double)curFrame->m_encData->m_frameStats.totalPu[depth]) * 100;
3202 frameStats->puStats.percentMergePu[depth][i] = (double)(curFrame->m_encData->m_frameStats.cntMergePu[depth][i] / (double)curFrame->m_encData->m_frameStats.totalPu[depth]) * 100;
3203 }
3204 }
3205 }
3206 }
3207
3208 if (m_param->csvLogLevel >= 1)
3209 {
3210 frameStats->cuStats.percentIntraNxN = curFrame->m_encData->m_frameStats.percentIntraNxN;
3211
3212 for (uint32_t depth = 0; depth <= m_param->maxCUDepth; depth++)
3213 {
3214 frameStats->cuStats.percentSkipCu[depth] = curFrame->m_encData->m_frameStats.percentSkipCu[depth];
3215 frameStats->cuStats.percentMergeCu[depth] = curFrame->m_encData->m_frameStats.percentMergeCu[depth];

3217 frameStats->cuStats.percentInterDistribution[depth][1] = curFrame->m_encData->m_frameStats.percentInterDistribution[depth][1];

3219 for (int n = 0; n < INTRA_MODES; n++)
3220 frameStats->cuStats.percentIntraDistribution[depth][n] = curFrame->m_encData->m_frameStats.percentIntraDistribution[depth][n];

3231void Encoder::initRefIdx()
3232{
3233 int j = 0;
3234
3235 for (j = 0; j < MAX_NUM_REF_IDX; j++)
3236 {
3237 m_refIdxLastGOP.numRefIdxl0[j] = 0;
3238 m_refIdxLastGOP.numRefIdxl1[j] = 0;
3239 }
3240
3241 return;
3242}
3243
3244void Encoder::analyseRefIdx(int *numRefIdx)
3245{
3246 int i_l0 = 0;
3247 int i_l1 = 0;
3248
3249 i_l0 = numRefIdx[0];
3250 i_l1 = numRefIdx[1];
3251
3252 if ((0 < i_l0) && (MAX_NUM_REF_IDX > i_l0))
3253 m_refIdxLastGOP.numRefIdxl0[i_l0]++;
3254 if ((0 < i_l1) && (MAX_NUM_REF_IDX > i_l1))
3255 m_refIdxLastGOP.numRefIdxl1[i_l1]++;
3256
3257 return;
3258}
3259
3260void Encoder::updateRefIdx()
3261{
3262 int i_max_l0 = 0;
3263 int i_max_l1 = 0;
3264 int j = 0;
3265
3266 i_max_l0 = 0;
3267 i_max_l1 = 0;
3268 m_refIdxLastGOP.numRefIdxDefault[0] = 1;
3269 m_refIdxLastGOP.numRefIdxDefault[1] = 1;
3270 for (j = 0; j < MAX_NUM_REF_IDX; j++)
3271 {
3272 if (i_max_l0 < m_refIdxLastGOP.numRefIdxl0[j])
3273 {
3274 i_max_l0 = m_refIdxLastGOP.numRefIdxl0[j];
3275 m_refIdxLastGOP.numRefIdxDefault[0] = j;
3276 }
3277 if (i_max_l1 < m_refIdxLastGOP.numRefIdxl1[j])
3278 {
3279 i_max_l1 = m_refIdxLastGOP.numRefIdxl1[j];
3280 m_refIdxLastGOP.numRefIdxDefault[1] = j;
3281 }
3282 }
3283
3284 m_pps.numRefIdxDefault[0] = m_refIdxLastGOP.numRefIdxDefault[0];
3285 m_pps.numRefIdxDefault[1] = m_refIdxLastGOP.numRefIdxDefault[1];
3286 initRefIdx();
3287
3288 return;
3289}
3290
3291void Encoder::getStreamHeaders(NALList& list, Entropy& sbacCoder, Bitstream& bs)
3292{
3293 sbacCoder.setBitstream(&bs);
3294
3295 if (m_param->dolbyProfile && !m_param->bRepeatHeaders)
3296 {
3297 bs.resetBits();
3298 bs.write(0x10, 8);
3299 list.serialize(NAL_UNIT_ACCESS_UNIT_DELIMITER, bs);
3300 }
3301
3302 /* headers for start of bitstream */
3303 bs.resetBits();
3304 sbacCoder.codeVPS(m_vps);
3305 bs.writeByteAlignment();
3306 list.serialize(NAL_UNIT_VPS, bs);
3307
3308 bs.resetBits();
3309 sbacCoder.codeSPS(m_sps, m_scalingList, m_vps.ptl);
3310 bs.writeByteAlignment();
3311 list.serialize(NAL_UNIT_SPS, bs);
3312
3313 bs.resetBits();
3314 sbacCoder.codePPS(m_pps, (m_param->maxSlices <= 1), m_iPPSQpMinus26);
3315 bs.writeByteAlignment();
3316 list.serialize(NAL_UNIT_PPS, bs);
3317
3318 if (m_param->bSingleSeiNal)
3319 bs.resetBits();
3320
3321 if (m_param->bEmitHDR10SEI)
3322 {
3323 if (m_param->bEmitCLL)
3324 {
3325 SEIContentLightLevel cllsei;
3326 cllsei.max_content_light_level = m_param->maxCLL;
3327 cllsei.max_pic_average_light_level = m_param->maxFALL;
3328 cllsei.writeSEImessages(bs, m_sps, NAL_UNIT_PREFIX_SEI, list, m_param->bSingleSeiNal);
3329 }
3330
3331 if (m_param->masteringDisplayColorVolume)
3332 {
3333 SEIMasteringDisplayColorVolume mdsei;
3334 if (mdsei.parse(m_param->masteringDisplayColorVolume))
3335 mdsei.writeSEImessages(bs, m_sps, NAL_UNIT_PREFIX_SEI, list, m_param->bSingleSeiNal);
3336 else
3337 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_WARNING, "unable to parse mastering display color volume info\n");
3338 }
3339 }
3340
3341 if (m_param->bEmitInfoSEI)
3342 {
3343 char *opts = x265_param2string(m_param, m_sps.conformanceWindow.rightOffset, m_sps.conformanceWindow.bottomOffset);
3344 if (opts)
3345 {
3346 char *buffer = X265_MALLOC(char, strlen(opts) + strlen(PFX(version_str)) +
3347 strlen(PFX(build_info_str)) + 200);
3348 if (buffer)
3349 {
3350 sprintf(buffer, "x265 (build %d) - %s:%s - H.265/HEVC codec - "
3351 "Copyright 2013-2018 (c) Multicoreware, Inc - "
3352 "http://x265.org - options: %s",
3353 X265_BUILD, PFX(version_str), PFX(build_info_str), opts);
3354
3355 SEIuserDataUnregistered idsei;
3356 idsei.m_userData = (uint8_t*)buffer;
3357 idsei.setSize((uint32_t)strlen(buffer));
3358 idsei.writeSEImessages(bs, m_sps, NAL_UNIT_PREFIX_SEI, list, m_param->bSingleSeiNal);
3359
3360 X265_FREE(buffer);
3361 }
3362
3363 X265_FREE(opts);
3364 }
3365 }
3366
3367 if ((m_param->bEmitHRDSEI || !!m_param->interlaceMode))
3368 {
3369 /* Picture Timing and Buffering Period SEI require the SPS to be "activated" */
3370 SEIActiveParameterSets sei;
3371 sei.m_selfContainedCvsFlag = true;
3372 sei.m_noParamSetUpdateFlag = true;
3373 sei.writeSEImessages(bs, m_sps, NAL_UNIT_PREFIX_SEI, list, m_param->bSingleSeiNal);
3374 }
3375}
3376
3377void Encoder::getEndNalUnits(NALList& list, Bitstream& bs)
3378{
3379 NALList nalList;
3380 bs.resetBits();
3381
3382 if (m_param->bEnableEndOfSequence)
3383 nalList.serialize(NAL_UNIT_EOS, bs);
3384 if (m_param->bEnableEndOfBitstream)
3385 nalList.serialize(NAL_UNIT_EOB, bs);
3386
3387 list.takeContents(nalList);
3388}

3477
3478void Encoder::initPPS(PPS *pps)
3479{
3480 bool bIsVbv = m_param->rc.vbvBufferSize > 0 && m_param->rc.vbvMaxBitrate > 0;
3481 bool bEnableDistOffset = m_param->analysisMultiPassDistortion && m_param->rc.bStatRead;
3482
3483 if (!m_param->bLossless && (m_param->rc.aqMode || bIsVbv || m_param->bAQMotion))
3484 {
3485 pps->bUseDQP = true;
3486 pps->maxCuDQPDepth = g_log2Size[m_param->maxCUSize] - g_log2Size[m_param->rc.qgSize];
3487 X265_CHECK(pps->maxCuDQPDepth <= 3, "max CU DQP depth cannot be greater than 3\n");
3488 }
3489 else if (!m_param->bLossless && bEnableDistOffset)
3490 {
3491 pps->bUseDQP = true;
3492 pps->maxCuDQPDepth = 0;
3493 }
3494 else
3495 {
3496 pps->bUseDQP = false;
3497 pps->maxCuDQPDepth = 0;
3498 }
3499
3500 pps->chromaQpOffset[0] = m_param->cbQpOffset;
3501 pps->chromaQpOffset[1] = m_param->crQpOffset;
3502 pps->pps_slice_chroma_qp_offsets_present_flag = m_param->bHDR10Opt;
3503
3504 pps->bConstrainedIntraPred = m_param->bEnableConstrainedIntra;
3505 pps->bUseWeightPred = m_param->bEnableWeightedPred;
3506 pps->bUseWeightedBiPred = m_param->bEnableWeightedBiPred;
3507 pps->bTransquantBypassEnabled = m_param->bCULossless || m_param->bLossless;
3508 pps->bTransformSkipEnabled = m_param->bEnableTransformSkip;
3509 pps->bSignHideEnabled = m_param->bEnableSignHiding;
3510
3511 pps->bDeblockingFilterControlPresent = !m_param->bEnableLoopFilter || m_param->deblockingFilterBetaOffset || m_param->deblockingFilterTCOffset;
3512 pps->bPicDisableDeblockingFilter = !m_param->bEnableLoopFilter;
3513 pps->deblockingFilterBetaOffsetDiv2 = m_param->deblockingFilterBetaOffset;
3514 pps->deblockingFilterTcOffsetDiv2 = m_param->deblockingFilterTCOffset;
3515
3516 pps->bEntropyCodingSyncEnabled = m_param->bEnableWavefront;
3517
3518 pps->numRefIdxDefault[0] = 1;
3519 pps->numRefIdxDefault[1] = 1;
3520}
3521
3522void Encoder::configureZone(x265_param *p, x265_param *zone)
3523{
3524 if (m_param->bResetZoneConfig)
3525 {
3526 p->maxNumReferences = zone->maxNumReferences;
3527 p->bEnableFastIntra = zone->bEnableFastIntra;
3528 p->bEnableEarlySkip = zone->bEnableEarlySkip;
3529 p->recursionSkipMode = zone->recursionSkipMode;
3530 p->searchMethod = zone->searchMethod;
3531 p->searchRange = zone->searchRange;
3532 p->subpelRefine = zone->subpelRefine;
3533 p->rdoqLevel = zone->rdoqLevel;
3534 p->rdLevel = zone->rdLevel;
3535 p->bEnableRectInter = zone->bEnableRectInter;
3536 p->maxNumMergeCand = zone->maxNumMergeCand;
3537 p->bIntraInBFrames = zone->bIntraInBFrames;
3538 if (zone->scalingLists)
3539 p->scalingLists = strdup(zone->scalingLists);
3540
3541 p->rc.aqMode = zone->rc.aqMode;
3542 p->rc.aqStrength = zone->rc.aqStrength;
3543 p->noiseReductionInter = zone->noiseReductionInter;
3544 p->noiseReductionIntra = zone->noiseReductionIntra;
3545
3546 p->limitModes = zone->limitModes;
3547 p->bEnableSplitRdSkip = zone->bEnableSplitRdSkip;
3548 p->bCULossless = zone->bCULossless;
3549 p->bEnableRdRefine = zone->bEnableRdRefine;
3550 p->limitTU = zone->limitTU;
3551 p->bEnableTSkipFast = zone->bEnableTSkipFast;
3552 p->rdPenalty = zone->rdPenalty;
3553 p->dynamicRd = zone->dynamicRd;
3554 p->bEnableTransformSkip = zone->bEnableTransformSkip;
3555 p->bEnableAMP = zone->bEnableAMP;
3556
3557 if (m_param->rc.rateControlMode == X265_RC_ABR)
3558 p->rc.bitrate = zone->rc.bitrate;
3559 if (m_param->rc.rateControlMode == X265_RC_CRF)
3560 p->rc.rfConstant = zone->rc.rfConstant;
3561 if (m_param->rc.rateControlMode == X265_RC_CQP)
3562 {
3563 p->rc.qp = zone->rc.qp;
3564 p->rc.aqMode = X265_AQ_NONE;
3565 p->rc.hevcAq = 0;
3566 }
3567 p->radl = zone->radl;
3568 }
3569 memcpy(zone, p, sizeof(x265_param));
3570}
3571
3572void Encoder::configureDolbyVisionParams(x265_param* p)
3573{
3574 uint32_t doviProfile = 0;
3575
3576 while (dovi[doviProfile].doviProfileId != p->dolbyProfile && doviProfile + 1 < sizeof(dovi) / sizeof(dovi[0]))
3577 doviProfile++;
3578
3579 p->bEmitHRDSEI = dovi[doviProfile].bEmitHRDSEI;
3580 p->vui.bEnableVideoSignalTypePresentFlag = dovi[doviProfile].bEnableVideoSignalTypePresentFlag;
3581 p->vui.bEnableColorDescriptionPresentFlag = dovi[doviProfile].bEnableColorDescriptionPresentFlag;
3582 p->bEnableAccessUnitDelimiters = dovi[doviProfile].bEnableAccessUnitDelimiters;
3583 p->bAnnexB = dovi[doviProfile].bAnnexB;
3584 p->vui.videoFormat = dovi[doviProfile].videoFormat;
3585 p->vui.bEnableVideoFullRangeFlag = dovi[doviProfile].bEnableVideoFullRangeFlag;
3586 p->vui.transferCharacteristics = dovi[doviProfile].transferCharacteristics;
3587 p->vui.colorPrimaries = dovi[doviProfile].colorPrimaries;
3588 p->vui.matrixCoeffs = dovi[doviProfile].matrixCoeffs;
3589
3590 if (dovi[doviProfile].doviProfileId == 81)
3591 p->bEmitHDR10SEI = p->bEmitCLL = 1;
3592
3593 if (dovi[doviProfile].doviProfileId == 50)
3594 p->crQpOffset = 3;
3595}
3596
3597void Encoder::configureVideoSignalTypePreset(x265_param* p)
3598{
3599 char systemId[20] = {};
3600 char colorVolume[20] = {};
3601 sscanf(p->videoSignalTypePreset, "%[^:]:%s", systemId, colorVolume);
3602 uint32_t sysId = 0;
3603 while (strcmp(vstPresets[sysId].systemId, systemId))
3604 {
3605 if (sysId + 1 == sizeof(vstPresets) / sizeof(vstPresets[0]))
3606 {
3607 x265_log(NULL, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Incorrect system-id, aborting\n");
3608 m_aborted = true;
3609 break;
3610 }
3611 sysId++;
3612 }
3613
3614 p->vui.bEnableVideoSignalTypePresentFlag = vstPresets[sysId].bEnableVideoSignalTypePresentFlag;
3615 p->vui.bEnableColorDescriptionPresentFlag = vstPresets[sysId].bEnableColorDescriptionPresentFlag;
3616 p->vui.bEnableChromaLocInfoPresentFlag = vstPresets[sysId].bEnableChromaLocInfoPresentFlag;
3617 p->vui.colorPrimaries = vstPresets[sysId].colorPrimaries;
3618 p->vui.transferCharacteristics = vstPresets[sysId].transferCharacteristics;
3619 p->vui.matrixCoeffs = vstPresets[sysId].matrixCoeffs;
3620 p->vui.bEnableVideoFullRangeFlag = vstPresets[sysId].bEnableVideoFullRangeFlag;
3621 p->vui.chromaSampleLocTypeTopField = vstPresets[sysId].chromaSampleLocTypeTopField;
3622 p->vui.chromaSampleLocTypeBottomField = vstPresets[sysId].chromaSampleLocTypeBottomField;
3623
3624 if (colorVolume[0] != '\0')
3625 {
3626 if (!strcmp(systemId, "BT2100_PQ_YCC") || !strcmp(systemId, "BT2100_PQ_ICTCP") || !strcmp(systemId, "BT2100_PQ_RGB"))
3627 {
3628 p->bEmitHDR10SEI = 1;
3629 if (!strcmp(colorVolume, "P3D65x1000n0005"))
3630 {
3631 p->masteringDisplayColorVolume = strdup("G(13250,34500)B(7500,3000)R(34000,16000)WP(15635,16450)L(10000000,5)");
3632 }
3633 else if (!strcmp(colorVolume, "P3D65x4000n005"))
3634 {
3635 p->masteringDisplayColorVolume = strdup("G(13250,34500)B(7500,3000)R(34000,16000)WP(15635,16450)L(40000000,50)");
3636 }
3637 else if (!strcmp(colorVolume, "BT2100x108n0005"))
3638 {
3639 p->masteringDisplayColorVolume = strdup("G(8500,39850)B(6550,2300)R(34000,146000)WP(15635,16450)L(10000000,1)");
3640 }
3641 else
3642 {
3643 x265_log(NULL, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Incorrect color-volume, aborting\n");
3644 m_aborted = true;
3645 }
3646 }
3647 else
3648 {
3649 x265_log(NULL, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Color-volume is not supported with the given system-id, aborting\n");
3650 m_aborted = true;
3651 }
3652 }
3653
3654}
3655
3656void Encoder::configure(x265_param *p)
3657{
3658 this->m_param = p;
3659 if (p->bAnalysisType == AVC_INFO)
3660 this->m_externalFlush = true;
3661 else
3662 this->m_externalFlush = false;
3663
3664 if (p->bAnalysisType == AVC_INFO && (p->limitTU == 3 || p->limitTU == 4))
3665 {
3666 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "limit TU = 3 or 4 with MVType AVCINFO produces inconsistent output\n");
3667 }
3668
3669 if (p->bAnalysisType == AVC_INFO && p->minCUSize != 8)
3670 {
3671 p->minCUSize = 8;
3672 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Setting minCuSize = 8, AVCINFO expects 8x8 blocks\n");
3673 }
3674
3675 if (p->keyframeMax < 0)
3676 {
3677 /* A negative max GOP size indicates the user wants only one I frame at
3678 * the start of the stream. Set an infinite GOP distance and disable
3679 * adaptive I frame placement */
3680 p->keyframeMax = INT_MAX;
3681 p->scenecutThreshold = 0;
3682 p->bHistBasedSceneCut = 0;
3683 }
3684 else if (p->keyframeMax <= 1)
3685 {
3686 p->keyframeMax = 1;
3687
3688 // disable lookahead for all-intra encodes
3689 p->bFrameAdaptive = 0;
3690 p->bframes = 0;
3691 p->bOpenGOP = 0;
3692 p->bRepeatHeaders = 1;
3693 p->lookaheadDepth = 0;
3694 p->bframes = 0;
3695 p->scenecutThreshold = 0;
3696 p->bHistBasedSceneCut = 0;
3697 p->bFrameAdaptive = 0;
3698 p->rc.cuTree = 0;
3699 p->bEnableWeightedPred = 0;
3700 p->bEnableWeightedBiPred = 0;
3701 p->bIntraRefresh = 0;
3702
3703 /* SPSs shall have sps_max_dec_pic_buffering_minus1[ sps_max_sub_layers_minus1 ] equal to 0 only */
3704 p->maxNumReferences = 1;
3705 }
3706 if (!p->keyframeMin)
3707 {
3708 double fps = (double)p->fpsNum / p->fpsDenom;
3709 p->keyframeMin = X265_MIN((int)fps, p->keyframeMax / 10);
3710 }
3711 p->keyframeMin = X265_MAX(1, p->keyframeMin);
3712
3713 if (!p->bframes)
3714 p->bBPyramid = 0;
3715 if (!p->rdoqLevel)
3716 p->psyRdoq = 0;
3717
3718 /* Disable features which are not supported by the current RD level */
3719 if (p->rdLevel < 3)
3720 {
3721 if (p->bCULossless) /* impossible */
3722 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "--cu-lossless disabled, requires --rdlevel 3 or higher\n");
3723 if (p->bEnableTransformSkip) /* impossible */
3724 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "--tskip disabled, requires --rdlevel 3 or higher\n");
3725 p->bCULossless = p->bEnableTransformSkip = 0;
3726 }
3727 if (p->rdLevel < 2)
3728 {
3729 if (p->bDistributeModeAnalysis) /* not useful */
3730 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "--pmode disabled, requires --rdlevel 2 or higher\n");
3731 p->bDistributeModeAnalysis = 0;
3732
3733 p->psyRd = 0; /* impossible */
3734
3735 if (p->bEnableRectInter) /* broken, not very useful */
3736 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "--rect disabled, requires --rdlevel 2 or higher\n");
3737 p->bEnableRectInter = 0;
3738 }
3739
3740 if (!p->bEnableRectInter) /* not useful */
3741 p->bEnableAMP = false;
3742
3743 /* In 444, chroma gets twice as much resolution, so halve quality when psy-rd is enabled */
3744 if (p->internalCsp == X265_CSP_I444 && p->psyRd)
3745 {
3746 if (!p->cbQpOffset && !p->crQpOffset)
3747 {
3748 p->cbQpOffset = MAX_CHROMA_QP_OFFSET / 2;
3749 p->crQpOffset = MAX_CHROMA_QP_OFFSET / 2;
3750 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "halving the quality when psy-rd is enabled for 444 input."
3751 " Setting cbQpOffset = %d and crQpOffset = %d\n", p->cbQpOffset, p->crQpOffset);
3752 }
3753 }
3754
3755 if (p->bLossless)
3756 {
3757 p->rc.rateControlMode = X265_RC_CQP;
3758 p->rc.qp = 4; // An oddity, QP=4 is more lossless than QP=0 and gives better lambdas
3759 p->bEnableSsim = 0;
3760 p->bEnablePsnr = 0;
3761 }
3762
3763 if (p->rc.rateControlMode == X265_RC_CQP)
3764 {
3765 p->rc.aqMode = X265_AQ_NONE;
3766 p->rc.hevcAq = 0;
3767 p->rc.bitrate = 0;
3768 p->rc.cuTree = 0;
3769 p->rc.aqStrength = 0;
3770 }
3771
3772 if (p->rc.aqMode == 0 && p->rc.cuTree)
3773 {
3774 p->rc.aqMode = X265_AQ_VARIANCE;
3775 p->rc.aqStrength = 0.0;
3776 }
3777
3778 if (p->lookaheadDepth == 0 && p->rc.cuTree && !p->rc.bStatRead)
3779 {
3780 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "cuTree disabled, requires lookahead to be enabled\n");
3781 p->rc.cuTree = 0;
3782 }
3783
3784 if (p->maxTUSize > p->maxCUSize)
3785 {
3786 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Max TU size should be less than or equal to max CU size, setting max TU size = %d\n", p->maxCUSize);
3787 p->maxTUSize = p->maxCUSize;
3788 }
3789 if (p->rc.aqStrength == 0 && p->rc.cuTree == 0)
3790 {
3791 p->rc.aqMode = X265_AQ_NONE;
3792 p->rc.hevcAq = 0;
3793 }
3794 if (p->rc.aqMode == X265_AQ_NONE && p->rc.cuTree == 0)
3795 p->rc.aqStrength = 0;
3796 if (p->rc.hevcAq && p->rc.aqMode)
3797 {
3798 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "hevc-aq enabled, disabling other aq-modes\n");
3799 }
3800
3801 if (p->totalFrames && p->totalFrames <= 2 * ((float)p->fpsNum) / p->fpsDenom && p->rc.bStrictCbr)
3802 p->lookaheadDepth = p->totalFrames;
3803 if (p->bIntraRefresh)
3804 {
3805 int numCuInWidth = (m_param->sourceWidth + m_param->maxCUSize - 1) / m_param->maxCUSize;
3806 if (p->maxNumReferences > 1)
3807 {
3808 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Max References > 1 + intra-refresh is not supported , setting max num references = 1\n");
3809 p->maxNumReferences = 1;
3810 }
3811
3812 if (p->bBPyramid && p->bframes)
3813 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "B pyramid cannot be enabled when max references is 1, Disabling B pyramid\n");
3814 p->bBPyramid = 0;
3815
3816
3817 if (p->bOpenGOP)
3818 {
3819 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Open Gop disabled, Intra Refresh is not compatible with openGop\n");
3820 p->bOpenGOP = 0;
3821 }
3822
3823 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Scenecut is disabled when Intra Refresh is enabled\n");
3824
3825 if (((float)numCuInWidth - 1) / m_param->keyframeMax > 1)
3826 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Keyint value is very low.It leads to frequent intra refreshes, can be almost every frame."
3827 "Prefered use case would be high keyint value or an API call to refresh when necessary\n");
3828
3829 }
3830
3831 if (p->selectiveSAO && !p->bEnableSAO)
3832 {
3833 p->bEnableSAO = 1;
3834 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "SAO turned ON when selective-sao is ON\n");
3835 }
3836
3837 if (!p->selectiveSAO && p->bEnableSAO)
3838 p->selectiveSAO = 4;
3839
3840 if (p->interlaceMode)
3841 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Support for interlaced video is experimental\n");
3842
3843 if (p->rc.rfConstantMin > p->rc.rfConstant)
3844 {
3845 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_WARNING, "CRF min must be less than CRF\n");
3846 p->rc.rfConstantMin = 0;
3847 }
3848
3849 if (p->analysisSaveReuseLevel && !p->analysisSave)
3850 {
3851 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "analysis-save-reuse-level can be set only when analysis-save is enabled."
3852 " Resetting analysis-save-reuse-level to 0.\n");
3853 p->analysisSaveReuseLevel = 0;
3854 }
3855
3856 if (p->analysisLoadReuseLevel && !p->analysisLoad)
3857 {
3858 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "analysis-load-reuse-level can be set only when analysis-load is enabled."
3859 " Resetting analysis-load-reuse-level to 0.\n");
3860 p->analysisLoadReuseLevel = 0;
3861 }
3862
3863 if (p->analysisSave && !p->analysisSaveReuseLevel)
3864 p->analysisSaveReuseLevel = 5;
3865
3866 if (p->analysisLoad && !p->analysisLoadReuseLevel)
3867 p->analysisLoadReuseLevel = 5;
3868
3869 if ((p->analysisLoad || p->analysisSave) && (p->bDistributeModeAnalysis || p->bDistributeMotionEstimation))
3870 {
3871 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Analysis load/save options incompatible with pmode/pme, Disabling pmode/pme\n");
3872 p->bDistributeMotionEstimation = p->bDistributeModeAnalysis = 0;
3873 }
3874
3875 if ((p->analysisLoad || p->analysisSave) && (p->analysisMultiPassRefine || p->analysisMultiPassDistortion))
3876 {
3877 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Cannot use Analysis load/save option and multi-pass-opt-analysis/multi-pass-opt-distortion together,"
3878 "Disabling Analysis load/save and multi-pass-opt-analysis/multi-pass-opt-distortion\n");
3879 p->analysisSave = p->analysisLoad = NULL;
3880 p->analysisMultiPassRefine = p->analysisMultiPassDistortion = 0;
3881 }
3882 if (p->scaleFactor)
3883 {
3884 if (p->scaleFactor == 1)
3885 {
3886 p->scaleFactor = 0;
3887 }
3888 else if ((p->analysisSaveReuseLevel > 6 && p->analysisSaveReuseLevel != 10) || (p->analysisLoadReuseLevel > 6 && p->analysisLoadReuseLevel != 10))
3889 {
3890 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Input scaling works with analysis-save/load and analysis-save/load-reuse-level 1-6 and 10. Disabling scale-factor.\n");
3891 p->scaleFactor = 0;
3892 }
3893 }
3894
3895 if (p->intraRefine && p->analysisLoadReuseLevel && p->analysisLoadReuseLevel < 10)
3896 {
3897 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Intra refinement requires analysis load, analysis-load-reuse-level 10. Disabling intra refine.\n");
3898 p->intraRefine = 0;
3899 }
3900
3901 if (p->interRefine && p->analysisLoadReuseLevel && p->analysisLoadReuseLevel < 10)
3902 {
3903 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Inter refinement requires analysis load, analysis-load-reuse-level 10. Disabling inter refine.\n");
3904 p->interRefine = 0;
3905 }
3906
3907 if (p->bDynamicRefine && p->analysisLoadReuseLevel && p->analysisLoadReuseLevel < 10)
3908 {
3909 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Dynamic refinement requires analysis load, analysis-load-reuse-level 10. Disabling dynamic refine.\n");
3910 p->bDynamicRefine = 0;
3911
3912 if (p->interRefine)
3913 {
3914 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Inter refine cannot be used with dynamic refine. Disabling refine-inter.\n");
3915 p->interRefine = 0;
3916 }
3917 }
3918 if (p->scaleFactor && !p->interRefine && !p->bDynamicRefine && p->analysisLoadReuseLevel == 10)
3919 {
3920 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Inter refinement 0 is not supported with scaling and analysis-reuse-level=10. Enabling refine-inter 1.\n");
3921 p->interRefine = 1;
3922 }
3923
3924 if (!(p->bAnalysisType == HEVC_INFO) && p->limitTU && (p->interRefine || p->bDynamicRefine))
3925 {
3926 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Inter refinement does not support limitTU. Disabling limitTU.\n");
3927 p->limitTU = 0;
3928 }
3929
3930 if (p->ctuDistortionRefine == CTU_DISTORTION_INTERNAL)
3931 {
3932 if (!p->analysisLoad && !p->analysisSave)
3933 {
3934 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "refine-ctu-distortion 1 requires analysis save/load. Disabling refine-ctu-distortion\n");
3935 p->ctuDistortionRefine = 0;
3936 }
3937 if (p->scaleFactor && p->analysisLoad)
3938 {
3939 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "refine-ctu-distortion 1 cannot be enabled along with multi resolution analysis refinement. Disabling refine-ctu-distortion\n");
3940 p->ctuDistortionRefine = 0;
3941 }
3942 }
3943
3944 if ((p->analysisMultiPassRefine || p->analysisMultiPassDistortion) && (p->bDistributeModeAnalysis || p->bDistributeMotionEstimation))
3945 {
3946 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "multi-pass-opt-analysis/multi-pass-opt-distortion incompatible with pmode/pme, Disabling pmode/pme\n");
3947 p->bDistributeMotionEstimation = p->bDistributeModeAnalysis = 0;
3948 }
3949
3950 if (p->bDistributeModeAnalysis && (p->limitReferences >> 1) && 1)
3951 {
3952 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Limit reference options 2 and 3 are not supported with pmode. Disabling limit reference\n");
3953 p->limitReferences = 0;
3954 }
3955
3956 if (p->bEnableTemporalSubLayers && !p->bframes)
3957 {
3958 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "B frames not enabled, temporal sublayer disabled\n");
3959 p->bEnableTemporalSubLayers = 0;
3960 }
3961
3962 m_bframeDelay = p->bframes ? (p->bBPyramid ? 2 : 1) : 0;
3963
3964 p->bFrameBias = X265_MIN(X265_MAX(-90, p->bFrameBias), 100);
3965 p->scenecutBias = (double)(p->scenecutBias / 100);
3966
3967 if (p->logLevel < X265_LOG_INFO)
3968 {
3969 /* don't measure these metrics if they will not be reported */
3970 p->bEnablePsnr = 0;
3971 p->bEnableSsim = 0;
3972 }
3973 /* Warn users trying to measure PSNR/SSIM with psy opts on. */
3974 if (p->bEnablePsnr || p->bEnableSsim)
3975 {
3976 const char *s = NULL;
3977
3978 if (p->psyRd || p->psyRdoq)
3979 {
3980 s = p->bEnablePsnr ? "psnr" : "ssim";
3981 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "--%s used with psy on: results will be invalid!\n", s);
3982 }
3983 else if (!p->rc.aqMode && p->bEnableSsim)
3984 {
3985 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "--ssim used with AQ off: results will be invalid!\n");
3986 s = "ssim";
3987 }
3988 else if (p->rc.aqStrength > 0 && p->bEnablePsnr)
3989 {
3990 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "--psnr used with AQ on: results will be invalid!\n");
3991 s = "psnr";
3992 }
3993 if (s)
3994 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "--tune %s should be used if attempting to benchmark %s!\n", s, s);
3995 }
3996 if (p->searchMethod == X265_SEA && (p->bDistributeMotionEstimation || p->bDistributeModeAnalysis))
3997 {
3998 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Disabling pme and pmode: --pme and --pmode cannot be used with SEA motion search!\n");
3999 p->bDistributeMotionEstimation = 0;
4000 p->bDistributeModeAnalysis = 0;
4001 }
4002
4003 if (!p->rc.bStatWrite && !p->rc.bStatRead && (p->analysisMultiPassRefine || p->analysisMultiPassDistortion))
4004 {
4005 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "analysis-multi-pass/distortion is enabled only when rc multi pass is enabled. Disabling multi-pass-opt-analysis and multi-pass-opt-distortion\n");
4006 p->analysisMultiPassRefine = 0;
4007 p->analysisMultiPassDistortion = 0;
4008 }
4009 if (p->analysisMultiPassRefine && p->rc.bStatWrite && p->rc.bStatRead)
4010 {
4011 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "--multi-pass-opt-analysis doesn't support refining analysis through multiple-passes; it only reuses analysis from the second-to-last pass to the last pass.Disabling reading\n");
4012 p->rc.bStatRead = 0;
4013 }
4014
4015 /* some options make no sense if others are disabled */
4016 p->bSaoNonDeblocked &= p->bEnableSAO;
4017 p->bEnableTSkipFast &= p->bEnableTransformSkip;
4018 p->bLimitSAO &= p->bEnableSAO;
4019
4020 if (m_param->bUseAnalysisFile && m_param->analysisLoad && (p->confWinRightOffset || p->confWinBottomOffset))
4021 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "It is recommended not to set conformance window offset in file based analysis-load."
4022 " Offsets are shared in the analysis file already.\n");
4023 /* initialize the conformance window */
4024 m_conformanceWindow.bEnabled = false;
4025 m_conformanceWindow.rightOffset = 0;
4026 m_conformanceWindow.topOffset = 0;
4027 m_conformanceWindow.bottomOffset = 0;
4028 m_conformanceWindow.leftOffset = 0;
4029
4030 uint32_t padsize = 0;
4031 if (m_param->analysisLoad && m_param->bUseAnalysisFile)
4032 {
4033 m_analysisFileIn = x265_fopen(m_param->analysisLoad, "rb");
4034 if (!m_analysisFileIn)
4035 {
4036 x265_log_file(NULL, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Analysis load: failed to open file %s\n", m_param->analysisLoad);
4037 m_aborted = true;
4038 }
4039 else
4040 {
4041 int rightOffset, bottomOffset;
4042 if (fread(&rightOffset, sizeof(int), 1, m_analysisFileIn) != 1)
4043 {
4044 x265_log(NULL, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Error reading analysis data. Conformance window right offset missing\n");
4045 m_aborted = true;
4046 }
4047 else if (rightOffset && p->analysisLoadReuseLevel > 1)
4048 {
4049 int scaleFactor = p->scaleFactor < 2 ? 1 : p->scaleFactor;
4050 padsize = rightOffset * scaleFactor;
4051 p->sourceWidth += padsize;
4052 m_conformanceWindow.bEnabled = true;
4053 m_conformanceWindow.rightOffset = padsize;
4054 }
4055
4056 if (fread(&bottomOffset, sizeof(int), 1, m_analysisFileIn) != 1)
4057 {
4058 x265_log(NULL, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Error reading analysis data. Conformance window bottom offset missing\n");
4059 m_aborted = true;
4060 }
4061 else if (bottomOffset && p->analysisLoadReuseLevel > 1)
4062 {
4063 int scaleFactor = p->scaleFactor < 2 ? 1 : p->scaleFactor;
4064 padsize = bottomOffset * scaleFactor;
4065 p->sourceHeight += padsize;
4066 m_conformanceWindow.bEnabled = true;
4067 m_conformanceWindow.bottomOffset = padsize;
4068 }
4069 }
4070 }
4071
4072 /* set pad size if width is not multiple of the minimum CU size */
4073 if (p->confWinRightOffset)
4074 {
4075 if ((p->sourceWidth + p->confWinRightOffset) & (p->minCUSize - 1))
4076 {
4077 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Incompatible conformance window right offset."
4078 " This when added to the source width should be a multiple of minCUSize\n");
4079 m_aborted = true;
4080 }
4081 else
4082 {
4083 p->sourceWidth += p->confWinRightOffset;
4084 m_conformanceWindow.bEnabled = true;
4085 m_conformanceWindow.rightOffset = p->confWinRightOffset;
4086 }
4087 }
4088 else if (p->sourceWidth & (p->minCUSize - 1))
4089 {
4090 uint32_t rem = p->sourceWidth & (p->minCUSize - 1);
4091 padsize = p->minCUSize - rem;
4092 p->sourceWidth += padsize;
4093
4094 m_conformanceWindow.bEnabled = true;
4095 m_conformanceWindow.rightOffset = padsize;
4096 }
4097
4098 if (p->bEnableRdRefine && (p->rdLevel < 5 || !p->rc.aqMode))
4099 {
4100 p->bEnableRdRefine = false;
4101 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "--rd-refine disabled, requires RD level > 4 and adaptive quant\n");
4102 }
4103
4104 if (p->bOptCUDeltaQP && p->rdLevel < 5)
4105 {
4106 p->bOptCUDeltaQP = false;
4107 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "--opt-cu-delta-qp disabled, requires RD level > 4\n");
4108 }
4109
4110 if (p->limitTU && p->tuQTMaxInterDepth < 2)
4111 {
4112 p->limitTU = 0;
4113 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "limit-tu disabled, requires tu-inter-depth > 1\n");
4114 }
4115 bool bIsVbv = m_param->rc.vbvBufferSize > 0 && m_param->rc.vbvMaxBitrate > 0;
4116 if (!m_param->bLossless && (m_param->rc.aqMode || bIsVbv || m_param->bAQMotion))
4117 {
4118 if (p->rc.qgSize < X265_MAX(8, p->minCUSize))
4119 {
4120 p->rc.qgSize = X265_MAX(8, p->minCUSize);
4121 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "QGSize should be greater than or equal to 8 and minCUSize, setting QGSize = %d\n", p->rc.qgSize);
4122 }
4123 if (p->rc.qgSize > p->maxCUSize)
4124 {
4125 p->rc.qgSize = p->maxCUSize;
4126 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "QGSize should be less than or equal to maxCUSize, setting QGSize = %d\n", p->rc.qgSize);
4127 }
4128 }
4129 else
4130 m_param->rc.qgSize = p->maxCUSize;
4131
4132 if (m_param->dynamicRd && (!bIsVbv || !p->rc.aqMode || p->rdLevel > 4))
4133 {
4134 p->dynamicRd = 0;
4135 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Dynamic-rd disabled, requires RD <= 4, VBV and aq-mode enabled\n");
4136 }
4137
4138 if (!p->bEnableFrameDuplication && p->dupThreshold && p->dupThreshold != 70)
4139 {
4140 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Frame-duplication threshold works only with frame-duplication enabled. Enabling frame-duplication.\n");
4141 p->bEnableFrameDuplication = 1;
4142 }
4143
4144 if (p->bEnableFrameDuplication && p->interlaceMode)
4145 {
4146 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Frame-duplication does not support interlace mode. Disabling Frame Duplication.\n");
4147 p->bEnableFrameDuplication = 0;
4148 }
4149
4150 if (p->bEnableFrameDuplication && p->pictureStructure != 0 && p->pictureStructure != -1)
4151 {
4152 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Frame-duplication works only with pic_struct = 0. Setting pic-struct = 0.\n");
4153 p->pictureStructure = 0;
4154 }
4155
4156 if (m_param->bEnableFrameDuplication && (!bIsVbv || !m_param->bEmitHRDSEI))
4157 {
4158 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Frame-duplication require NAL HRD and VBV parameters. Disabling frame duplication\n");
4159 m_param->bEnableFrameDuplication = 0;
4160 }
4161#ifdef ENABLE_HDR10_PLUS
4162 if (m_param->bDhdr10opt && m_param->toneMapFile == NULL)
4163 {
4164 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Disabling dhdr10-opt. dhdr10-info must be enabled.\n");
4165 m_param->bDhdr10opt = 0;
4166 }
4167
4168 if (m_param->toneMapFile)
4169 {
4170 if (!x265_fopen(p->toneMapFile, "r"))
4171 {
4172 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Unable to open tone-map file.\n");
4173 m_bToneMap = 0;
4174 m_param->toneMapFile = NULL;
4175 m_aborted = true;
4176 }
4177 else
4178 m_bToneMap = 1;
4179 }
4180 else
4181 m_bToneMap = 0;
4182#else
4183 if (m_param->toneMapFile)
4184 {
4185 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "--dhdr10-info disabled. Enable HDR10_PLUS in cmake.\n");
4186 m_bToneMap = 0;
4187 m_param->toneMapFile = NULL;
4188 }
4189 else if (m_param->bDhdr10opt)
4190 {
4191 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Disabling dhdr10-opt. dhdr10-info must be enabled.\n");
4192 m_param->bDhdr10opt = 0;
4193 }
4194#endif
4195
4196 if (p->uhdBluray)
4197 {
4198 p->bEnableAccessUnitDelimiters = 1;
4199 p->vui.aspectRatioIdc = 1;
4200 p->bEmitHRDSEI = 1;
4201 int disableUhdBd = 0;
4202
4203 if (p->levelIdc && p->levelIdc != 51)
4204 {
4205 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "uhd-bd: Wrong level specified, UHD Bluray mandates Level 5.1\n");
4206 }
4207 p->levelIdc = 51;
4208
4209 if (!p->bHighTier)
4210 {
4211 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "uhd-bd: Turning on high tier\n");
4212 p->bHighTier = 1;
4213 }
4214
4215 if (!p->bRepeatHeaders)
4216 {
4217 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "uhd-bd: Turning on repeat-headers\n");
4218 p->bRepeatHeaders = 1;
4219 }
4220
4221 if (p->bOpenGOP)
4222 {
4223 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "uhd-bd: Turning off open GOP\n");
4224 p->bOpenGOP = false;
4225 }
4226
4227 if (p->bIntraRefresh)
4228 {
4229 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "uhd-bd: turning off intra-refresh\n");
4230 p->bIntraRefresh = 0;
4231 }
4232
4233 if (p->keyframeMin != 1)
4234 {
4235 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "uhd-bd: keyframeMin is always 1\n");
4236 p->keyframeMin = 1;
4237 }
4238
4239 int fps = (p->fpsNum + p->fpsDenom - 1) / p->fpsDenom;
4240 if (p->keyframeMax > fps)
4241 {
4242 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "uhd-bd: reducing keyframeMax to %d\n", fps);
4243 p->keyframeMax = fps;
4244 }
4245
4246 if (p->maxNumReferences > 6)
4247 {
4248 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "uhd-bd: reducing references to 6\n");
4249 p->maxNumReferences = 6;
4250 }
4251
4252 if (p->bEnableTemporalSubLayers)
4253 {
4254 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "uhd-bd: Turning off temporal layering\n");
4255 p->bEnableTemporalSubLayers = 0;
4256 }
4257
4258 if (p->vui.colorPrimaries != 1 && p->vui.colorPrimaries != 9)
4259 {
4260 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_ERROR, "uhd-bd: colour primaries should be either BT.709 or BT.2020\n");
4261 disableUhdBd = 1;
4262 }
4263 else if (p->vui.colorPrimaries == 9)
4264 {
4265 p->vui.bEnableChromaLocInfoPresentFlag = 1;
4266 p->vui.chromaSampleLocTypeTopField = 2;
4267 p->vui.chromaSampleLocTypeBottomField = 2;
4268 }
4269
4270 if (p->vui.transferCharacteristics != 1 && p->vui.transferCharacteristics != 14 && p->vui.transferCharacteristics != 16)
4271 {
4272 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_ERROR, "uhd-bd: transfer characteristics supported are BT.709, BT.2020-10 or SMPTE ST.2084\n");
4273 disableUhdBd = 1;
4274 }
4275 if (p->vui.matrixCoeffs != 1 && p->vui.matrixCoeffs != 9)
4276 {
4277 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_ERROR, "uhd-bd: matrix coeffs supported are either BT.709 or BT.2020\n");
4278 disableUhdBd = 1;
4279 }
4280 if ((p->sourceWidth != 1920 && p->sourceWidth != 3840) || (p->sourceHeight != 1080 && p->sourceHeight != 2160))
4281 {
4282 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_ERROR, "uhd-bd: Supported resolutions are 1920x1080 and 3840x2160\n");
4283 disableUhdBd = 1;
4284 }
4285 if (disableUhdBd)
4286 {
4287 p->uhdBluray = 0;
4288 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_ERROR, "uhd-bd: Disabled\n");
4289 }
4290 }
4291 /* set pad size if height is not multiple of the minimum CU size */
4292 if (p->confWinBottomOffset)
4293 {
4294 if ((p->sourceHeight + p->confWinBottomOffset) & (p->minCUSize - 1))
4295 {
4296 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Incompatible conformance window bottom offset."
4297 " This when added to the source height should be a multiple of minCUSize\n");
4298 m_aborted = true;
4299 }
4300 else
4301 {
4302 p->sourceHeight += p->confWinBottomOffset;
4303 m_conformanceWindow.bEnabled = true;
4304 m_conformanceWindow.bottomOffset = p->confWinBottomOffset;
4305 }
4306 }
4307 else if(p->sourceHeight & (p->minCUSize - 1))
4308 {
4309 uint32_t rem = p->sourceHeight & (p->minCUSize - 1);
4310 padsize = p->minCUSize - rem;
4311 p->sourceHeight += padsize;
4312 m_conformanceWindow.bEnabled = true;
4313 m_conformanceWindow.bottomOffset = padsize;
4314 }
4315
4316 if (p->bLogCuStats)
4317 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "--cu-stats option is now deprecated\n");
4318
4319 if (p->log2MaxPocLsb < 4)
4320 {
4321 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "maximum of the picture order count can not be less than 4\n");
4322 p->log2MaxPocLsb = 4;
4323 }
4324
4325 if (p->maxSlices < 1)
4326 {
4327 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "maxSlices can not be less than 1, force set to 1\n");
4328 p->maxSlices = 1;
4329 }
4330 const uint32_t numRows = (p->sourceHeight + p->maxCUSize - 1) / p->maxCUSize;
4331 const uint32_t slicesLimit = X265_MIN(numRows, NALList::MAX_NAL_UNITS - 1);
4332 if (p->maxSlices > slicesLimit)
4333 {
4334 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "maxSlices can not be more than min(rows, MAX_NAL_UNITS-1), force set to %d\n", slicesLimit);
4335 p->maxSlices = slicesLimit;
4336 }
4337 if (p->bHDR10Opt)
4338 {
4339 if (p->internalCsp != X265_CSP_I420 || p->internalBitDepth != 10 || p->vui.colorPrimaries != 9 ||
4340 p->vui.transferCharacteristics != 16 || p->vui.matrixCoeffs != 9)
4341 {
4342 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Recommended Settings for HDR10-opt: colour primaries should be BT.2020,\n"
4343 " transfer characteristics should be SMPTE ST.2084,\n"
4344 " matrix coeffs should be BT.2020,\n"
4345 " the input video should be 10 bit 4:2:0\n"
4346 " Disabling hdr10-opt.\n");
4347 p->bHDR10Opt = 0;
4348 }
4349 }
4350
4351 if (p->videoSignalTypePreset) // Default disabled.
4352 configureVideoSignalTypePreset(p);
4353
4354 if (m_param->toneMapFile || p->bHDR10Opt || p->bEmitHDR10SEI)
4355 {
4356 if (!p->bRepeatHeaders)
4357 {
4358 p->bRepeatHeaders = 1;
4359 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Turning on repeat-headers for HDR compatibility\n");
4360 }
4361 }
4362
