4363 p->maxLog2CUSize = g_log2Size[p->maxCUSize];
4364 p->maxCUDepth = p->maxLog2CUSize - g_log2Size[p->minCUSize];
4365 p->unitSizeDepth = p->maxLog2CUSize - LOG2_UNIT_SIZE;
4366 p->num4x4Partitions = (1U << (p->unitSizeDepth << 1));
4367
4368 if (p->radl && p->bOpenGOP)
4369 {
4370 p->radl = 0;
4371 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Radl requires closed gop structure. Disabling radl.\n");
4372 }
4373
4374 if ((p->chunkStart || p->chunkEnd) && p->bOpenGOP && m_param->bResetZoneConfig)
4375 {
4376 p->chunkStart = p->chunkEnd = 0;
4377 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Chunking requires closed gop structure. Disabling chunking.\n");
4378 }
4379
4380 if (p->chunkEnd < p->chunkStart)
4381 {
4382 p->chunkStart = p->chunkEnd = 0;
4383 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "chunk-end cannot be less than chunk-start. Disabling chunking.\n");
4384 }
4385
4386 if (p->dolbyProfile) // Default disabled.
4387 configureDolbyVisionParams(p);
4388
4389 if (p->rc.zonefileCount && p->rc.zoneCount)
4390 {
4391 p->rc.zoneCount = 0;
4392 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Only zone or zonefile can be used. Enabling only zonefile\n");
4393 }
4394
4395 if (m_param->rc.zonefileCount && p->bOpenGOP)
4396 {
4397 p->bOpenGOP = 0;
4398 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Zone encoding requires closed gop structure. Enabling closed GOP.\n");
4399 }
4400
4401 if (m_param->rc.zonefileCount && !p->bRepeatHeaders)
4402 {
4403 p->bRepeatHeaders = 1;
4404 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Turning on repeat - headers for zone encoding\n");
4405 }
4406
4407 if (m_param->bEnableHME)
4408 {
4409 if (m_param->sourceHeight < 540)
4410 {
4411 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Source height < 540p is too low for HME. Disabling HME.\n");
4412 p->bEnableHME = 0;
4413 }
4414 }
4415
4416 if (m_param->bEnableHME)
4417 {
4418 if (m_param->searchMethod != m_param->hmeSearchMethod[2])
4419 m_param->searchMethod = m_param->hmeSearchMethod[2];
4420 if (m_param->searchRange != m_param->hmeRange[2])
4421 m_param->searchRange = m_param->hmeRange[2];
4422 }
4423
4424 if (p->bHistBasedSceneCut && !p->edgeTransitionThreshold)
4425 {
4426 p->edgeTransitionThreshold = 0.03;
4427 x265_log(p, X265_LOG_WARNING, "using default threshold %.2lf for scene cut detection\n", p->edgeTransitionThreshold);
4428 }
4429
4430}
4431
4432void Encoder::readAnalysisFile(x265_analysis_data* analysis, int curPoc, const x265_picture* picIn, int paramBytes)
4433{
4434#define X265_FREAD(val, size, readSize, fileOffset, src)\
4435 if (!m_param->bUseAnalysisFile)\
4436 {\
4437 memcpy(val, src, (size * readSize));\
4438 }\
4439 else if (fread(val, size, readSize, fileOffset) != readSize)\
4440 {\
4441 x265_log(NULL, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Error reading analysis data\n");\
4442 x265_free_analysis_data(m_param, analysis);\
4443 m_aborted = true;\
4444 return;\
4445 }\
4446
4447 static uint64_t consumedBytes = 0;
4448 static uint64_t totalConsumedBytes = 0;
4449 uint32_t depthBytes = 0;
4450 if (m_param->bUseAnalysisFile)
4451 fseeko(m_analysisFileIn, totalConsumedBytes + paramBytes, SEEK_SET);
4452 const x265_analysis_data *picData = &(picIn->analysisData);
4453 x265_analysis_intra_data *intraPic = picData->intraData;
4454 x265_analysis_inter_data *interPic = picData->interData;
4455 x265_analysis_distortion_data *picDistortion = picData->distortionData;
4456
4457 int poc; uint32_t frameRecordSize;
4458 X265_FREAD(&frameRecordSize, sizeof(uint32_t), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(picData->frameRecordSize));
4459 X265_FREAD(&depthBytes, sizeof(uint32_t), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(picData->depthBytes));
4460 X265_FREAD(&poc, sizeof(int), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(picData->poc));
4461
4462 if (m_param->bUseAnalysisFile)
4463 {
4464 uint64_t currentOffset = totalConsumedBytes;
4465
4466 /* Seeking to the right frame Record */
4467 while (poc != curPoc && !feof(m_analysisFileIn))
4468 {
4469 currentOffset += frameRecordSize;
4470 fseeko(m_analysisFileIn, currentOffset + paramBytes, SEEK_SET);
4471 X265_FREAD(&frameRecordSize, sizeof(uint32_t), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(picData->frameRecordSize));
4472 X265_FREAD(&depthBytes, sizeof(uint32_t), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(picData->depthBytes));
4473 X265_FREAD(&poc, sizeof(int), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(picData->poc));
4474 }
4475 if (poc != curPoc || feof(m_analysisFileIn))
4476 {
4477 x265_log(NULL, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Error reading analysis data: Cannot find POC %d\n", curPoc);
4478 x265_free_analysis_data(m_param, analysis);
4479 return;
4480 }
4481 }
4482
4483 uint32_t numCUsLoad, numCUsInHeightLoad;
4484
4485 /* Now arrived at the right frame, read the record */
4486 analysis->poc = poc;
4487 analysis->frameRecordSize = frameRecordSize;
4488 X265_FREAD(&analysis->sliceType, sizeof(int), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(picData->sliceType));
4489 X265_FREAD(&analysis->bScenecut, sizeof(int), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(picData->bScenecut));
4490 if (m_param->bHistBasedSceneCut)
4491 {
4492 X265_FREAD(&analysis->edgeHist, sizeof(int32_t), EDGE_BINS, m_analysisFileIn, &m_curEdgeHist);
4493 X265_FREAD(&analysis->yuvHist[0], sizeof(int32_t), HISTOGRAM_BINS, m_analysisFileIn, &m_curYUVHist[0]);
4494 if (m_param->internalCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
4495 {
4496 X265_FREAD(&analysis->yuvHist[1], sizeof(int32_t), HISTOGRAM_BINS, m_analysisFileIn, &m_curYUVHist[1]);
4497 X265_FREAD(&analysis->yuvHist[2], sizeof(int32_t), HISTOGRAM_BINS, m_analysisFileIn, &m_curYUVHist[2]);
4498 }
4499 }
4500 X265_FREAD(&analysis->satdCost, sizeof(int64_t), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(picData->satdCost));
4501 X265_FREAD(&numCUsLoad, sizeof(int), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(picData->numCUsInFrame));
4502 X265_FREAD(&analysis->numPartitions, sizeof(int), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(picData->numPartitions));
4503
4504 /* Update analysis info to save current settings */
4505 uint32_t widthInCU = (m_param->sourceWidth + m_param->maxCUSize - 1) >> m_param->maxLog2CUSize;
4506 uint32_t heightInCU = (m_param->sourceHeight + m_param->maxCUSize - 1) >> m_param->maxLog2CUSize;
4507 uint32_t numCUsInFrame = widthInCU * heightInCU;
4508 analysis->numCUsInFrame = numCUsInFrame;
4509 analysis->numCuInHeight = heightInCU;
4510
4511 if (m_param->bDisableLookahead)
4512 {
4513 X265_FREAD(&numCUsInHeightLoad, sizeof(uint32_t), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(picData->numCuInHeight));
4514 X265_FREAD(&analysis->lookahead, sizeof(x265_lookahead_data), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(picData->lookahead));
4515 }
4516 int scaledNumPartition = analysis->numPartitions;
4517 int factor = 1 << m_param->scaleFactor;
4518
4519 if (m_param->scaleFactor)
4520 analysis->numPartitions *= factor;
4521 /* Memory is allocated for inter and intra analysis data based on the slicetype */
4522 x265_alloc_analysis_data(m_param, analysis);
4523
4524 if (m_param->ctuDistortionRefine == CTU_DISTORTION_INTERNAL)
4525 {
4526 X265_FREAD((analysis->distortionData)->ctuDistortion, sizeof(sse_t), numCUsLoad, m_analysisFileIn, picDistortion);
4527 computeDistortionOffset(analysis);
4528 }
4529 if (m_param->bDisableLookahead && m_rateControl->m_isVbv)
4530 {
4531 size_t vbvCount = m_param->lookaheadDepth + m_param->bframes + 2;
4532 X265_FREAD(analysis->lookahead.intraVbvCost, sizeof(uint32_t), numCUsLoad, m_analysisFileIn, picData->lookahead.intraVbvCost);
4533 X265_FREAD(analysis->lookahead.vbvCost, sizeof(uint32_t), numCUsLoad, m_analysisFileIn, picData->lookahead.vbvCost);
4534 X265_FREAD(analysis->lookahead.satdForVbv, sizeof(uint32_t), numCUsInHeightLoad, m_analysisFileIn, picData->lookahead.satdForVbv);
4535 X265_FREAD(analysis->lookahead.intraSatdForVbv, sizeof(uint32_t), numCUsInHeightLoad, m_analysisFileIn, picData->lookahead.intraSatdForVbv);
4536 X265_FREAD(analysis->lookahead.plannedSatd, sizeof(int64_t), vbvCount, m_analysisFileIn, picData->lookahead.plannedSatd);
4537
4538 if (m_param->scaleFactor)
4539 {
4540 for (uint64_t index = 0; index < vbvCount; index++)
4541 analysis->lookahead.plannedSatd[index] *= factor;
4542
4543 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < numCUsInHeightLoad; i++)
4544 {
4545 analysis->lookahead.satdForVbv[i] *= factor;
4546 analysis->lookahead.intraSatdForVbv[i] *= factor;
4547 }
4548 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < numCUsLoad; i++)
4549 {
4550 analysis->lookahead.vbvCost[i] *= factor;
4551 analysis->lookahead.intraVbvCost[i] *= factor;
4552 }
4553 }
4554 }
4555 if (analysis->sliceType == X265_TYPE_IDR || analysis->sliceType == X265_TYPE_I)
4556 {
4557 if (m_param->bAnalysisType == HEVC_INFO)
4558 return;
4559 if (m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel < 2)
4560 return;
4561
4562 uint8_t *tempBuf = NULL, *depthBuf = NULL, *modeBuf = NULL, *partSizes = NULL;
4563 int8_t *cuQPBuf = NULL;
4564
4565 tempBuf = X265_MALLOC(uint8_t, depthBytes * 3);
4566 depthBuf = tempBuf;
4567 modeBuf = tempBuf + depthBytes;
4568 partSizes = tempBuf + 2 * depthBytes;
4569 if (m_param->rc.cuTree)
4570 cuQPBuf = X265_MALLOC(int8_t, depthBytes);
4571
4572 X265_FREAD(depthBuf, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn, intraPic->depth);
4573 X265_FREAD(modeBuf, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn, intraPic->chromaModes);
4574 X265_FREAD(partSizes, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn, intraPic->partSizes);
4575 if (m_param->rc.cuTree) { X265_FREAD(cuQPBuf, sizeof(int8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn, intraPic->cuQPOff); }
4576
4577 size_t count = 0;
4578 for (uint32_t d = 0; d < depthBytes; d++)
4579 {
4580 int bytes = analysis->numPartitions >> (depthBuf[d] * 2);
4581 if (m_param->scaleFactor)
4582 {
4583 if (depthBuf[d] == 0)
4584 depthBuf[d] = 1;
4585 if (partSizes[d] == SIZE_NxN)
4586 partSizes[d] = SIZE_2Nx2N;
4587 }
4588 memset(&(analysis->intraData)->depth[count], depthBuf[d], bytes);
4589 memset(&(analysis->intraData)->chromaModes[count], modeBuf[d], bytes);
4590 memset(&(analysis->intraData)->partSizes[count], partSizes[d], bytes);
4591 if (m_param->rc.cuTree)
4592 memset(&(analysis->intraData)->cuQPOff[count], cuQPBuf[d], bytes);
4593 count += bytes;
4594 }
4595
4596 if (!m_param->scaleFactor)
4597 {
4598 X265_FREAD((analysis->intraData)->modes, sizeof(uint8_t), numCUsLoad * analysis->numPartitions, m_analysisFileIn, intraPic->modes);
4599 }
4600 else
4601 {
4602 uint8_t *tempLumaBuf = X265_MALLOC(uint8_t, numCUsLoad * scaledNumPartition);
4603 X265_FREAD(tempLumaBuf, sizeof(uint8_t), numCUsLoad * scaledNumPartition, m_analysisFileIn, intraPic->modes);
4604 for (uint32_t ctu32Idx = 0, cnt = 0; ctu32Idx < numCUsLoad * scaledNumPartition; ctu32Idx++, cnt += factor)
4605 memset(&(analysis->intraData)->modes[cnt], tempLumaBuf[ctu32Idx], factor);
4606 X265_FREE(tempLumaBuf);
4607 }
4608 if (m_param->rc.cuTree)
4609 X265_FREE(cuQPBuf);
4610 X265_FREE(tempBuf);
4611 consumedBytes += frameRecordSize;
4612 }
4613
4614 else
4615 {
4616 uint32_t numDir = analysis->sliceType == X265_TYPE_P ? 1 : 2;
4617 uint32_t numPlanes = m_param->internalCsp == X265_CSP_I400 ? 1 : 3;
4618 X265_FREAD((WeightParam*)analysis->wt, sizeof(WeightParam), numPlanes * numDir, m_analysisFileIn, (picIn->analysisData.wt));
4619 if (m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel < 2)
4620 return;
4621
4622 uint8_t *tempBuf = NULL, *depthBuf = NULL, *modeBuf = NULL, *partSize = NULL, *mergeFlag = NULL;
4623 uint8_t *interDir = NULL, *chromaDir = NULL, *mvpIdx[2];
4624 MV* mv[2];
4625 int8_t* refIdx[2];
4626 int8_t* cuQPBuf = NULL;
4627
4628 int numBuf = m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel > 4 ? 4 : 2;
4629 bool bIntraInInter = false;
4630 if (m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel == 10)
4631 {
4632 numBuf++;
4633 bIntraInInter = (analysis->sliceType == X265_TYPE_P || m_param->bIntraInBFrames);
4634 if (bIntraInInter) numBuf++;
4635 }
4636 if (m_param->bAnalysisType == HEVC_INFO)
4637 {
4638 depthBytes = numCUsLoad * analysis->numPartitions;
4639 memcpy(((x265_analysis_inter_data *)analysis->interData)->depth, interPic->depth, depthBytes);
4640 }
4641 else
4642 {
4643 tempBuf = X265_MALLOC(uint8_t, depthBytes * numBuf);
4644 depthBuf = tempBuf;
4645 modeBuf = tempBuf + depthBytes;
4646 if (m_param->rc.cuTree)
4647 cuQPBuf = X265_MALLOC(int8_t, depthBytes);
4648
4649 X265_FREAD(depthBuf, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn, interPic->depth);
4650 X265_FREAD(modeBuf, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn, interPic->modes);
4651 if (m_param->rc.cuTree) { X265_FREAD(cuQPBuf, sizeof(int8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn, interPic->cuQPOff); }
4652
4653 if (m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel > 4)
4654 {
4655 partSize = modeBuf + depthBytes;
4656 mergeFlag = partSize + depthBytes;
4657 X265_FREAD(partSize, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn, interPic->partSize);
4658 X265_FREAD(mergeFlag, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn, interPic->mergeFlag);
4659
4660 if (m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel == 10)
4661 {
4662 interDir = mergeFlag + depthBytes;
4663 X265_FREAD(interDir, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn, interPic->interDir);
4664 if (bIntraInInter)
4665 {
4666 chromaDir = interDir + depthBytes;
4667 X265_FREAD(chromaDir, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn, intraPic->chromaModes);
4668 }
4669 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < numDir; i++)
4670 {
4671 mvpIdx[i] = X265_MALLOC(uint8_t, depthBytes);
4672 refIdx[i] = X265_MALLOC(int8_t, depthBytes);
4673 mv[i] = X265_MALLOC(MV, depthBytes);
4674 X265_FREAD(mvpIdx[i], sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn, interPic->mvpIdx[i]);
4675 X265_FREAD(refIdx[i], sizeof(int8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn, interPic->refIdx[i]);
4676 X265_FREAD(mv[i], sizeof(MV), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn, interPic->mv[i]);
4677 }
4678 }
4679 }
4680
4681 size_t count = 0;
4682 for (uint32_t d = 0; d < depthBytes; d++)
4683 {
4684 int bytes = analysis->numPartitions >> (depthBuf[d] * 2);
4685 if (m_param->scaleFactor && modeBuf[d] == MODE_INTRA && depthBuf[d] == 0)
4686 depthBuf[d] = 1;
4687 memset(&(analysis->interData)->depth[count], depthBuf[d], bytes);
4688 memset(&(analysis->interData)->modes[count], modeBuf[d], bytes);
4689 if (m_param->rc.cuTree)
4690 memset(&(analysis->interData)->cuQPOff[count], cuQPBuf[d], bytes);
4691 if (m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel > 4)
4692 {
4693 if (m_param->scaleFactor && modeBuf[d] == MODE_INTRA && partSize[d] == SIZE_NxN)
4694 partSize[d] = SIZE_2Nx2N;
4695 memset(&(analysis->interData)->partSize[count], partSize[d], bytes);
4696 int numPU = (modeBuf[d] == MODE_INTRA) ? 1 : nbPartsTable[(int)partSize[d]];
4697 for (int pu = 0; pu < numPU; pu++)
4698 {
4699 if (pu) d++;
4700 (analysis->interData)->mergeFlag[count + pu] = mergeFlag[d];
4701 if (m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel == 10)
4702 {
4703 (analysis->interData)->interDir[count + pu] = interDir[d];
4704 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < numDir; i++)
4705 {
4706 (analysis->interData)->mvpIdx[i][count + pu] = mvpIdx[i][d];
4707 (analysis->interData)->refIdx[i][count + pu] = refIdx[i][d];
4708 if (m_param->scaleFactor)
4709 {
4710 mv[i][d].x *= (int32_t)m_param->scaleFactor;
4711 mv[i][d].y *= (int32_t)m_param->scaleFactor;
4712 }
4713 memcpy(&(analysis->interData)->mv[i][count + pu], &mv[i][d], sizeof(MV));
4714 }
4715 }
4716 }
4717 if (m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel == 10 && bIntraInInter)
4718 memset(&(analysis->intraData)->chromaModes[count], chromaDir[d], bytes);
4719 }
4720 count += bytes;
4721 }
4722
4723 if (m_param->rc.cuTree)
4724 X265_FREE(cuQPBuf);
4725 X265_FREE(tempBuf);
4726 }
4727 if (m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel == 10)
4728 {
4729 if (m_param->bAnalysisType != HEVC_INFO)
4730 {
4731 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < numDir; i++)
4732 {
4733 X265_FREE(mvpIdx[i]);
4734 X265_FREE(refIdx[i]);
4735 X265_FREE(mv[i]);
4736 }
4737 }
4738 if (bIntraInInter)
4739 {
4740 if (!m_param->scaleFactor)
4741 {
4742 X265_FREAD((analysis->intraData)->modes, sizeof(uint8_t), numCUsLoad * analysis->numPartitions, m_analysisFileIn, intraPic->modes);
4743 }
4744 else
4745 {
4746 uint8_t *tempLumaBuf = X265_MALLOC(uint8_t, numCUsLoad * scaledNumPartition);
4747 X265_FREAD(tempLumaBuf, sizeof(uint8_t), numCUsLoad * scaledNumPartition, m_analysisFileIn, intraPic->modes);
4748 for (uint32_t ctu32Idx = 0, cnt = 0; ctu32Idx < numCUsLoad * scaledNumPartition; ctu32Idx++, cnt += factor)
4749 memset(&(analysis->intraData)->modes[cnt], tempLumaBuf[ctu32Idx], factor);
4750 X265_FREE(tempLumaBuf);
4751 }
4752 }
4753 }
4754 else
4755 X265_FREAD((analysis->interData)->ref, sizeof(int32_t), numCUsLoad * X265_MAX_PRED_MODE_PER_CTU * numDir, m_analysisFileIn, interPic->ref);
4756
4757 consumedBytes += frameRecordSize;
4758 if (numDir == 1)
4759 totalConsumedBytes = consumedBytes;
4760 }
4761
4762#undef X265_FREAD
4763}
4764
4765void Encoder::readAnalysisFile(x265_analysis_data* analysis, int curPoc, const x265_picture* picIn, int paramBytes, cuLocation cuLoc)
4766{
4767#define X265_FREAD(val, size, readSize, fileOffset, src)\
4768 if (!m_param->bUseAnalysisFile)\
4769 {\
4770 memcpy(val, src, (size * readSize));\
4771 }\
4772 else if (fread(val, size, readSize, fileOffset) != readSize)\
4773 {\
4774 x265_log(NULL, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Error reading analysis data\n");\
4775 x265_free_analysis_data(m_param, analysis);\
4776 m_aborted = true;\
4777 return;\
4778 }\
4779
4780 static uint64_t consumedBytes = 0;
4781 static uint64_t totalConsumedBytes = 0;
4782 uint32_t depthBytes = 0;
4783 if (m_param->bUseAnalysisFile)
4784 fseeko(m_analysisFileIn, totalConsumedBytes + paramBytes, SEEK_SET);
4785
4786 const x265_analysis_data *picData = &(picIn->analysisData);
4787 x265_analysis_intra_data *intraPic = picData->intraData;
4788 x265_analysis_inter_data *interPic = picData->interData;
4789 x265_analysis_distortion_data *picDistortion = picData->distortionData;
4790
4791 int poc; uint32_t frameRecordSize;
4792 X265_FREAD(&frameRecordSize, sizeof(uint32_t), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(picData->frameRecordSize));
4793 X265_FREAD(&depthBytes, sizeof(uint32_t), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(picData->depthBytes));
4794 X265_FREAD(&poc, sizeof(int), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(picData->poc));
4795
4796 if (m_param->bUseAnalysisFile)
4797 {
4798 uint64_t currentOffset = totalConsumedBytes;
4799
4800 /* Seeking to the right frame Record */
4801 while (poc != curPoc && !feof(m_analysisFileIn))
4802 {
4803 currentOffset += frameRecordSize;
4804 fseeko(m_analysisFileIn, currentOffset + paramBytes, SEEK_SET);
4805 X265_FREAD(&frameRecordSize, sizeof(uint32_t), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(picData->frameRecordSize));
4806 X265_FREAD(&depthBytes, sizeof(uint32_t), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(picData->depthBytes));
4807 X265_FREAD(&poc, sizeof(int), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(picData->poc));
4808 }
4809 if (poc != curPoc || feof(m_analysisFileIn))
4810 {
4811 x265_log(NULL, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Error reading analysis data: Cannot find POC %d\n", curPoc);
4812 x265_free_analysis_data(m_param, analysis);
4813 return;
4814 }
4815 }
4816
4817 /* Now arrived at the right frame, read the record */
4818 analysis->poc = poc;
4819 analysis->frameRecordSize = frameRecordSize;
4820 X265_FREAD(&analysis->sliceType, sizeof(int), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(picData->sliceType));
4821 X265_FREAD(&analysis->bScenecut, sizeof(int), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(picData->bScenecut));
4822 if (m_param->bHistBasedSceneCut)
4823 {
4824 X265_FREAD(&analysis->edgeHist, sizeof(int32_t), EDGE_BINS, m_analysisFileIn, &m_curEdgeHist);
4825 X265_FREAD(&analysis->yuvHist[0], sizeof(int32_t), HISTOGRAM_BINS, m_analysisFileIn, &m_curYUVHist[0]);
4826 if (m_param->internalCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
4827 {
4828 X265_FREAD(&analysis->yuvHist[1], sizeof(int32_t), HISTOGRAM_BINS, m_analysisFileIn, &m_curYUVHist[1]);
4829 X265_FREAD(&analysis->yuvHist[2], sizeof(int32_t), HISTOGRAM_BINS, m_analysisFileIn, &m_curYUVHist[2]);
4830 }
4831 }
4832 X265_FREAD(&analysis->satdCost, sizeof(int64_t), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(picData->satdCost));
4833 X265_FREAD(&analysis->numCUsInFrame, sizeof(int), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(picData->numCUsInFrame));
4834 X265_FREAD(&analysis->numPartitions, sizeof(int), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(picData->numPartitions));
4835
4836 if (m_param->bDisableLookahead)
4837 {
4838 X265_FREAD(&analysis->numCuInHeight, sizeof(uint32_t), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(picData->numCuInHeight));
4839 X265_FREAD(&analysis->lookahead, sizeof(x265_lookahead_data), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(picData->lookahead));
4840 }
4841 int scaledNumPartition = analysis->numPartitions;
4842 int factor = 1 << m_param->scaleFactor;
4843
4844 int numPartitions = analysis->numPartitions;
4845 int numCUsInFrame = analysis->numCUsInFrame;
4846 int numCuInHeight = analysis->numCuInHeight;
4847 /* Allocate memory for scaled resoultion's numPartitions and numCUsInFrame*/
4848 analysis->numPartitions = m_param->num4x4Partitions;
4849 analysis->numCUsInFrame = cuLoc.heightInCU * cuLoc.widthInCU;
4850 analysis->numCuInHeight = cuLoc.heightInCU;
4851
4852 /* Memory is allocated for inter and intra analysis data based on the slicetype */
4853 x265_alloc_analysis_data(m_param, analysis);
4854
4855 if (m_param->ctuDistortionRefine == CTU_DISTORTION_INTERNAL)
4856 {
4857 X265_FREAD((analysis->distortionData)->ctuDistortion, sizeof(sse_t), analysis->numCUsInFrame, m_analysisFileIn, picDistortion);
4858 computeDistortionOffset(analysis);
4859 }
4860
4861 analysis->numPartitions = numPartitions * factor;
4862 analysis->numCUsInFrame = numCUsInFrame;
4863 analysis->numCuInHeight = numCuInHeight;
4864 if (m_param->bDisableLookahead && m_rateControl->m_isVbv)
4865 {
4866 uint32_t width = analysis->numCUsInFrame / analysis->numCuInHeight;
4867 bool skipLastRow = (analysis->numCuInHeight * 2) > cuLoc.heightInCU;
4868 bool skipLastCol = (width * 2) > cuLoc.widthInCU;
4869 uint32_t *intraVbvCostBuf = NULL, *vbvCostBuf = NULL, *satdForVbvBuf = NULL, *intraSatdForVbvBuf = NULL;
4870 intraVbvCostBuf = X265_MALLOC(uint32_t, analysis->numCUsInFrame);
4871 vbvCostBuf = X265_MALLOC(uint32_t, analysis->numCUsInFrame);
4872 satdForVbvBuf = X265_MALLOC(uint32_t, analysis->numCuInHeight);
4873 intraSatdForVbvBuf = X265_MALLOC(uint32_t, analysis->numCuInHeight);
4874
4875 X265_FREAD(intraVbvCostBuf, sizeof(uint32_t), analysis->numCUsInFrame, m_analysisFileIn, picData->lookahead.intraVbvCost);
4876 X265_FREAD(vbvCostBuf, sizeof(uint32_t), analysis->numCUsInFrame, m_analysisFileIn, picData->lookahead.vbvCost);
4877 X265_FREAD(satdForVbvBuf, sizeof(uint32_t), analysis->numCuInHeight, m_analysisFileIn, picData->lookahead.satdForVbv);
4878 X265_FREAD(intraSatdForVbvBuf, sizeof(uint32_t), analysis->numCuInHeight, m_analysisFileIn, picData->lookahead.intraSatdForVbv);
4879
4880 int k = 0;
4881 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < analysis->numCuInHeight; i++)
4882 {
4883 analysis->lookahead.satdForVbv[m_param->scaleFactor * i] = satdForVbvBuf[i] * m_param->scaleFactor;
4884 analysis->lookahead.intraSatdForVbv[m_param->scaleFactor * i] = intraSatdForVbvBuf[i] * m_param->scaleFactor;
4885 if (!(i == (analysis->numCuInHeight - 1) && skipLastRow))
4886 {
4887 analysis->lookahead.satdForVbv[(m_param->scaleFactor * i) + 1] = satdForVbvBuf[i] * m_param->scaleFactor;
4888 analysis->lookahead.intraSatdForVbv[(m_param->scaleFactor * i) + 1] = intraSatdForVbvBuf[i] * m_param->scaleFactor;
4889 }
4890
4891 for (uint32_t j = 0; j < width; j++, k++)
4892 {
4893 analysis->lookahead.vbvCost[(i * m_param->scaleFactor * cuLoc.widthInCU) + (j * m_param->scaleFactor)] = vbvCostBuf[k];
4894 analysis->lookahead.intraVbvCost[(i * m_param->scaleFactor * cuLoc.widthInCU) + (j * m_param->scaleFactor)] = intraVbvCostBuf[k];
4895
4896 if (!(j == (width - 1) && skipLastCol))
4897 {
4898 analysis->lookahead.vbvCost[(i * m_param->scaleFactor * cuLoc.widthInCU) + (j * m_param->scaleFactor) + 1] = vbvCostBuf[k];
4899 analysis->lookahead.intraVbvCost[(i * m_param->scaleFactor * cuLoc.widthInCU) + (j * m_param->scaleFactor) + 1] = intraVbvCostBuf[k];
4900 }
4901 if (!(i == (analysis->numCuInHeight - 1) && skipLastRow))
4902 {
4903 analysis->lookahead.vbvCost[(i * m_param->scaleFactor * cuLoc.widthInCU) + cuLoc.widthInCU + (j * m_param->scaleFactor)] = vbvCostBuf[k];
4904 analysis->lookahead.intraVbvCost[(i * m_param->scaleFactor * cuLoc.widthInCU) + cuLoc.widthInCU + (j * m_param->scaleFactor)] = intraVbvCostBuf[k];
4905 if (!(j == (width - 1) && skipLastCol))
4906 {
4907 analysis->lookahead.vbvCost[(i * m_param->scaleFactor * cuLoc.widthInCU) + cuLoc.widthInCU + (j * m_param->scaleFactor) + 1] = vbvCostBuf[k];
4908 analysis->lookahead.intraVbvCost[(i * m_param->scaleFactor * cuLoc.widthInCU) + cuLoc.widthInCU + (j * m_param->scaleFactor) + 1] = intraVbvCostBuf[k];
4909 }
4910 }
4911 }
4912 }
4913 X265_FREE(satdForVbvBuf);
4914 X265_FREE(intraSatdForVbvBuf);
4915 X265_FREE(intraVbvCostBuf);
4916 X265_FREE(vbvCostBuf);
4917 }
4918
4919 if (analysis->sliceType == X265_TYPE_IDR || analysis->sliceType == X265_TYPE_I)
4920 {
4921 if (m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel < 2)
4922 return;
4923
4924 uint8_t *tempBuf = NULL, *depthBuf = NULL, *modeBuf = NULL, *partSizes = NULL;
4925 int8_t *cuQPBuf = NULL;
4926
4927 tempBuf = X265_MALLOC(uint8_t, depthBytes * 3);
4928 depthBuf = tempBuf;
4929 modeBuf = tempBuf + depthBytes;
4930 partSizes = tempBuf + 2 * depthBytes;
4931 if (m_param->rc.cuTree)
4932 cuQPBuf = X265_MALLOC(int8_t, depthBytes);
4933
4934 X265_FREAD(depthBuf, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn, intraPic->depth);
4935 X265_FREAD(modeBuf, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn, intraPic->chromaModes);
4936 X265_FREAD(partSizes, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn, intraPic->partSizes);
4937 if (m_param->rc.cuTree) { X265_FREAD(cuQPBuf, sizeof(int8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn, intraPic->cuQPOff); }
4938
4939 uint32_t count = 0;
4940 for (uint32_t d = 0; d < depthBytes; d++)
4941 {
4942 int bytes = analysis->numPartitions >> (depthBuf[d] * 2);
4943 int numCTUCopied = 1;
4944 if (!depthBuf[d]) //copy data of one 64x64 to four scaled 64x64 CTUs.
4945 {
4946 bytes /= 4;
4947 numCTUCopied = 4;
4948 }
4949 if (partSizes[d] == SIZE_NxN)
4950 partSizes[d] = SIZE_2Nx2N;
4951 if ((depthBuf[d] > 1 && m_param->maxCUSize == 64) || (depthBuf[d] && m_param->maxCUSize != 64))
4952 depthBuf[d]--;
4953
4954 for (int numCTU = 0; numCTU < numCTUCopied; numCTU++)
4955 {
4956 memset(&(analysis->intraData)->depth[count], depthBuf[d], bytes);
4957 memset(&(analysis->intraData)->chromaModes[count], modeBuf[d], bytes);
4958 memset(&(analysis->intraData)->partSizes[count], partSizes[d], bytes);
4959 if (m_param->rc.cuTree)
4960 memset(&(analysis->intraData)->cuQPOff[count], cuQPBuf[d], bytes);
4961 count += bytes;
4962 d += getCUIndex(&cuLoc, &count, bytes, 1);
4963 }
4964 }
4965
4966 cuLoc.evenRowIndex = 0;
4967 cuLoc.oddRowIndex = m_param->num4x4Partitions * cuLoc.widthInCU;
4968 cuLoc.switchCondition = 0;
4969 uint8_t *tempLumaBuf = X265_MALLOC(uint8_t, analysis->numCUsInFrame * scaledNumPartition);
4970 X265_FREAD(tempLumaBuf, sizeof(uint8_t), analysis->numCUsInFrame * scaledNumPartition, m_analysisFileIn, intraPic->modes);
4971 uint32_t cnt = 0;
4972 for (uint32_t ctu32Idx = 0; ctu32Idx < analysis->numCUsInFrame * scaledNumPartition; ctu32Idx++)
4973 {
4974 memset(&(analysis->intraData)->modes[cnt], tempLumaBuf[ctu32Idx], factor);
4975 cnt += factor;
4976 ctu32Idx += getCUIndex(&cuLoc, &cnt, factor, 0);
4977 }
4978 X265_FREE(tempLumaBuf);
4979 if (m_param->rc.cuTree)
4980 X265_FREE(cuQPBuf);
4981 X265_FREE(tempBuf);
4982 consumedBytes += frameRecordSize;
4983 }
4984
4985 else
4986 {
4987 uint32_t numDir = analysis->sliceType == X265_TYPE_P ? 1 : 2;
4988 uint32_t numPlanes = m_param->internalCsp == X265_CSP_I400 ? 1 : 3;
4989 X265_FREAD((WeightParam*)analysis->wt, sizeof(WeightParam), numPlanes * numDir, m_analysisFileIn, (picIn->analysisData.wt));
4990 if (m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel < 2)
4991 return;
4992
4993 uint8_t *tempBuf = NULL, *depthBuf = NULL, *modeBuf = NULL, *partSize = NULL, *mergeFlag = NULL;
4994 uint8_t *interDir = NULL, *chromaDir = NULL, *mvpIdx[2];
4995 MV* mv[2];
4996 int8_t* refIdx[2];
4997 int8_t* cuQPBuf = NULL;
4998
4999 int numBuf = m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel > 4 ? 4 : 2;
5000 bool bIntraInInter = false;
5001 if (m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel == 10)
5002 {
5003 numBuf++;
5004 bIntraInInter = (analysis->sliceType == X265_TYPE_P || m_param->bIntraInBFrames);
5005 if (bIntraInInter) numBuf++;
5006 }
5007
5008 tempBuf = X265_MALLOC(uint8_t, depthBytes * numBuf);
5009 depthBuf = tempBuf;
5010 modeBuf = tempBuf + depthBytes;
5011 if (m_param->rc.cuTree)
5012 cuQPBuf = X265_MALLOC(int8_t, depthBytes);
5013
5014 X265_FREAD(depthBuf, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn, interPic->depth);
5015 X265_FREAD(modeBuf, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn, interPic->modes);
5016 if (m_param->rc.cuTree) { X265_FREAD(cuQPBuf, sizeof(int8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn, interPic->cuQPOff); }
5017 if (m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel > 4)
5018 {
5019 partSize = modeBuf + depthBytes;
5020 mergeFlag = partSize + depthBytes;
5021 X265_FREAD(partSize, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn, interPic->partSize);
5022 X265_FREAD(mergeFlag, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn, interPic->mergeFlag);
5023 if (m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel == 10)
5024 {
5025 interDir = mergeFlag + depthBytes;
5026 X265_FREAD(interDir, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn, interPic->interDir);
5027 if (bIntraInInter)
5028 {
5029 chromaDir = interDir + depthBytes;
5030 X265_FREAD(chromaDir, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn, intraPic->chromaModes);
5031 }
5032 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < numDir; i++)
5033 {
5034 mvpIdx[i] = X265_MALLOC(uint8_t, depthBytes);
5035 refIdx[i] = X265_MALLOC(int8_t, depthBytes);
5036 mv[i] = X265_MALLOC(MV, depthBytes);
5037 X265_FREAD(mvpIdx[i], sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn, interPic->mvpIdx[i]);
5038 X265_FREAD(refIdx[i], sizeof(int8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn, interPic->refIdx[i]);
5039 X265_FREAD(mv[i], sizeof(MV), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn, interPic->mv[i]);
5040 }
5041 }
5042 }
5043
5044 uint32_t count = 0;
5045 cuLoc.switchCondition = 0;
5046 for (uint32_t d = 0; d < depthBytes; d++)
5047 {
5048 int bytes = analysis->numPartitions >> (depthBuf[d] * 2);
5049 bool isScaledMaxCUSize = false;
5050 int numCTUCopied = 1;
5051 int writeDepth = depthBuf[d];
5052 if (!depthBuf[d]) //copy data of one 64x64 to four scaled 64x64 CTUs.
5053 {
5054 isScaledMaxCUSize = true;
5055 bytes /= 4;
5056 numCTUCopied = 4;
5057 }
5058 if ((modeBuf[d] != MODE_INTRA && depthBuf[d] != 0) || (modeBuf[d] == MODE_INTRA && depthBuf[d] > 1))
5059 writeDepth--;
5060
5061 for (int numCTU = 0; numCTU < numCTUCopied; numCTU++)
5062 {
5063 memset(&(analysis->interData)->depth[count], writeDepth, bytes);
5064 memset(&(analysis->interData)->modes[count], modeBuf[d], bytes);
5065 if (m_param->rc.cuTree)
5066 memset(&(analysis->interData)->cuQPOff[count], cuQPBuf[d], bytes);
5067 if (m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel == 10 && bIntraInInter)
5068 memset(&(analysis->intraData)->chromaModes[count], chromaDir[d], bytes);
5069
5070 if (m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel > 4)
5071 {
5072 puOrientation puOrient;
5073 puOrient.init();
5074 if (modeBuf[d] == MODE_INTRA && partSize[d] == SIZE_NxN)
5075 partSize[d] = SIZE_2Nx2N;
5076 int partitionSize = partSize[d];
5077 if (isScaledMaxCUSize && partSize[d] != SIZE_2Nx2N)
5078 partitionSize = getPuShape(&puOrient, partSize[d], numCTU);
5079 memset(&(analysis->interData)->partSize[count], partitionSize, bytes);
5080 int numPU = (modeBuf[d] == MODE_INTRA) ? 1 : nbPartsTable[(int)partSize[d]];
5081 for (int pu = 0; pu < numPU; pu++)
5082 {
5083 if (!isScaledMaxCUSize && pu)
5084 d++;
5085 int restoreD = d;
5086 /* Adjust d value when the current CTU takes data from 2nd PU */
5087 if (puOrient.isRect || (puOrient.isAmp && partitionSize == SIZE_2Nx2N))
5088 {
5089 if ((numCTU > 1 && !puOrient.isVert) || ((numCTU % 2 == 1) && puOrient.isVert))
5090 d++;
5091 }
5092 if (puOrient.isAmp && pu)
5093 d++;
5094
5095 (analysis->interData)->mergeFlag[count + pu] = mergeFlag[d];
5096 if (m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel == 10)
5097 {
5098 (analysis->interData)->interDir[count + pu] = interDir[d];
5099 MV mvCopy[2];
5100 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < numDir; i++)
5101 {
5102 (analysis->interData)->mvpIdx[i][count + pu] = mvpIdx[i][d];
5103 (analysis->interData)->refIdx[i][count + pu] = refIdx[i][d];
5104 mvCopy[i].x = mv[i][d].x * (int32_t)m_param->scaleFactor;
5105 mvCopy[i].y = mv[i][d].y * (int32_t)m_param->scaleFactor;
5106 memcpy(&(analysis->interData)->mv[i][count + pu], &mvCopy[i], sizeof(MV));
5107 }
5108 }
5109 d = restoreD; // Restore d value after copying each of the 4 64x64 CTUs
5110
5111 if (isScaledMaxCUSize && (puOrient.isRect || puOrient.isAmp))
5112 {
5113 /* Skip PU index when current CTU is a 2Nx2N */
5114 if (partitionSize == SIZE_2Nx2N)
5115 pu++;
5116 /* Adjust d after completion of all 4 CTU copies */
5117 if (numCTU == 3 && (pu == (numPU - 1)))
5118 d++;
5119 }
5120 }
5121 }
5122 count += bytes;
5123 d += getCUIndex(&cuLoc, &count, bytes, 1);
5124 }
5125 }
5126
5127 if (m_param->rc.cuTree)
5128 X265_FREE(cuQPBuf);
5129 X265_FREE(tempBuf);
5130
5131 if (m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel == 10)
5132 {
5133 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < numDir; i++)
5134 {
5135 X265_FREE(mvpIdx[i]);
5136 X265_FREE(refIdx[i]);
5137 X265_FREE(mv[i]);
5138 }
5139 if (bIntraInInter)
5140 {
5141 cuLoc.evenRowIndex = 0;
5142 cuLoc.oddRowIndex = m_param->num4x4Partitions * cuLoc.widthInCU;
5143 cuLoc.switchCondition = 0;
5144 uint8_t *tempLumaBuf = X265_MALLOC(uint8_t, analysis->numCUsInFrame * scaledNumPartition);
5145 X265_FREAD(tempLumaBuf, sizeof(uint8_t), analysis->numCUsInFrame * scaledNumPartition, m_analysisFileIn, intraPic->modes);
5146 uint32_t cnt = 0;
5147 for (uint32_t ctu32Idx = 0; ctu32Idx < analysis->numCUsInFrame * scaledNumPartition; ctu32Idx++)
5148 {
5149 memset(&(analysis->intraData)->modes[cnt], tempLumaBuf[ctu32Idx], factor);
5150 cnt += factor;
5151 ctu32Idx += getCUIndex(&cuLoc, &cnt, factor, 0);
5152 }
5153 X265_FREE(tempLumaBuf);
5154 }
5155 }
5156 else
5157 X265_FREAD((analysis->interData)->ref, sizeof(int32_t), analysis->numCUsInFrame * X265_MAX_PRED_MODE_PER_CTU * numDir, m_analysisFileIn, interPic->ref);
5158
5159 consumedBytes += frameRecordSize;
5160 if (numDir == 1)
5161 totalConsumedBytes = consumedBytes;
5162 }
5163
5164 /* Restore to the current encode's numPartitions and numCUsInFrame */
5165 analysis->numPartitions = m_param->num4x4Partitions;
5166 analysis->numCUsInFrame = cuLoc.heightInCU * cuLoc.widthInCU;
5167 analysis->numCuInHeight = cuLoc.heightInCU;
5168#undef X265_FREAD
5169}
5170
5171
5172int Encoder::validateAnalysisData(x265_analysis_validate* saveParam, int writeFlag)
5173{
5174#define X265_PARAM_VALIDATE(analysisParam, size, bytes, param, errorMsg)\
5175 if(!writeFlag)\
5176 {\
5177 fileOffset = m_analysisFileIn;\
5178 if ((!m_param->bUseAnalysisFile && analysisParam != (int)*param) || \
5179 (m_param->bUseAnalysisFile && (fread(&readValue, size, bytes, fileOffset) != bytes || (readValue != (int)*param))))\
5180 {\
5181 x265_log(NULL, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Error reading analysis data. Incompatible option : <%s> \n", #errorMsg);\
5182 m_aborted = true;\
5183 return -1;\
5184 }\
5185 }\
5186 if(writeFlag)\
5187 {\
5188 fileOffset = m_analysisFileOut;\
5189 if(!m_param->bUseAnalysisFile)\
5190 analysisParam = *param;\
5191 else if(fwrite(param, size, bytes, fileOffset) < bytes)\
5192 {\
5193 x265_log(NULL, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Error writing analysis data\n"); \
5194 m_aborted = true;\
5195 return -1; \
5196 }\
5197 }\
5198 count++;
5199
5200#define X265_FREAD(val, size, readSize, fileOffset, src)\
5201 if (!m_param->bUseAnalysisFile)\
5202 {\
5203 memcpy(val, src, (size * readSize));\
5204 }\
5205 else if (fread(val, size, readSize, fileOffset) != readSize)\
5206 {\
5207 x265_log(NULL, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Error reading analysis data\n");\
5208 m_aborted = true;\
5209 return -1;\
5210 }\
5211 count++;
5212
5213 FILE* fileOffset = NULL;
5214 int readValue = 0;
5215 int count = 0;
5216
5217 if (m_param->bUseAnalysisFile && writeFlag)
5218 {
5219 X265_PARAM_VALIDATE(saveParam->rightOffset, sizeof(int), 1, &m_conformanceWindow.rightOffset, right-offset);
5220 X265_PARAM_VALIDATE(saveParam->bottomOffset, sizeof(int), 1, &m_conformanceWindow.bottomOffset, bottom-offset);
5221 }
5222
5223 X265_PARAM_VALIDATE(saveParam->intraRefresh, sizeof(int), 1, &m_param->bIntraRefresh, intra-refresh);
5224 X265_PARAM_VALIDATE(saveParam->maxNumReferences, sizeof(int), 1, &m_param->maxNumReferences, ref);
5225 X265_PARAM_VALIDATE(saveParam->keyframeMax, sizeof(int), 1, &m_param->keyframeMax, keyint);
5226 X265_PARAM_VALIDATE(saveParam->keyframeMin, sizeof(int), 1, &m_param->keyframeMin, min-keyint);
5227 X265_PARAM_VALIDATE(saveParam->openGOP, sizeof(int), 1, &m_param->bOpenGOP, open-gop);
5228 X265_PARAM_VALIDATE(saveParam->bframes, sizeof(int), 1, &m_param->bframes, bframes);
5229 X265_PARAM_VALIDATE(saveParam->bPyramid, sizeof(int), 1, &m_param->bBPyramid, bPyramid);
5230 X265_PARAM_VALIDATE(saveParam->minCUSize, sizeof(int), 1, &m_param->minCUSize, min - cu - size);
5231 X265_PARAM_VALIDATE(saveParam->lookaheadDepth, sizeof(int), 1, &m_param->lookaheadDepth, rc - lookahead);
5232 X265_PARAM_VALIDATE(saveParam->chunkStart, sizeof(int), 1, &m_param->chunkStart, chunk-start);
5233 X265_PARAM_VALIDATE(saveParam->chunkEnd, sizeof(int), 1, &m_param->chunkEnd, chunk-end);
5234 X265_PARAM_VALIDATE(saveParam->ctuDistortionRefine, sizeof(int), 1, &m_param->ctuDistortionRefine, ctu - distortion);
5235 X265_PARAM_VALIDATE(saveParam->frameDuplication, sizeof(int), 1, &m_param->bEnableFrameDuplication, frame - dup);
5236
5237 int sourceHeight, sourceWidth;
5238 if (writeFlag)
5239 {
5240 X265_PARAM_VALIDATE(saveParam->analysisReuseLevel, sizeof(int), 1, &m_param->analysisSaveReuseLevel, analysis - save - reuse - level);
5241 X265_PARAM_VALIDATE(saveParam->cuTree, sizeof(int), 1, &m_param->rc.cuTree, cutree-offset);
5242 sourceHeight = m_param->sourceHeight - m_conformanceWindow.bottomOffset;
5243 sourceWidth = m_param->sourceWidth - m_conformanceWindow.rightOffset;
5244 X265_PARAM_VALIDATE(saveParam->sourceWidth, sizeof(int), 1, &sourceWidth, res-width);
5245 X265_PARAM_VALIDATE(saveParam->sourceHeight, sizeof(int), 1, &sourceHeight, res-height);
5246 X265_PARAM_VALIDATE(saveParam->maxCUSize, sizeof(int), 1, &m_param->maxCUSize, ctu);
5247 }
5248 else
5249 {
5250 fileOffset = m_analysisFileIn;
5251
5252 int saveLevel = 0;
5253 bool isIncompatibleReuseLevel = false;
5254 int loadLevel = m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel;
5255
5256 X265_FREAD(&saveLevel, sizeof(int), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(saveParam->analysisReuseLevel));
5257
5258 if (loadLevel == 10 && saveLevel != 10)
5259 isIncompatibleReuseLevel = true;
5260 else if (((loadLevel >= 7) && (loadLevel <= 9)) && ((saveLevel < 7) || (saveLevel > 9)))
5261 isIncompatibleReuseLevel = true;
5262 else if ((loadLevel == 5 || loadLevel == 6) && ((saveLevel != 5) && (saveLevel != 6)))
5263 isIncompatibleReuseLevel = true;
5264 else if ((loadLevel >= 2 && loadLevel <= 4) && (saveLevel < 2 || saveLevel > 6))
5265 isIncompatibleReuseLevel = true;
5266 else if (!saveLevel)
5267 isIncompatibleReuseLevel = true;
5268
5269 if (isIncompatibleReuseLevel)
5270 {
5271 x265_log(NULL, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Error reading analysis data. Incompatible reuse-levels.\n");
5272 m_aborted = true;
5273 return -1;
5274 }
5275
5276 int bcutree;
5277 X265_FREAD(&bcutree, sizeof(int), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(saveParam->cuTree));
5278 if (loadLevel >= 2 && m_param->rc.cuTree && (!bcutree || saveLevel < 2))
5279 {
5280 x265_log(NULL, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Error reading cu-tree info. Disabling cutree offsets. \n");
5281 m_param->rc.cuTree = 0;
5282 return -1;
5283 }
5284
5285 bool error = false;
5286 int curSourceHeight = m_param->sourceHeight - m_conformanceWindow.bottomOffset;
5287 int curSourceWidth = m_param->sourceWidth - m_conformanceWindow.rightOffset;
5288
5289 X265_FREAD(&sourceWidth, sizeof(int), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(saveParam->sourceWidth));
5290 X265_FREAD(&sourceHeight, sizeof(int), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(saveParam->sourceHeight));
5291 X265_FREAD(&readValue, sizeof(int), 1, m_analysisFileIn, &(saveParam->maxCUSize));
5292
5293 bool isScaledRes = (2 * sourceHeight == curSourceHeight) && (2 * sourceWidth == curSourceWidth);
5294 if (!isScaledRes && (m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel > 1) && (sourceHeight != curSourceHeight
5295 || sourceWidth != curSourceWidth || readValue != (int)m_param->maxCUSize || m_param->scaleFactor))
5296 error = true;
5297 else if (isScaledRes && !m_param->scaleFactor)
5298 error = true;
5299 else if (isScaledRes && (int)m_param->maxCUSize == readValue)
5300 m_saveCTUSize = 1;
5301 else if (isScaledRes && (g_log2Size[m_param->maxCUSize] - g_log2Size[readValue]) != 1)
5302 error = true;
5303
5304 if (error)
5305 {
5306 x265_log(NULL, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Error reading analysis data. Incompatible option : <input-res / scale-factor / ctu> \n");
5307 m_aborted = true;
5308 return -1;
5309 }
5310 }
5311 return (count * sizeof(int));
5312
5313#undef X265_FREAD
5314#undef X265_PARAM_VALIDATE
5315}
5316
5317/* Toggle between two consecutive CTU rows. The save's CTU is copied
5318twice consecutively in the first and second CTU row of load*/
5319
5320int Encoder::getCUIndex(cuLocation* cuLoc, uint32_t* count, int bytes, int flag)
5321{
5322 int index = 0;
5323 cuLoc->switchCondition += bytes;
5324 int isBoundaryW = (*count % (m_param->num4x4Partitions * cuLoc->widthInCU) == 0);
5325
5326 /* Width boundary case :
5327 Skip to appropriate index when out of boundary cases occur
5328 Out of boundary may occur when the out of bound pixels along
5329 the width in low resoultion is greater than half of the maxCUSize */
5330 if (cuLoc->skipWidth && isBoundaryW)
5331 {
5332 if (flag)
5333 index++;
5334 else
5335 {
5336 /* Number of 4x4 blocks in out of bound region */
5337 int outOfBound = m_param->maxCUSize / 2;
5338 uint32_t sum = (uint32_t)pow((outOfBound >> 2), 2);
5339 index += sum;
5340 }
5341 cuLoc->switchCondition += m_param->num4x4Partitions;
5342 }
5343
5344 /* Completed writing 2 CTUs - move to the last remembered index of the next CTU row*/
5345 if (cuLoc->switchCondition == 2 * m_param->num4x4Partitions)
5346 {
5347 if (isBoundaryW)
5348 cuLoc->evenRowIndex = *count + (m_param->num4x4Partitions * cuLoc->widthInCU); // end of row - skip to the next even row
5349 else
5350 cuLoc->evenRowIndex = *count;
5351 *count = cuLoc->oddRowIndex;
5352
5353 /* Height boundary case :
5354 Skip to appropriate index when out of boundary cases occur
5355 Out of boundary may occur when the out of bound pixels along
5356 the height in low resoultion is greater than half of the maxCUSize */
5357 int isBoundaryH = (*count >= (m_param->num4x4Partitions * cuLoc->heightInCU * cuLoc->widthInCU));
5358 if (cuLoc->skipHeight && isBoundaryH)
5359 {
5360 if (flag)
5361 index += 2;
5362 else
5363 {
5364 int outOfBound = m_param->maxCUSize / 2;
5365 uint32_t sum = (uint32_t)(2 * pow((abs(outOfBound) >> 2), 2));
5366 index += sum;
5367 }
5368 *count = cuLoc->evenRowIndex;
5369 cuLoc->switchCondition = 0;
5370 }
5371 }
5372 /* Completed writing 4 CTUs - move to the last remembered index of
5373 the previous CTU row to copy the next save CTU's data*/
5374 else if (cuLoc->switchCondition == 4 * m_param->num4x4Partitions)
5375 {
5376 if (isBoundaryW)
5377 cuLoc->oddRowIndex = *count + (m_param->num4x4Partitions * cuLoc->widthInCU); // end of row - skip to the next odd row
5378 else
5379 cuLoc->oddRowIndex = *count;
5380 *count = cuLoc->evenRowIndex;
5381 cuLoc->switchCondition = 0;
5382 }
5383 return index;
5384}
5385
5386/* save load
5387 CTU0 CTU1 CTU2 CTU3
5388 2NxN 2Nx2N 2Nx2N 2Nx2N 2Nx2N
5389 NX2N 2Nx2N 2Nx2N 2Nx2N 2Nx2N
5390 2NxnU 2NxN 2NxN 2Nx2N 2Nx2N
5391 2NxnD 2Nx2N 2Nx2N 2NxN 2NxN
5392 nLx2N Nx2N 2Nx2N Nx2N 2Nx2N
5393 nRx2N 2Nx2N Nx2N 2Nx2N Nx2N
5394*/
5395int Encoder::getPuShape(puOrientation* puOrient, int partSize, int numCTU)
5396{
5397 puOrient->isRect = true;
5398 if (partSize == SIZE_Nx2N)
5399 puOrient->isVert = true;
5400 if (partSize >= SIZE_2NxnU) // All AMP modes
5401 {
5402 puOrient->isAmp = true;
5403 puOrient->isRect = false;
5404 if (partSize == SIZE_2NxnD && numCTU > 1)
5405 return SIZE_2NxN;
5406 else if (partSize == SIZE_2NxnU && numCTU < 2)
5407 return SIZE_2NxN;
5408 else if (partSize == SIZE_nLx2N)
5409 {
5410 puOrient->isVert = true;
5411 if (!(numCTU % 2))
5412 return SIZE_Nx2N;
5413 }
5414 else if (partSize == SIZE_nRx2N)
5415 {
5416 puOrient->isVert = true;
5417 if (numCTU % 2)
5418 return SIZE_Nx2N;
5419 }
5420 }
5421 return SIZE_2Nx2N;
5422}
5423void Encoder::computeDistortionOffset(x265_analysis_data* analysis)
5424{
5425 x265_analysis_distortion_data *distortionData = analysis->distortionData;
5426
5427 double sum = 0.0, sqrSum = 0.0;
5428 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < analysis->numCUsInFrame; ++i)
5429 {
5430 distortionData->scaledDistortion[i] = X265_LOG2(X265_MAX(distortionData->ctuDistortion[i], 1));
5431 sum += distortionData->scaledDistortion[i];
5432 sqrSum += distortionData->scaledDistortion[i] * distortionData->scaledDistortion[i];
5433 }
5434 double avg = sum / analysis->numCUsInFrame;
5435 distortionData->sdDistortion = pow(((sqrSum / analysis->numCUsInFrame) - (avg * avg)), 0.5);
5436 distortionData->averageDistortion = avg;
5437 distortionData->highDistortionCtuCount = distortionData->lowDistortionCtuCount = 0;
5438 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < analysis->numCUsInFrame; ++i)
5439 {
5440 distortionData->threshold[i] = distortionData->scaledDistortion[i] / distortionData->averageDistortion;
5441 distortionData->offset[i] = (distortionData->averageDistortion - distortionData->scaledDistortion[i]) / distortionData->sdDistortion;
5442 if (distortionData->threshold[i] < 0.9 && distortionData->offset[i] >= 1)
5443 distortionData->lowDistortionCtuCount++;
5444 else if (distortionData->threshold[i] > 1.1 && distortionData->offset[i] <= -1)
5445 distortionData->highDistortionCtuCount++;
5446 }
5447}
5448void Encoder::readAnalysisFile(x265_analysis_data* analysis, int curPoc, int sliceType)
5449{
5450
5451#define X265_FREAD(val, size, readSize, fileOffset)\
5452 if (fread(val, size, readSize, fileOffset) != readSize)\
5453 {\
5454 x265_log(NULL, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Error reading analysis 2 pass data\n"); \
5455 x265_alloc_analysis_data(m_param, analysis); \
5456 m_aborted = true; \
5457 return; \
5458}\
5459
5460 uint32_t depthBytes = 0;
5461 int poc; uint32_t frameRecordSize;
5462 X265_FREAD(&frameRecordSize, sizeof(uint32_t), 1, m_analysisFileIn);
5463 X265_FREAD(&depthBytes, sizeof(uint32_t), 1, m_analysisFileIn);
5464 X265_FREAD(&poc, sizeof(int), 1, m_analysisFileIn);
5465
5466 if (poc != curPoc || feof(m_analysisFileIn))
5467 {
5468 x265_log(NULL, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Error reading analysis 2 pass data: Cannot find POC %d\n", curPoc);
5469 x265_free_analysis_data(m_param, analysis);
5470 return;
5471 }
5472 /* Now arrived at the right frame, read the record */
5473 analysis->frameRecordSize = frameRecordSize;
5474 uint8_t* tempBuf = NULL, *depthBuf = NULL;
5475 X265_FREAD((analysis->distortionData)->ctuDistortion, sizeof(sse_t), analysis->numCUsInFrame, m_analysisFileIn);
5476 tempBuf = X265_MALLOC(uint8_t, depthBytes);
5477 X265_FREAD(tempBuf, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn);
5478 depthBuf = tempBuf;
5479 x265_analysis_data *analysisData = (x265_analysis_data*)analysis;
5480 x265_analysis_intra_data *intraData = analysisData->intraData;
5481 x265_analysis_inter_data *interData = analysisData->interData;
5482
5483 computeDistortionOffset(analysis);
5484 size_t count = 0;
5485 for (uint32_t d = 0; d < depthBytes; d++)
5486 {
5487 int bytes = analysis->numPartitions >> (depthBuf[d] * 2);
5488 if (IS_X265_TYPE_I(sliceType))
5489 memset(&intraData->depth[count], depthBuf[d], bytes);
5490 else
5491 memset(&interData->depth[count], depthBuf[d], bytes);
5492 count += bytes;
5493 }
5494
5495
5496 if (!IS_X265_TYPE_I(sliceType))
5497 {
5498 MV *tempMVBuf[2], *MVBuf[2];
5499 int32_t *tempRefBuf, *refBuf;
5500 uint8_t *tempMvpBuf[2], *mvpBuf[2];
5501 uint8_t* tempModeBuf = NULL, *modeBuf = NULL;
5502 int numDir = sliceType == X265_TYPE_P ? 1 : 2;
5503 tempRefBuf = X265_MALLOC(int32_t, numDir * depthBytes);
5504
5505 for (int i = 0; i < numDir; i++)
5506 {
5507 tempMVBuf[i] = X265_MALLOC(MV, depthBytes);
5508 X265_FREAD(tempMVBuf[i], sizeof(MV), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn);
5509 MVBuf[i] = tempMVBuf[i];
5510 tempMvpBuf[i] = X265_MALLOC(uint8_t, depthBytes);
5511 X265_FREAD(tempMvpBuf[i], sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn);
5512 mvpBuf[i] = tempMvpBuf[i];
5513 X265_FREAD(&tempRefBuf[i*depthBytes], sizeof(int32_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn);
5514 }
5515 refBuf = tempRefBuf;
5516 tempModeBuf = X265_MALLOC(uint8_t, depthBytes);
5517 X265_FREAD(tempModeBuf, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileIn);
5518 modeBuf = tempModeBuf;
5519
5520 count = 0;
5521
5522 for (uint32_t d = 0; d < depthBytes; d++)
5523 {
5524 size_t bytes = analysis->numPartitions >> (depthBuf[d] * 2);
5525 for (int i = 0; i < numDir; i++)
5526 {
5527 int32_t* ref = &(analysis->interData)->ref[i * analysis->numPartitions * analysis->numCUsInFrame];
5528 for (size_t j = count, k = 0; k < bytes; j++, k++)
5529 {
5530 memcpy(&(analysis->interData)->mv[i][j], MVBuf[i] + d, sizeof(MV));
5531 memcpy(&(analysis->interData)->mvpIdx[i][j], mvpBuf[i] + d, sizeof(uint8_t));
5532 memcpy(&ref[j], refBuf + (i * depthBytes) + d, sizeof(int32_t));
5533 }
5534 }
5535 memset(&(analysis->interData)->modes[count], modeBuf[d], bytes);
5536 count += bytes;
5537 }
5538
5539 for (int i = 0; i < numDir; i++)
5540 {
5541 X265_FREE(tempMVBuf[i]);
5542 X265_FREE(tempMvpBuf[i]);
5543 }
5544 X265_FREE(tempRefBuf);
5545 X265_FREE(tempModeBuf);
5546 }
5547 X265_FREE(tempBuf);
5548
5549#undef X265_FREAD
5550}
5551
5552void Encoder::copyDistortionData(x265_analysis_data* analysis, FrameData &curEncData)
5553{
5554 for (uint32_t cuAddr = 0; cuAddr < analysis->numCUsInFrame; cuAddr++)
5555 {
5556 uint8_t depth = 0;
5557 CUData* ctu = curEncData.getPicCTU(cuAddr);
5558 x265_analysis_distortion_data *distortionData = (x265_analysis_distortion_data *)analysis->distortionData;
5559 distortionData->ctuDistortion[cuAddr] = 0;
5560 for (uint32_t absPartIdx = 0; absPartIdx < ctu->m_numPartitions;)
5561 {
5562 depth = ctu->m_cuDepth[absPartIdx];
5563 distortionData->ctuDistortion[cuAddr] += ctu->m_distortion[absPartIdx];
5564 absPartIdx += ctu->m_numPartitions >> (depth * 2);
5565 }
5566 }
5567}
5568
5569void Encoder::writeAnalysisFile(x265_analysis_data* analysis, FrameData &curEncData)
5570{
5571
5572#define X265_FWRITE(val, size, writeSize, fileOffset)\
5573 if (fwrite(val, size, writeSize, fileOffset) < writeSize)\
5574 {\
5575 x265_log(NULL, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Error writing analysis data\n");\
5576 x265_free_analysis_data(m_param, analysis);\
5577 m_aborted = true;\
5578 return;\
5579 }\
5580
5581 uint32_t depthBytes = 0;
5582 uint32_t numDir, numPlanes;
5583 bool bIntraInInter = false;
5584
5585 if (!analysis->poc)
5586 {
5587 if (validateAnalysisData(&analysis->saveParam, 1) == -1)
5588 {
5589 m_aborted = true;
5590 return;
5591 }
5592 }
5593
5594 /* calculate frameRecordSize */
5595 analysis->frameRecordSize = sizeof(analysis->frameRecordSize) + sizeof(depthBytes) + sizeof(analysis->poc) + sizeof(analysis->sliceType) +
5596 sizeof(analysis->numCUsInFrame) + sizeof(analysis->numPartitions) + sizeof(analysis->bScenecut) + sizeof(analysis->satdCost);
5597 if (m_param->bHistBasedSceneCut)
5598 {
5599 analysis->frameRecordSize += sizeof(analysis->edgeHist);
5600 analysis->frameRecordSize += sizeof(int32_t) * HISTOGRAM_BINS;
5601 if (m_param->internalCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
5602 {
5603 analysis->frameRecordSize += sizeof(int32_t) * HISTOGRAM_BINS;
5604 analysis->frameRecordSize += sizeof(int32_t) * HISTOGRAM_BINS;
5605 }
5606 }
5607
5608 if (analysis->sliceType > X265_TYPE_I)
5609 {
5610 numDir = (analysis->sliceType == X265_TYPE_P) ? 1 : 2;
5611 numPlanes = m_param->internalCsp == X265_CSP_I400 ? 1 : 3;
5612 analysis->frameRecordSize += sizeof(WeightParam) * numPlanes * numDir;
5613 }
5614
5615 if (m_param->ctuDistortionRefine == CTU_DISTORTION_INTERNAL)
5616 {
5617 copyDistortionData(analysis, curEncData);
5618 analysis->frameRecordSize += analysis->numCUsInFrame * sizeof(sse_t);
5619 }
5620
5621 if (m_param->analysisSaveReuseLevel > 1)
5622 {
5623
5624 if (analysis->sliceType == X265_TYPE_IDR || analysis->sliceType == X265_TYPE_I)
5625 {
5626 for (uint32_t cuAddr = 0; cuAddr < analysis->numCUsInFrame; cuAddr++)
5627 {
5628 uint8_t depth = 0;
5629 uint8_t mode = 0;
5630 uint8_t partSize = 0;
5631
5632 CUData* ctu = curEncData.getPicCTU(cuAddr);
5633 x265_analysis_intra_data* intraDataCTU = analysis->intraData;
5634 int baseQP = (int)(ctu->m_encData->m_cuStat[cuAddr].baseQp + 0.5);
5635
5636 for (uint32_t absPartIdx = 0; absPartIdx < ctu->m_numPartitions; depthBytes++)
5637 {
5638 depth = ctu->m_cuDepth[absPartIdx];
5639 intraDataCTU->depth[depthBytes] = depth;
5640
5641 mode = ctu->m_chromaIntraDir[absPartIdx];
5642 intraDataCTU->chromaModes[depthBytes] = mode;
5643
5644 partSize = ctu->m_partSize[absPartIdx];
5645 intraDataCTU->partSizes[depthBytes] = partSize;
5646
5647 if (m_param->rc.cuTree)
5648 intraDataCTU->cuQPOff[depthBytes] = (int8_t)(ctu->m_qpAnalysis[absPartIdx] - baseQP);
5649 absPartIdx += ctu->m_numPartitions >> (depth * 2);
5650 }
5651 memcpy(&intraDataCTU->modes[ctu->m_cuAddr * ctu->m_numPartitions], ctu->m_lumaIntraDir, sizeof(uint8_t)* ctu->m_numPartitions);
5652 }
5653 }
5654 else
5655 {
5656 bIntraInInter = (analysis->sliceType == X265_TYPE_P || m_param->bIntraInBFrames);
5657 for (uint32_t cuAddr = 0; cuAddr < analysis->numCUsInFrame; cuAddr++)
5658 {
5659 uint8_t depth = 0;
5660 uint8_t predMode = 0;
5661 uint8_t partSize = 0;
5662
5663 CUData* ctu = curEncData.getPicCTU(cuAddr);
5664 x265_analysis_inter_data* interDataCTU = analysis->interData;
5665 x265_analysis_intra_data* intraDataCTU = analysis->intraData;
5666 int baseQP = (int)(ctu->m_encData->m_cuStat[cuAddr].baseQp + 0.5);
5667
5668 for (uint32_t absPartIdx = 0; absPartIdx < ctu->m_numPartitions; depthBytes++)
5669 {
5670 depth = ctu->m_cuDepth[absPartIdx];
5671 interDataCTU->depth[depthBytes] = depth;
5672
5673 predMode = ctu->m_predMode[absPartIdx];
5674 if (m_param->analysisSaveReuseLevel != 10 && ctu->m_refIdx[1][absPartIdx] != -1)
5675 predMode = 4; // used as indicator if the block is coded as bidir
5676
5677 interDataCTU->modes[depthBytes] = predMode;
5678 if (m_param->rc.cuTree)
5679 interDataCTU->cuQPOff[depthBytes] = (int8_t)(ctu->m_qpAnalysis[absPartIdx] - baseQP);
5680
5681 if (m_param->analysisSaveReuseLevel > 4)
5682 {
5683 partSize = ctu->m_partSize[absPartIdx];
5684 interDataCTU->partSize[depthBytes] = partSize;
5685
5686 /* Store per PU data */
5687 uint32_t numPU = (predMode == MODE_INTRA) ? 1 : nbPartsTable[(int)partSize];
5688 for (uint32_t puIdx = 0; puIdx < numPU; puIdx++)
5689 {
5690 uint32_t puabsPartIdx = ctu->getPUOffset(puIdx, absPartIdx) + absPartIdx;
5691 if (puIdx) depthBytes++;
5692 interDataCTU->mergeFlag[depthBytes] = ctu->m_mergeFlag[puabsPartIdx];
5693
5694 if (m_param->analysisSaveReuseLevel == 10)
5695 {
5696 interDataCTU->interDir[depthBytes] = ctu->m_interDir[puabsPartIdx];
5697 for (uint32_t dir = 0; dir < numDir; dir++)
5698 {
5699 interDataCTU->mvpIdx[dir][depthBytes] = ctu->m_mvpIdx[dir][puabsPartIdx];
5700 interDataCTU->refIdx[dir][depthBytes] = ctu->m_refIdx[dir][puabsPartIdx];
5701 interDataCTU->mv[dir][depthBytes].word = ctu->m_mv[dir][puabsPartIdx].word;
5702 }
5703 }
5704 }
5705 if (m_param->analysisSaveReuseLevel == 10 && bIntraInInter)
5706 intraDataCTU->chromaModes[depthBytes] = ctu->m_chromaIntraDir[absPartIdx];
5707 }
5708 absPartIdx += ctu->m_numPartitions >> (depth * 2);
5709 }
5710 if (m_param->analysisSaveReuseLevel == 10 && bIntraInInter)
5711 memcpy(&intraDataCTU->modes[ctu->m_cuAddr * ctu->m_numPartitions], ctu->m_lumaIntraDir, sizeof(uint8_t)* ctu->m_numPartitions);
5712 }
5713 }
5714
5715 if ((analysis->sliceType == X265_TYPE_IDR || analysis->sliceType == X265_TYPE_I) && m_param->rc.cuTree)
5716 analysis->frameRecordSize += sizeof(uint8_t)* analysis->numCUsInFrame * analysis->numPartitions + depthBytes * 3 + (sizeof(int8_t) * depthBytes);
5717 else if (analysis->sliceType == X265_TYPE_IDR || analysis->sliceType == X265_TYPE_I)
5718 analysis->frameRecordSize += sizeof(uint8_t)* analysis->numCUsInFrame * analysis->numPartitions + depthBytes * 3;
5719 else
5720 {
5721 /* Add sizeof depth, modes, partSize, cuQPOffset, mergeFlag */
5722 analysis->frameRecordSize += depthBytes * 2;
5723 if (m_param->rc.cuTree)
5724 analysis->frameRecordSize += (sizeof(int8_t) * depthBytes);
5725 if (m_param->analysisSaveReuseLevel > 4)
5726 analysis->frameRecordSize += (depthBytes * 2);
5727
5728 if (m_param->analysisSaveReuseLevel == 10)
5729 {
5730 /* Add Size of interDir, mvpIdx, refIdx, mv, luma and chroma modes */
5731 analysis->frameRecordSize += depthBytes;
5732 analysis->frameRecordSize += sizeof(uint8_t)* depthBytes * numDir;
5733 analysis->frameRecordSize += sizeof(int8_t)* depthBytes * numDir;
5734 analysis->frameRecordSize += sizeof(MV)* depthBytes * numDir;
5735 if (bIntraInInter)
5736 analysis->frameRecordSize += sizeof(uint8_t)* analysis->numCUsInFrame * analysis->numPartitions + depthBytes;
5737 }
5738 else
5739 analysis->frameRecordSize += sizeof(int32_t)* analysis->numCUsInFrame * X265_MAX_PRED_MODE_PER_CTU * numDir;
5740 }
5741 analysis->depthBytes = depthBytes;
5742 }
5743
5744 if (!m_param->bUseAnalysisFile)
5745 return;
5746
5747 X265_FWRITE(&analysis->frameRecordSize, sizeof(uint32_t), 1, m_analysisFileOut);
5748 X265_FWRITE(&depthBytes, sizeof(uint32_t), 1, m_analysisFileOut);
5749 X265_FWRITE(&analysis->poc, sizeof(int), 1, m_analysisFileOut);
5750 X265_FWRITE(&analysis->sliceType, sizeof(int), 1, m_analysisFileOut);
5751 X265_FWRITE(&analysis->bScenecut, sizeof(int), 1, m_analysisFileOut);
5752 if (m_param->bHistBasedSceneCut)
5753 {
5754 X265_FWRITE(&analysis->edgeHist, sizeof(int32_t), EDGE_BINS, m_analysisFileOut);
5755 X265_FWRITE(&analysis->yuvHist[0], sizeof(int32_t), HISTOGRAM_BINS, m_analysisFileOut);
5756 if (m_param->internalCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
5757 {
5758 X265_FWRITE(&analysis->yuvHist[1], sizeof(int32_t), HISTOGRAM_BINS, m_analysisFileOut);
5759 X265_FWRITE(&analysis->yuvHist[2], sizeof(int32_t), HISTOGRAM_BINS, m_analysisFileOut);
5760 }
5761 }
5762
5763 X265_FWRITE(&analysis->satdCost, sizeof(int64_t), 1, m_analysisFileOut);
5764 X265_FWRITE(&analysis->numCUsInFrame, sizeof(int), 1, m_analysisFileOut);
5765 X265_FWRITE(&analysis->numPartitions, sizeof(int), 1, m_analysisFileOut);
5766 if (m_param->ctuDistortionRefine == CTU_DISTORTION_INTERNAL)
5767 X265_FWRITE((analysis->distortionData)->ctuDistortion, sizeof(sse_t), analysis->numCUsInFrame, m_analysisFileOut);
5768 if (analysis->sliceType > X265_TYPE_I)
5769 X265_FWRITE((WeightParam*)analysis->wt, sizeof(WeightParam), numPlanes * numDir, m_analysisFileOut);
5770
5771 if (m_param->analysisSaveReuseLevel < 2)
5772 return;
5773
5774 if (analysis->sliceType == X265_TYPE_IDR || analysis->sliceType == X265_TYPE_I)
5775 {
5776 X265_FWRITE((analysis->intraData)->depth, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileOut);
5777 X265_FWRITE((analysis->intraData)->chromaModes, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileOut);
5778 X265_FWRITE((analysis->intraData)->partSizes, sizeof(char), depthBytes, m_analysisFileOut);
5779 if (m_param->rc.cuTree)
5780 X265_FWRITE((analysis->intraData)->cuQPOff, sizeof(int8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileOut);
5781 X265_FWRITE((analysis->intraData)->modes, sizeof(uint8_t), analysis->numCUsInFrame * analysis->numPartitions, m_analysisFileOut);
5782 }
5783 else
5784 {
5785 X265_FWRITE((analysis->interData)->depth, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileOut);
5786 X265_FWRITE((analysis->interData)->modes, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileOut);
5787 if (m_param->rc.cuTree)
5788 X265_FWRITE((analysis->interData)->cuQPOff, sizeof(int8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileOut);
5789 if (m_param->analysisSaveReuseLevel > 4)
5790 {
5791 X265_FWRITE((analysis->interData)->partSize, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileOut);
5792 X265_FWRITE((analysis->interData)->mergeFlag, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileOut);
5793 if (m_param->analysisSaveReuseLevel == 10)
5794 {
5795 X265_FWRITE((analysis->interData)->interDir, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileOut);
5796 if (bIntraInInter) X265_FWRITE((analysis->intraData)->chromaModes, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileOut);
5797 for (uint32_t dir = 0; dir < numDir; dir++)
5798 {
5799 X265_FWRITE((analysis->interData)->mvpIdx[dir], sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileOut);
5800 X265_FWRITE((analysis->interData)->refIdx[dir], sizeof(int8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileOut);
5801 X265_FWRITE((analysis->interData)->mv[dir], sizeof(MV), depthBytes, m_analysisFileOut);
5802 }
5803 if (bIntraInInter)
5804 X265_FWRITE((analysis->intraData)->modes, sizeof(uint8_t), analysis->numCUsInFrame * analysis->numPartitions, m_analysisFileOut);
5805 }
5806 }
5807 if (m_param->analysisSaveReuseLevel != 10)
5808 X265_FWRITE((analysis->interData)->ref, sizeof(int32_t), analysis->numCUsInFrame * X265_MAX_PRED_MODE_PER_CTU * numDir, m_analysisFileOut);
5809
5810 }
5811#undef X265_FWRITE
5812}
5813
5814void Encoder::writeAnalysisFileRefine(x265_analysis_data* analysis, FrameData &curEncData)
5815{
5816#define X265_FWRITE(val, size, writeSize, fileOffset)\
5817 if (fwrite(val, size, writeSize, fileOffset) < writeSize)\
5818 {\
5819 x265_log(NULL, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Error writing analysis 2 pass data\n"); \
5820 x265_free_analysis_data(m_param, analysis); \
5821 m_aborted = true; \
5822 return; \
5823}\
5824
5825 uint32_t depthBytes = 0;
5826 x265_analysis_data *analysisData = (x265_analysis_data*)analysis;
5827 x265_analysis_intra_data *intraData = analysisData->intraData;
5828 x265_analysis_inter_data *interData = analysisData->interData;
5829 x265_analysis_distortion_data *distortionData = analysisData->distortionData;
5830
5831 copyDistortionData(analysis, curEncData);
5832
5833 if (curEncData.m_slice->m_sliceType == I_SLICE)
5834 {
5835 for (uint32_t cuAddr = 0; cuAddr < analysis->numCUsInFrame; cuAddr++)
5836 {
5837 uint8_t depth = 0;
5838 CUData* ctu = curEncData.getPicCTU(cuAddr);
5839 for (uint32_t absPartIdx = 0; absPartIdx < ctu->m_numPartitions; depthBytes++)
5840 {
5841 depth = ctu->m_cuDepth[absPartIdx];
5842 intraData->depth[depthBytes] = depth;
5843 absPartIdx += ctu->m_numPartitions >> (depth * 2);
5844 }
5845 }
5846 }
5847
5848 else
5849 {
5850 int32_t* ref[2];
5851 ref[0] = (analysis->interData)->ref;
5852 ref[1] = &(analysis->interData)->ref[analysis->numPartitions * analysis->numCUsInFrame];
5853 depthBytes = 0;
5854 for (uint32_t cuAddr = 0; cuAddr < analysis->numCUsInFrame; cuAddr++)
5855 {
5856 uint8_t depth = 0;
5857 uint8_t predMode = 0;
5858
5859 CUData* ctu = curEncData.getPicCTU(cuAddr);
5860 for (uint32_t absPartIdx = 0; absPartIdx < ctu->m_numPartitions; depthBytes++)
5861 {
5862 depth = ctu->m_cuDepth[absPartIdx];
5863 interData->depth[depthBytes] = depth;
5864 interData->mv[0][depthBytes].word = ctu->m_mv[0][absPartIdx].word;
5865 interData->mvpIdx[0][depthBytes] = ctu->m_mvpIdx[0][absPartIdx];
5866 ref[0][depthBytes] = ctu->m_refIdx[0][absPartIdx];
5867 predMode = ctu->m_predMode[absPartIdx];
5868 if (ctu->m_refIdx[1][absPartIdx] != -1)
5869 {
5870 interData->mv[1][depthBytes].word = ctu->m_mv[1][absPartIdx].word;
5871 interData->mvpIdx[1][depthBytes] = ctu->m_mvpIdx[1][absPartIdx];
5872 ref[1][depthBytes] = ctu->m_refIdx[1][absPartIdx];
5873 predMode = 4; // used as indiacator if the block is coded as bidir
5874 }
5875 interData->modes[depthBytes] = predMode;
5876
5877 absPartIdx += ctu->m_numPartitions >> (depth * 2);
5878 }
5879 }
5880 }
5881
5882 /* calculate frameRecordSize */
5883 analysis->frameRecordSize = sizeof(analysis->frameRecordSize) + sizeof(depthBytes) + sizeof(analysis->poc);
5884 analysis->frameRecordSize += depthBytes * sizeof(uint8_t);
5885 analysis->frameRecordSize += analysis->numCUsInFrame * sizeof(sse_t);
5886 if (curEncData.m_slice->m_sliceType != I_SLICE)
5887 {
5888 int numDir = (curEncData.m_slice->m_sliceType == P_SLICE) ? 1 : 2;
5889 analysis->frameRecordSize += depthBytes * sizeof(MV) * numDir;
5890 analysis->frameRecordSize += depthBytes * sizeof(int32_t) * numDir;
5891 analysis->frameRecordSize += depthBytes * sizeof(uint8_t) * numDir;
5892 analysis->frameRecordSize += depthBytes * sizeof(uint8_t);
5893 }
5894 X265_FWRITE(&analysis->frameRecordSize, sizeof(uint32_t), 1, m_analysisFileOut);
5895 X265_FWRITE(&depthBytes, sizeof(uint32_t), 1, m_analysisFileOut);
5896 X265_FWRITE(&analysis->poc, sizeof(uint32_t), 1, m_analysisFileOut);
5897 X265_FWRITE(distortionData->ctuDistortion, sizeof(sse_t), analysis->numCUsInFrame, m_analysisFileOut);
5898 if (curEncData.m_slice->m_sliceType == I_SLICE)
5899 {
5900 X265_FWRITE((analysis->intraData)->depth, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileOut);
5901 }
5902 else
5903 {
5904 X265_FWRITE((analysis->interData)->depth, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileOut);
5905 }
5906 if (curEncData.m_slice->m_sliceType != I_SLICE)
5907 {
5908 int numDir = curEncData.m_slice->m_sliceType == P_SLICE ? 1 : 2;
5909 for (int i = 0; i < numDir; i++)
5910 {
5911 int32_t* ref = &(analysis->interData)->ref[i * analysis->numPartitions * analysis->numCUsInFrame];
5912 X265_FWRITE(interData->mv[i], sizeof(MV), depthBytes, m_analysisFileOut);
5913 X265_FWRITE(interData->mvpIdx[i], sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileOut);
5914 X265_FWRITE(ref, sizeof(int32_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileOut);
5915 }
5916 X265_FWRITE((analysis->interData)->modes, sizeof(uint8_t), depthBytes, m_analysisFileOut);
5917 }
5918#undef X265_FWRITE
5919}
5920
5921void Encoder::printReconfigureParams()
5922{
5923 if (!(m_reconfigure || m_reconfigureRc))
5924 return;
5925 x265_param* oldParam = m_param;
5926 x265_param* newParam = m_latestParam;
5927
5928 x265_log(newParam, X265_LOG_DEBUG, "Reconfigured param options, input Frame: %d\n", m_pocLast + 1);
5929
5930 char tmp[60];
5931#define TOOLCMP(COND1, COND2, STR) if (COND1 != COND2) { sprintf(tmp, STR, COND1, COND2); x265_log(newParam, X265_LOG_DEBUG, tmp); }
5932 TOOLCMP(oldParam->maxNumReferences, newParam->maxNumReferences, "ref=%d to %d\n");
5933 TOOLCMP(oldParam->bEnableFastIntra, newParam->bEnableFastIntra, "fast-intra=%d to %d\n");
5934 TOOLCMP(oldParam->bEnableEarlySkip, newParam->bEnableEarlySkip, "early-skip=%d to %d\n");
5935 TOOLCMP(oldParam->recursionSkipMode, newParam->recursionSkipMode, "rskip=%d to %d\n");
5936 TOOLCMP(oldParam->searchMethod, newParam->searchMethod, "me=%d to %d\n");
5937 TOOLCMP(oldParam->searchRange, newParam->searchRange, "merange=%d to %d\n");
5938 TOOLCMP(oldParam->subpelRefine, newParam->subpelRefine, "subme= %d to %d\n");
5939 TOOLCMP(oldParam->rdLevel, newParam->rdLevel, "rd=%d to %d\n");
5940 TOOLCMP(oldParam->rdoqLevel, newParam->rdoqLevel, "rdoq=%d to %d\n" );
5941 TOOLCMP(oldParam->bEnableRectInter, newParam->bEnableRectInter, "rect=%d to %d\n");
5942 TOOLCMP(oldParam->maxNumMergeCand, newParam->maxNumMergeCand, "max-merge=%d to %d\n");
5943 TOOLCMP(oldParam->bIntraInBFrames, newParam->bIntraInBFrames, "b-intra=%d to %d\n");
5944 TOOLCMP(oldParam->scalingLists, newParam->scalingLists, "scalinglists=%s to %s\n");
5945 TOOLCMP(oldParam->rc.vbvMaxBitrate, newParam->rc.vbvMaxBitrate, "vbv-maxrate=%d to %d\n");
5946 TOOLCMP(oldParam->rc.vbvBufferSize, newParam->rc.vbvBufferSize, "vbv-bufsize=%d to %d\n");
5947 TOOLCMP(oldParam->rc.bitrate, newParam->rc.bitrate, "bitrate=%d to %d\n");
5948 TOOLCMP(oldParam->rc.rfConstant, newParam->rc.rfConstant, "crf=%f to %f\n");
5949}
5950
5951void Encoder::readUserSeiFile(x265_sei_payload& seiMsg, int curPoc)
5952{
5953 char line[1024];
5954 while (fgets(line, sizeof(line), m_naluFile))
5955 {
5956 int poc = atoi(strtok(line, " "));
5957 char *prefix = strtok(NULL, " ");
5958 int nalType = atoi(strtok(NULL, "/"));
5959 int payloadType = atoi(strtok(NULL, " "));
5960 char *base64Encode = strtok(NULL, "\n");
5961 int base64EncodeLength = (int)strlen(base64Encode);
5962 char *base64Decode = SEI::base64Decode(base64Encode, base64EncodeLength);
5963 if (nalType == NAL_UNIT_PREFIX_SEI && (!strcmp(prefix, "PREFIX")))
5964 {
5965 int currentPOC = curPoc;
5966 if (currentPOC == poc)
5967 {
5968 seiMsg.payloadSize = (base64EncodeLength / 4) * 3;
5969 seiMsg.payload = (uint8_t*)x265_malloc(sizeof(uint8_t) * seiMsg.payloadSize);
5970 if (!seiMsg.payload)
5971 {
5972 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Unable to allocate memory for SEI payload\n");
5973 break;
5974 }
5975 if (payloadType == 4)
5976 seiMsg.payloadType = USER_DATA_REGISTERED_ITU_T_T35;
5977 else if (payloadType == 5)
5978 seiMsg.payloadType = USER_DATA_UNREGISTERED;
5979 else
5980 {
5981 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Unsupported SEI payload Type for frame %d\n", poc);
5982 break;
5983 }
5984 memcpy(seiMsg.payload, base64Decode, seiMsg.payloadSize);
5985 break;
5986 }
5987 }
5988 else
5989 {
5990 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_WARNING, "SEI message for frame %d is not inserted. Will support only PREFIX SEI messages.\n", poc);
5991 break;
5992 }
5993 }
5994}
5995
5996bool Encoder::computeSPSRPSIndex()
5997{
5998 RPS* rpsInSPS = m_sps.spsrps;
5999 int* rpsNumInPSP = &m_sps.spsrpsNum;
6000 int beginNum = m_sps.numGOPBegin;
6001 int endNum;
6002 RPS* rpsInRec;
6003 RPS* rpsInIdxList;
6004 RPS* thisRpsInSPS;
6005 RPS* thisRpsInList;
6006 RPSListNode* headRpsIdxList = NULL;
6007 RPSListNode* tailRpsIdxList = NULL;
6008 RPSListNode* rpsIdxListIter = NULL;
6009 RateControlEntry *rce2Pass = m_rateControl->m_rce2Pass;
6010 int numEntries = m_rateControl->m_numEntries;
6011 RateControlEntry *rce;
6012 int idx = 0;
6013 int pos = 0;
6014 int resultIdx[64];
6015 memset(rpsInSPS, 0, sizeof(RPS) * MAX_NUM_SHORT_TERM_RPS);
6016
6017 // find out all RPS date in current GOP
6018 beginNum++;
6019 endNum = beginNum;
6020 if (!m_param->bRepeatHeaders)
6021 {
6022 endNum = numEntries;
6023 }
6024 else
6025 {
6026 while (endNum < numEntries)
6027 {
6028 rce = &rce2Pass[endNum];
6029 if (rce->sliceType == I_SLICE)
6030 {
6031 if (m_param->keyframeMin && (endNum - beginNum + 1 < m_param->keyframeMin))
6032 {
6033 endNum++;
6034 continue;
6035 }
6036 break;
6037 }
6038 endNum++;
6039 }
6040 }
6041 m_sps.numGOPBegin = endNum;
6042
6043 // find out all kinds of RPS
6044 for (int i = beginNum; i < endNum; i++)
6045 {
6046 rce = &rce2Pass[i];
6047 rpsInRec = &rce->rpsData;
6048 rpsIdxListIter = headRpsIdxList;
6049 // i frame don't recode RPS info
6050 if (rce->sliceType != I_SLICE)
6051 {
6052 while (rpsIdxListIter)
6053 {
6054 rpsInIdxList = rpsIdxListIter->rps;
6055 if (rpsInRec->numberOfPictures == rpsInIdxList->numberOfPictures
6056 && rpsInRec->numberOfNegativePictures == rpsInIdxList->numberOfNegativePictures
6057 && rpsInRec->numberOfPositivePictures == rpsInIdxList->numberOfPositivePictures)
6058 {
6059 for (pos = 0; pos < rpsInRec->numberOfPictures; pos++)
6060 {
6061 if (rpsInRec->deltaPOC[pos] != rpsInIdxList->deltaPOC[pos]
6062 || rpsInRec->bUsed[pos] != rpsInIdxList->bUsed[pos])
6063 break;
6064 }
6065 if (pos == rpsInRec->numberOfPictures) // if this type of RPS has exist
6066 {
6067 rce->rpsIdx = rpsIdxListIter->idx;
6068 rpsIdxListIter->count++;
6069 // sort RPS type link after reset RPS type count.
6070 RPSListNode* next = rpsIdxListIter->next;
6071 RPSListNode* prior = rpsIdxListIter->prior;
6072 RPSListNode* iter = prior;
6073 if (iter)
6074 {
6075 while (iter)
6076 {
6077 if (iter->count > rpsIdxListIter->count)
6078 break;
6079 iter = iter->prior;
6080 }
6081 if (iter)
6082 {
6083 prior->next = next;
6084 if (next)
6085 next->prior = prior;
6086 else
6087 tailRpsIdxList = prior;
6088 rpsIdxListIter->next = iter->next;
6089 rpsIdxListIter->prior = iter;
6090 iter->next->prior = rpsIdxListIter;
6091 iter->next = rpsIdxListIter;
6092 }
6093 else
6094 {
6095 prior->next = next;
6096 if (next)
6097 next->prior = prior;
6098 else
6099 tailRpsIdxList = prior;
6100 headRpsIdxList->prior = rpsIdxListIter;
6101 rpsIdxListIter->next = headRpsIdxList;
6102 rpsIdxListIter->prior = NULL;
6103 headRpsIdxList = rpsIdxListIter;
6104 }
6105 }
6106 break;
6107 }
6108 }
6109 rpsIdxListIter = rpsIdxListIter->next;
6110 }
6111 if (!rpsIdxListIter) // add new type of RPS
6112 {
6113 RPSListNode* newIdxNode = new RPSListNode();
6114 if (newIdxNode == NULL)
6115 goto fail;
6116 newIdxNode->rps = rpsInRec;
6117 newIdxNode->idx = idx++;
6118 newIdxNode->count = 1;
6119 newIdxNode->next = NULL;
6120 newIdxNode->prior = NULL;
6121 if (!tailRpsIdxList)
6122 tailRpsIdxList = headRpsIdxList = newIdxNode;
6123 else
6124 {
6125 tailRpsIdxList->next = newIdxNode;
6126 newIdxNode->prior = tailRpsIdxList;
6127 tailRpsIdxList = newIdxNode;
6128 }
6129 rce->rpsIdx = newIdxNode->idx;
6130 }
6131 }
6132 else
6133 {
6134 rce->rpsIdx = -1;
6135 }
6136 }
6137
6138 // get commonly RPS set
6139 memset(resultIdx, 0, sizeof(resultIdx));
6140 if (idx > MAX_NUM_SHORT_TERM_RPS)
6141 idx = MAX_NUM_SHORT_TERM_RPS;
6142
6143 *rpsNumInPSP = idx;
6144 rpsIdxListIter = headRpsIdxList;
6145 for (int i = 0; i < idx; i++)
6146 {
6147 resultIdx[i] = rpsIdxListIter->idx;
6148 m_rpsInSpsCount += rpsIdxListIter->count;
6149 thisRpsInSPS = rpsInSPS + i;
6150 thisRpsInList = rpsIdxListIter->rps;
6151 thisRpsInSPS->numberOfPictures = thisRpsInList->numberOfPictures;
6152 thisRpsInSPS->numberOfNegativePictures = thisRpsInList->numberOfNegativePictures;
6153 thisRpsInSPS->numberOfPositivePictures = thisRpsInList->numberOfPositivePictures;
6154 for (pos = 0; pos < thisRpsInList->numberOfPictures; pos++)
6155 {
6156 thisRpsInSPS->deltaPOC[pos] = thisRpsInList->deltaPOC[pos];
6157 thisRpsInSPS->bUsed[pos] = thisRpsInList->bUsed[pos];
6158 }
6159 rpsIdxListIter = rpsIdxListIter->next;
6160 }
6161
6162 //reset every frame's RPS index
6163 for (int i = beginNum; i < endNum; i++)
6164 {
6165 int j;
6166 rce = &rce2Pass[i];
6167 for (j = 0; j < idx; j++)
6168 {
6169 if (rce->rpsIdx == resultIdx[j])
6170 {
6171 rce->rpsIdx = j;
6172 break;
6173 }
6174 }
6175
6176 if (j == idx)
6177 rce->rpsIdx = -1;
6178 }
6179
6180 rpsIdxListIter = headRpsIdxList;
6181 while (rpsIdxListIter)
6182 {
6183 RPSListNode* freeIndex = rpsIdxListIter;
6184 rpsIdxListIter = rpsIdxListIter->next;
6185 delete freeIndex;
6186 }
6187 return true;
6188
6189fail:
6190 rpsIdxListIter = headRpsIdxList;
6191 while (rpsIdxListIter)
6192 {
6193 RPSListNode* freeIndex = rpsIdxListIter;
6194 rpsIdxListIter = rpsIdxListIter->next;
6195 delete freeIndex;
6196 }
6197 return false;
6198}
